  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: BOOK ONEPSALM 1The Righteous and the Wicked Contrasted.'
      title: BOOK ONEPSALM 1The Righteous and the Wicked Contrasted.
      number: 1
      content: '    Blessed [fortunate, prosperous, and favored by God] is the man
        who does not walk in the counsel of the wicked [following their advice and
        example],Nor stand in the path of sinners,Nor sit [down to rest] in the seat
        of scoffers (ridiculers).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But his delight is in the law of the Lord,And on His law [His precepts
        and teachings] he [habitually] meditates day and night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he will be like a tree firmly planted [and fed] by streams of
        water,Which yields its fruit in its season;Its leaf does not wither;And in
        whatever he does, he prospers [and comes to maturity].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The wicked [those who live in disobedience to God\u2019s law] are
        not so,But they are like the chaff [worthless and without substance] which
        the wind blows away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore the wicked will not stand [unpunished] in the judgment,Nor
        sinners in the assembly of the righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For the Lord knows and fully approves the way of the righteous,But
        the way of the wicked shall perish.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 2The Reign of the Lord\u2019s Anointed."
      title: "PSALM 2The Reign of the Lord\u2019s Anointed."
      number: 1
      content: '  Why are the nations in an uproar [in turmoil against God],And why
        do the people devise a vain and hopeless plot?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The kings of the earth take their stand;And the rulers take counsel
        togetherAgainst the Lord and His Anointed (the Davidic King, the Messiah,
        the Christ), saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CLet us break apart their [divine] bands [of restraint]And cast
        away their cords [of control] from us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He who sits [enthroned] in the heavens laughs [at their rebellion];The
        [Sovereign] Lord scoffs at them [and in supreme contempt He mocks them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then He will speak to them in His [profound] angerAnd terrify them
        with His displeasure, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CYet as for Me, I have anointed and firmly installed My KingUpon
        Zion, My holy mountain.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CI will declare the decree of the Lord:He said to Me, \u2018You
        are My Son;This day [I proclaim] I have begotten You.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ask of Me, and I will assuredly give [You] the nations as Your inheritance,And
        the ends of the earth as Your possession.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "You shall break them with a rod of iron;You shall shatter them [in
        pieces] like earthenware.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now therefore, O kings, act wisely;Be instructed and take warning,
        O leaders (judges, rulers) of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Worship the Lord  and serve Him with reverence [with awe-inspired
        fear and submissive wonder];Rejoice [yet do so] with trembling.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Kiss (pay respect to) the Son, so that He does not become angry, and
        you perish in the way,For His wrath may soon be kindled and set aflame.How
        blessed [fortunate, prosperous, and favored by God] are all those who take
        refuge in Him!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 3Morning Prayer of Trust in God.A Psalm of David. When he fled
        from Absalom his son.'
      title: PSALM 3Morning Prayer of Trust in God.A Psalm of David. When he fled
        from Absalom his son.
      number: 1
      content: '  O Lord, how my enemies have increased!Many are rising up against
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Many are saying of me,\u201CThere is no help [no salvation] for him
        in God.\u201D Selah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But You, O Lord, are a shield for me,My glory [and my honor], and
        the One who lifts my head.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'With my voice I was crying to the Lord,And He answered me from His
        holy mountain. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I lay down and slept [safely];I awakened, for the Lord sustains me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will not be intimidated or afraid of the ten thousandsWho have
        set themselves against me all around.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Arise, O Lord; save me, O my God!For You have struck all my enemies
        on the cheek;You have shattered the teeth of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Salvation belongs to the Lord;May Your blessing be upon Your people.
        Selah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 4Evening Prayer of Trust in God.To the Chief Musician; on stringed
        instruments. A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 4Evening Prayer of Trust in God.To the Chief Musician; on stringed
        instruments. A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Answer me when I call, O God of my righteousness!You have freed
        me when I was hemmed in and relieved me when I was in distress;Be gracious
        to me and hear [and respond to] my prayer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'O sons of men, how long will my honor and glory be [turned into]
        shame?  How long will you [my enemies] love worthless (vain, futile) things
        and seek deception and lies? Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But know that the Lord has set apart for Himself [and dealt wonderfully
        with] the godly man [the one of honorable character and moral courage\u2014the
        one who does right].The Lord hears and responds when I call to Him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Tremble [with anger or fear], and do not sin;Meditate in your heart
        upon your bed and be still [reflect on your sin and repent of your rebellion].
        Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Offer righteous sacrifices;Trust [confidently] in the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Many are saying, \u201COh, that we might see some good!\u201DLift
        up the light of Your face upon us, O Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You have put joy in my heart,More than [others know] when their wheat
        and new wine have yielded abundantly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: In peace [and with a tranquil heart] I will both lie down and sleep,For
        You alone, O Lord, make me dwell in safety and confident trust.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 5Prayer for Protection from the Wicked.To the Chief Musician;
        on wind instruments. A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 5Prayer for Protection from the Wicked.To the Chief Musician;
        on wind instruments. A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Listen to my words, O Lord,Consider my groaning and sighing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Heed the sound of my cry for help, my King and my God,For to You
        I pray.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In the morning, O Lord, You will hear my voice;In the morning I will
        prepare [a prayer and a sacrifice] for You and watch and wait [for You to
        speak to my heart].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For You are not a God who takes pleasure in wickedness;No evil [person]
        dwells with You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The boastful and the arrogant will not stand in Your sight;You hate
        all who do evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You destroy those who tell lies;The Lord detests and rejects the
        bloodthirsty and deceitful man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But as for me, I will enter Your house through the abundance of Your
        steadfast love and tender mercy;At Your holy temple I will bow [obediently]
        in reverence for You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O Lord, lead me in Your righteousness because of my enemies;Make
        Your way straight (direct, right) before me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For there is nothing trustworthy or reliable or truthful in what
        they say;Their heart is destruction [just a treacherous chasm, a yawning
        gulf of lies].Their throat is an open grave;They [glibly] flatter with their
        [silken] tongue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Hold them guilty, O God;Let them fall by their own designs and councils!Cast
        them out because of the abundance of their transgressions,For they are mutinous
        and have rebelled against You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But let all who take refuge and put their trust in You rejoice,Let
        them ever sing for joy;Because You cover and shelter them,Let those who love
        Your name be joyful and exult in You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: For You, O Lord, bless the righteous man [the one who is in right
        standing with You];You surround him with favor as with a shield.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 6Prayer for Mercy in Time of Trouble.To the Chief Musician;
        on stringed instruments, set [possibly] an octave below. A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 6Prayer for Mercy in Time of Trouble.To the Chief Musician; on
        stringed instruments, set [possibly] an octave below. A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  O Lord, do not rebuke or punish me in Your anger,Nor discipline
        me in Your wrath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Have mercy on me and be gracious to me, O Lord, for I am weak (faint,
        frail);Heal me, O Lord, for my bones are dismayed and anguished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "My soul [as well as my body] is greatly dismayed.But as for You,
        O Lord\u2014how long [until You act on my behalf]?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Return, O Lord, rescue my soul;Save me because of Your [unfailing]
        steadfast love and mercy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For in death there is no mention of You;In Sheol (the nether world,
        the place of the dead) who will praise You and give You thanks?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I am weary with my groaning;Every night I soak my bed with tears,I
        drench my couch with my weeping.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'My eye grows dim with grief;It grows old because of all my enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Depart from me, all you who do evil,For the Lord has heard the voice
        of my weeping.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Lord has heard my supplication [my plea for grace];The Lord receives
        my prayer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Let all my enemies be ashamed and greatly horrified;Let them turn
        back, let them suddenly be ashamed [of what they have done].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 7The Lord Implored to Defend the Psalmist against the Wicked.An
        Meaning uncertain, perhaps a wild, enthusiastic song. The ancient rabbis
        connected the Hebrew word to another word of similar spelling meaning \u201Cinadvertent
        sin\u201D or \u201Cerror,\u201D and maintained that God called David to account
        for what he said in 6:10. He had in essence cursed his enemies, and God supposedly
        pointed out that Saul was David\u2019s enemy, so David thereby had cursed
        Saul in violation of Ex 22:28. David pleaded with God to count this a sin
        of error on his part, and thereafter composed Ps 7. The rabbis also maintained
        that Cush was a reference to Saul (cf 1&nbsp;Sam 9:1).Ode of David, [perhaps
        in a wild, irregular, enthusiastic strain,] which he sang to the Lord concerning
        the words of Cush, a Benjamite."
      title: "PSALM 7The Lord Implored to Defend the Psalmist against the Wicked.An
        Meaning uncertain, perhaps a wild, enthusiastic song. The ancient rabbis
        connected the Hebrew word to another word of similar spelling meaning \u201Cinadvertent
        sin\u201D or \u201Cerror,\u201D and maintained that God called David to account
        for what he said in 6:10. He had in essence cursed his enemies, and God supposedly
        pointed out that Saul was David\u2019s enemy, so David thereby had cursed
        Saul in violation of Ex 22:28. David pleaded with God to count this a sin
        of error on his part, and thereafter composed Ps 7. The rabbis also maintained
        that Cush was a reference to Saul (cf 1&nbsp;Sam 9:1).Ode of David, [perhaps
        in a wild, irregular, enthusiastic strain,] which he sang to the Lord concerning
        the words of Cush, a Benjamite."
      number: 1
      content: '  O Lord my God, in You I take refuge;Save me and rescue me from
        all those who pursue me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So that my enemy will not tear me like a lion,Dragging me away while
        there is no one to rescue [me].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'O Lord my God, if I have done this,If there is injustice in my hands,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If I have done evil to him who was at peace with me,Or without cause
        robbed him who was my enemy,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Let the enemy pursue me and overtake me;And let him trample my life
        to the groundAnd lay my honor in the dust. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Arise, O Lord, in Your anger;Lift up Yourself against the rage of
        my enemies;Rise up for me; You have commanded judgment and vindication.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Let the assembly of the nations be gathered around You,And return
        on high over them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord judges the peoples;Judge me, O Lord, and grant me justice
        according to my righteousness and according to the integrity within me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Oh, let the wickedness of the wicked come to an end, but establish
        the righteous [those in right standing with You];For the righteous God tries
        the hearts and minds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'My shield and my defense depend on God,Who saves the upright in heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'God is a righteous judge,And a God who is indignant every day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'If a man does not repent, God will sharpen His sword;He has strung
        and bent His [mighty] bow and made it ready.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He has also prepared [other] deadly weapons for Himself;He makes
        His arrows fiery shafts [aimed at the unrepentant].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Behold, the [wicked and irreverent] man is pregnant with sin,And
        he conceives mischief and gives birth to lies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He has dug a pit and hollowed it out,And has fallen into the [very]
        pit which he made [as a trap].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'His mischief will return on his own head,And his violence will come
        down on the top of his head [like loose dirt].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I will give thanks to the Lord according to His righteousness and
        justice,And I will sing praise to the name of the Lord Most High.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 8The Lord\u2019s Glory and Man\u2019s Dignity.To the Chief
        Musician; set to Or perhaps to a particular key; meaning uncertain.a Philistine
        lute [or perhaps to a particular Hittite tune]. A Psalm of David."
      title: "PSALM 8The Lord\u2019s Glory and Man\u2019s Dignity.To the Chief Musician;
        set to Or perhaps to a particular key; meaning uncertain.a Philistine lute
        [or perhaps to a particular Hittite tune]. A Psalm of David."
      number: 1
      content: '  O Lord, our Lord,How majestic and glorious and excellent is Your
        name in all the earth!You have displayed Your splendor above the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Out of the mouths of infants and nursing babes You have established
        strengthBecause of Your adversaries,That You might silence the enemy and
        make the revengeful cease.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When I see and consider Your heavens, the work of Your fingers,The
        moon and the stars, which You have established,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'What is man that You are mindful of him,And the son of [earthborn]
        man that You care for him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Yet You have made him a little lower than God,And You have crowned
        him with glory and honor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You made him to have dominion over the works of Your hands;You have
        put all things under his feet,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All sheep and oxen,And also the beasts of the field,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The birds of the air, and the fish of the sea,Whatever passes through
        the paths of the seas.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: O Lord, our Lord,How majestic and glorious and excellent is Your name
        in all the earth!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 9A Psalm of Thanksgiving for God\u2019s Justice.To the Chief
        Musician; on A transliteration of the Hebrew, whose meaning is unknown. Possibly
        referring to a tune titled \u201CDeath to the Son.\u201D Perhaps for soprano
        voices.Muth-labben. A Psalm of David."
      title: "PSALM 9A Psalm of Thanksgiving for God\u2019s Justice.To the Chief
        Musician; on A transliteration of the Hebrew, whose meaning is unknown. Possibly
        referring to a tune titled \u201CDeath to the Son.\u201D Perhaps for soprano
        voices.Muth-labben. A Psalm of David."
      number: 1
      content: '  I will give thanks and praise the Lord, with all my heart;I will
        tell aloud all Your wonders and marvelous deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will rejoice and exult in you;I will sing praise to Your name,
        O Most High.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When my enemies turn back,They stumble and perish before You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For You have maintained my right and my cause;You have sat on the
        throne judging righteously.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You have rebuked the nations, You have destroyed the wicked and unrepentant;You
        have wiped out their name forever and ever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The enemy has been cut off and has vanished in everlasting ruins,You
        have uprooted their cities;The very memory of them has perished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But the Lord will remain and sit enthroned forever;He has prepared
        and established His throne for judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And He will judge the world in righteousness;He will execute judgment
        for the nations with fairness (equity).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Lord also will be a refuge and a stronghold for the oppressed,A
        refuge in times of trouble;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And those who know Your name [who have experienced Your precious
        mercy] will put their confident trust in You,For You, O Lord, have not abandoned
        those who seek You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Sing praises to the Lord, who dwells in Zion;Declare among the peoples
        His [great and wondrous] deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For He who avenges blood [unjustly shed] remembers them (His people);He
        does not forget the cry of the afflicted and abused.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Have mercy on me and be gracious to me, O Lord;See how I am afflicted
        by those who hate me,You who lift me up from the gates of death,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'That I may tell aloud all Your praises,That in the gates of the daughter
        of Zion (Jerusalem)I may rejoice in Your salvation and Your help.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The nations have sunk down in the pit which they have made;In the
        net which they hid, their own foot has been caught.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The Lord has made Himself known;He executes judgment;The wicked are
        trapped by the work of their own hands. Higgaion (meditation) Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The wicked will turn to Sheol (the nether world, the place of the
        dead),  Even all the nations who forget God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For the poor will not always be forgotten,Nor the hope of the burdened
        perish forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Arise, O Lord, do not let man prevail;Let the nations be judged before
        You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Put them in [reverent] fear of You, O Lord,So that the nations may
        know they are but [frail and mortal] men. Selah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 10A Prayer for the Overthrow of the Wicked.'
      title: PSALM 10A Prayer for the Overthrow of the Wicked.
      number: 1
      content: '  Why do You stand far away, O Lord?Why do You hide [Yourself, veiling
        Your eyes] in times of trouble?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'In pride and arrogance the wicked hotly pursue and persecute the
        afflicted;Let them be caught in the plots which they have devised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For the wicked boasts and sings the praises of his heart\u2019s desire,And
        the greedy man curses and spurns [and even despises] the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The wicked, in the haughtiness of his face, will not seek nor inquire
        for Him;All his thoughts are, \u201CThere is no God [so there is no accountability
        or punishment].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'His ways prosper at all times;Your judgments [Lord] are on high,
        out of his sight [so he never thinks about them];As for all his enemies,
        he sneers at them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He says to himself, \u201CI will not be moved;For throughout all
        generations I will not be in adversity [for nothing bad will happen to me].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'His mouth is full of curses and deceit (fraud) and oppression;Under
        his tongue is mischief and wickedness [injustice and sin].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He lurks in ambush in the villages;In hiding places he kills the
        innocent;He lies in wait for the unfortunate [the unhappy, the poor, the
        helpless].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He lurks in a hiding place like a lion in his lair;He lies in wait
        to catch the afflicted;He catches the afflicted when he draws him into his
        net.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He crushes [his prey] and crouches;And the unfortunate fall by his
        mighty claws.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He says to himself, \u201CGod has [quite] forgotten;He has hidden
        His face; He will never see my deed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Arise, O Lord! O God, lift up Your hand [in judgment];Do not forget
        the suffering.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Why has the wicked spurned and shown disrespect to God?He has said
        to himself, \u201CYou will not require me to account.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You have seen it, for You have noted mischief and vexation (irritation)
        to take it into Your hand.The unfortunate commits himself to You;You are
        the helper of the fatherless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Break the arm of the wicked and the evildoer,Seek out his wickedness
        until You find no more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The Lord is King forever and ever;The nations will perish from His
        land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'O Lord, You have heard the desire of the humble and oppressed;You
        will strengthen their heart, You will incline Your ear to hear,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: To vindicate and obtain justice for the fatherless and the oppressed,So
        that man who is of the earth will no longer terrify them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 11The Lord a Refuge and Defense.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm
        of David.'
      title: PSALM 11The Lord a Refuge and Defense.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm
        of David.
      number: 1
      content: "  In the Lord I take refuge [and put my trust];How can you say to
        me, \u201CFlee like a bird to your mountain;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For look, the wicked are bending the bow;They take aim with their
        arrow on the stringTo shoot [by stealth] in darkness at the upright in heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "If the foundations [of a godly society] are destroyed,What can the
        righteous do?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The Lord is in His holy temple; the Lord\u2019s throne is in heaven.His
        eyes see, His eyelids test the children of men.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord tests the righteous and the wicked,And His soul hates the
        [malevolent] one who loves violence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Upon the wicked (godless) He will rain coals of fire;Fire and brimstone
        and a dreadful scorching wind will be the portion of their cup [of doom].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: For the Lord is [absolutely] righteous, He loves righteousness (virtue,
        morality, justice);The upright shall see His face.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 12God, a Helper against the Treacherous.To the Chief Musician;
        Or possibly on the eight-stringed lyre; meaning uncertain.set an octave below.
        A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 12God, a Helper against the Treacherous.To the Chief Musician;
        Or possibly on the eight-stringed lyre; meaning uncertain.set an octave below.
        A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Save and help and rescue, Lord, for godly people cease to be,For
        the faithful vanish from among the sons of men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They speak deceitful and worthless words to one another;With flattering
        lips and a double heart they speak.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'May the Lord cut off all flattering lips,The tongue that speaks great
        things [in boasting];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Who have said, \u201CWith our tongue we will prevail;Our lips are
        our own; who is lord and master over us?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CBecause of the devastation of the afflicted, because of the
        groaning of the needy,Now I will arise,\u201D says the Lord; \u201CI will
        place him in the safety for which he longs.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The words and promises of the Lord are pure words,Like silver refined
        in an earthen furnace, purified seven times.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You, O Lord, will preserve and keep them;You will protect him from
        this [evil] generation forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The wicked strut about [in pompous self-importance] on every side,As
        vileness is exalted and baseness is prized among the sons of men.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 13Prayer for Help in Trouble.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm
        of David.'
      title: PSALM 13Prayer for Help in Trouble.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of
        David.
      number: 1
      content: '  How long, O Lord? Will You forget me forever?How long will You
        hide Your face from me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'How long must I take counsel in my soul,  Having sorrow in my heart
        day after day?How long will my enemy exalt himself and triumph over me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Consider and answer me, O Lord my God;Give light (life) to my eyes,
        or I will sleep the sleep of death,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And my enemy will say, \u201CI have overcome him,\u201DAnd my adversaries
        will rejoice when I am shaken.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But I have trusted and relied on and been confident in Your lovingkindness
        and faithfulness;My heart shall rejoice and delight in Your salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: I will sing to the Lord,Because He has dealt bountifully with me.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 14Folly and Wickedness of Men.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm
        of David.'
      title: PSALM 14Folly and Wickedness of Men.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of
        David.
      number: 1
      content: "  The [spiritually ignorant] fool has said in his heart, \u201CThere
        is no God.\u201DThey are corrupt, they have committed repulsive and unspeakable
        deeds;There is no one who does good.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord has looked down from heaven upon the children of menTo see
        if there are any who understand (act wisely),Who [truly] seek after God,
        [longing for His wisdom and guidance].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They have all turned aside, together they have become corrupt;There
        is no one who does good, not even one.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Have all the workers of wickedness and injustice no knowledge,Who
        eat up my people as they eat bread,And do not call upon the Lord?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'There they tremble with great fear,For God is with the [consistently]
        righteous generation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You [evildoers] shamefully plan against the poor,But the Lord is
        his safe refuge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Oh, that the salvation of Israel would come out of Zion!When the Lord
        restores His captive people,Then Jacob will rejoice, Israel will be glad.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 15Description of a Citizen of Zion.A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 15Description of a Citizen of Zion.A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  O Lord, who may lodge [as a guest] in Your tent?Who may dwell [continually]
        on Your holy hill?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He who walks with integrity and strength of character, and works
        righteousness,And speaks and holds truth in his heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He does not slander with his tongue,Nor does evil to his neighbor,Nor
        takes up a reproach against his friend;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'In his eyes an evil person is despised,But he honors those who fear
        the Lord [and obediently worship Him with awe-inspired reverence and submissive
        wonder].He keeps his word even to his own disadvantage and does not change
        it [for his own benefit];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: He does not put out his money at interest [to a fellow Israelite],And
        does not take a bribe against the innocent.He who does these things will
        never be shaken.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 16The Lord, the Psalmist\u2019s Portion in Life and Deliverer
        in Death.A Meaning uncertain; perhaps a poem.Mikhtam of David [probably intended
        to record memorable thoughts]."
      title: "PSALM 16The Lord, the Psalmist\u2019s Portion in Life and Deliverer
        in Death.A Meaning uncertain; perhaps a poem.Mikhtam of David [probably intended
        to record memorable thoughts]."
      number: 1
      content: '  Keep and protect me, O God, for in You I have placed my trust and
        found refuge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I said to the Lord, \u201CYou are my Lord;I have no good besides
        You.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'As for the saints (godly people) who are in the land,They are the
        majestic and the noble and the excellent ones in whom is all my delight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The sorrows [pain and suffering] of those who have chosen another
        god will be multiplied [because of their idolatry];I will not pour out their
        drink offerings of blood,Nor will I take their names upon my lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord is the portion of my inheritance, my cup [He is all I need];You
        support my lot.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The [boundary] lines [of the land] have fallen for me in pleasant
        places;Indeed, my heritage is beautiful to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will bless the Lord who has counseled me;Indeed, my heart (mind)
        instructs me in the night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I have set the Lord continually before me;Because He is at my right
        hand, I will not be shaken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore my heart is glad and my glory [my innermost self] rejoices;My
        body too will dwell [confidently] in safety,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For You will not abandon me to Sheol (the nether world, the place
        of the dead),Nor will You allow Your Holy One to undergo decay.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: You will show me the path of life;In Your presence is fullness of
        joy;In Your right hand there are pleasures forevermore.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 17Prayer for Protection against Oppressors.A Prayer of David.'
      title: PSALM 17Prayer for Protection against Oppressors.A Prayer of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear the just (righteous) cause, O Lord; listen to my loud [piercing]
        cry;Listen to my prayer, that comes from guileless lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Let my verdict of vindication come from Your presence;May Your eyes
        look with equity and behold things that are just.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You have tried my heart;You have visited me in the night;You have
        tested me and You find nothing [evil in me];I intend that my mouth will not
        transgress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Concerning the deeds of men, by the word of Your lipsI have kept
        away from the paths of the violent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'My steps have held closely to Your paths;My feet have not staggered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I have called upon You, for You, O God, will answer me;Incline Your
        ear to me, hear my speech.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Wondrously show Your [marvelous and amazing] lovingkindness,O Savior
        of those who take refuge at Your right handFrom those who rise up against
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Keep me [in Your affectionate care, protect me] as the apple of Your
        eye;Hide me in the [protective] shadow of Your wings  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'From the wicked who despoil and deal violently with me,My deadly
        enemies who surround me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They have closed their unfeeling heart [to kindness and compassion];With
        their mouths they speak proudly and make presumptuous claims.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They track us down and have now surrounded us in our steps;They set
        their eyes to force us to the ground,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He is like a lion eager to tear [his prey],And like a young lion
        lurking in hiding places.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Arise, O Lord, confront him, cast him down;Save my soul from the
        wicked with Your sword,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "From men with Your hand, O Lord,From men of the world [these moths
        of the night] whose portion [of enjoyment] is in this life\u2014idle and
        vain,And whose belly You fill with Your treasure;They are satisfied with
        children,And they leave what they have left [of wealth] to their children.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: As for me, I shall see Your face in righteousness;I will be [fully]
        satisfied when I awake [to find myself] seeing Your likeness.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 18David Praises the Lord for Rescuing Him.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David, the servant of the Lord, who spoke the words of this song
        to the Lord on the day when the Lord rescued him from the hand of all his
        enemies and from the hand of Saul. And he said:'
      title: 'PSALM 18David Praises the Lord for Rescuing Him.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David, the servant of the Lord, who spoke the words of this song
        to the Lord on the day when the Lord rescued him from the hand of all his
        enemies and from the hand of Saul. And he said:'
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CI love You [fervently and devotedly], O Lord, my strength.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Lord is my rock, my fortress, and the One who rescues me;My God,
        my rock and strength in whom I trust and take refuge;My shield, and the horn
        of my salvation, my high tower\u2014my stronghold.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I call upon the Lord, who is worthy to be praised;And I am saved
        from my enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The cords of death surrounded me,And the streams of ungodliness and
        torrents of destruction terrified me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The cords of Sheol (the nether world, the place of the dead) surrounded
        me;The snares of death confronted me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In my distress [when I seemed surrounded] I called upon the LordAnd
        cried to my God for help;He heard my voice from His temple,And my cry for
        help came before Him, into His very ears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the earth shook and quaked,The foundations of the mountains
        trembled;They were shaken because He was indignant and angry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Smoke went up from His nostrils,And fire from His mouth devoured;Coals
        were kindled by it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He bowed the heavens also and came down;And thick darkness was under
        His feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And He rode upon a cherub (storm) and flew;And He sped on the wings
        of the wind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He made darkness His hiding place (covering); His pavilion (canopy)
        around Him,The darkness of the waters, the thick clouds of the skies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Out of the brightness before Him passed His thick clouds,Hailstones
        and coals of fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The Lord also thundered in the heavens,And the Most High uttered
        His voice,Hailstones and coals of fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He sent out His arrows and scattered them;And He sent an abundance
        of lightning flashes and confused and routed them [in defeat].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the stream beds of the waters appeared,And the foundations of
        the world were laid bareAt Your rebuke, O Lord,At the blast of the breath
        of Your nostrils.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He reached from on high, He took me;He drew me out of many waters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He rescued me from my strong enemy,And from those who hated me, for
        they were too strong for me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They confronted me in the day of my disaster,But the Lord was my
        support.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He brought me out into a broad place;He rescued me because He was
        pleased with me and delighted in me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The Lord dealt with me according to my righteousness (moral character,
        spiritual integrity);According to the cleanness of my hands He has rewarded
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For I have kept the ways of the Lord,And have not wickedly departed
        from my God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For all His ordinances were before me,And I did not put away His
        statutes from me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I was blameless before Him,And I kept myself free from my sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Therefore the Lord has rewarded me according to my righteousness
        (moral character, spiritual integrity),According to the cleanness of my hands
        in His sight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'With the kind (merciful, faithful, loyal) You show Yourself kind,With
        the blameless You show Yourself blameless,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'With the pure You show Yourself pure,And with the crooked You show
        Yourself astute.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For You save an afflicted and humble people,But bring down those
        [arrogant fools] with haughty eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For You cause my lamp to be lighted and to shine;The Lord my God
        illumines my darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For by You I can crush a troop,And by my God I can leap over a wall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'As for God, His way is blameless.The word of the Lord is tested [it
        is perfect, it is faultless];He is a shield to all who take refuge in Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For who is God, but the Lord?Or who is a rock, except our God,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The God who encircles me with strengthAnd makes my way blameless?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "He makes my feet like hinds\u2019 feet [able to stand firmly and
        tread safely on paths of testing and trouble];He sets me [securely] upon
        my high places.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'He trains my hands for war,So that my arms can bend a bow of bronze.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'You have also given me the shield of Your salvation,And Your right
        hand upholds and sustains me;Your gentleness [Your gracious response when
        I pray] makes me great.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'You enlarge the path beneath me and make my steps secure,So that
        my feet will not slip.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'I pursued my enemies and overtook them;And I did not turn back until
        they were consumed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'I shattered them so that they were not able to rise;They fell [wounded]
        under my feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'For You have encircled me with strength for the battle;You have subdued
        under me those who rose up against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'You have also made my enemies turn their backs to me [in defeat],And
        I silenced and destroyed those who hated me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "They cried for help, but there was no one to save them\u2014Even
        to the Lord [they cried], but He did not answer them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Then I beat them fine as the dust before the wind;I emptied them
        out as the dirt of the streets.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'You have rescued me from the contentions of the people;You have placed
        me as the head of the nations;A people whom I have not known serve me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'As soon as they hear me, they respond and obey me;Foreigners feign
        obedience to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Foreigners lose heart,And come trembling out of their strongholds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'The Lord lives, blessed be my rock;And may the God of my salvation
        be exalted,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'The God who avenges me,And subdues peoples (nations) under me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'He rescues me from my enemies;Yes, You lift me up above those who
        rise up against me;You deliver me from the man of violence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Therefore will I give thanks and praise You, O Lord, among the nations,And
        sing praises to Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: He gives great triumphs to His king,And shows steadfast love and mercy
        to His anointed,To David and his descendants forever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 19The Works and the Word of God.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm
        of David.'
      title: PSALM 19The Works and the Word of God.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm
        of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  The heavens are telling of the glory of God;And the expanse [of
        heaven] is declaring the work of His hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Day after day pours forth speech,And night after night reveals knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'There is no speech, nor are there [spoken] words [from the stars];Their
        voice is not heard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Yet their voice [in quiet evidence] has gone out through all the
        earth,Their words to the end of the world.In them and in the heavens He has
        made a tent for the sun,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Which is as a bridegroom coming out of his chamber;It rejoices as
        a strong man to run his course.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The sun\u2019s rising is from one end of the heavens,And its circuit
        to the other end of them;And there is nothing hidden from its heat.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The law of the Lord is perfect (flawless), restoring and refreshing
        the soul;The statutes of the Lord are reliable and trustworthy, making wise
        the simple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The precepts of the Lord are right, bringing joy to the heart;The
        commandment of the Lord is pure, enlightening the eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The fear of the Lord is clean, enduring forever;The judgments of
        the Lord are true, they are righteous altogether.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They are more desirable than gold, yes, than much fine gold;Sweeter
        also than honey and the drippings of the honeycomb.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Moreover, by them Your servant is warned [reminded, illuminated,
        and instructed];In keeping them there is great reward.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Who can understand his errors or omissions? Acquit me of hidden (unconscious,
        unintended) faults.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Also keep back Your servant from presumptuous (deliberate, willful)
        sins;Let them not rule and have control over me.Then I will be blameless
        (complete),And I shall be acquitted of great transgression.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Let the words of my mouth and the meditation of my heartBe acceptable
        and pleasing in Your sight,O Lord, my [firm, immovable] rock and my Redeemer.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 20Prayer for Victory over Enemies.To the Chief Musician. A
        Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 20Prayer for Victory over Enemies.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm
        of David.
      number: 1
      content: '    May the Lord answer you (David) in the day of trouble!May the
        name of the God of Jacob set you securely on high [and defend you in battle]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'May He send you help from the sanctuary (His dwelling place)And support
        and strengthen you from Zion!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'May He remember all your meal offeringsAnd accept your burnt offering.
        Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "May He grant you your heart\u2019s desireAnd fulfill all your plans.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'We will sing joyously over your victory,And in the name of our God
        we will set up our banners.May the Lord fulfill all your petitions.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now I know that the Lord saves His anointed;He will answer him from
        His holy heavenWith the saving strength of His right hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Some trust in chariots and some in horses,But we will remember and
        trust in the name of the Lord our God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They have bowed down and fallen,But we have risen and stood upright.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: O Lord, save [the king];May the King answer us in the day we call.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 21Praise for Help.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 21Praise for Help.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  O Lord the king will delight in Your strength,And in Your salvation
        how greatly will he rejoice!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "You have given him his heart\u2019s desire,And You have not withheld
        the request of his lips. Selah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For You meet him with blessings of good things;You set a crown of
        pure gold on his head.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He asked life of You,And You gave it to him,Long life forever and
        evermore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'His glory is great because of Your victory;Splendor and majesty You
        bestow upon him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For You make him most blessed [and a blessing] forever;You make him
        joyful with the joy of Your presence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For the king [confidently] trusts in the Lord,And through the lovingkindness
        (faithfulness, goodness) of the Most High he will never be shaken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Your hand will reach out and defeat all your enemies;Your right hand
        will reach those who hate you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You will make them as [if in] a blazing oven in the time of your
        anger;The Lord will swallow them up in His wrath,And the fire will devour
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Their offspring You will destroy from the earth,And their descendants
        from the sons of men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For they planned evil against You;They devised a [malevolent] plotAnd
        they will not succeed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For You will make them turn their backs [in defeat];You will aim
        Your bowstring [of divine justice] at their faces.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Be exalted, Lord, in Your strength;We will sing and praise Your power.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 22A Cry of Anguish and a Song of Praise.To the Chief Musician;
        set to [the tune of] Aijeleth Hashshahar (The Doe of the Dawn). A Psalm of
        David.'
      title: PSALM 22A Cry of Anguish and a Song of Praise.To the Chief Musician;
        set to [the tune of] Aijeleth Hashshahar (The Doe of the Dawn). A Psalm of
        David.
      number: 1
      content: '    My God, my God, why have You forsaken me?Why are You so far from
        helping me, and from the words of my groaning?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'O my God, I call out by day, but You do not answer;And by night,
        but I find no rest nor quiet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But You are holy,O You who are enthroned in [the holy place where]
        the praises of Israel [are offered].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'In You our fathers trusted [leaned on, relied on, and were confident];They
        trusted and You rescued them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They cried out to You and were delivered;They trusted in You and
        were not disappointed or ashamed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But I am [treated as] a worm [insignificant and powerless] and not
        a man;I am the scorn of men and despised by the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All who see me laugh at me and mock me;They [insultingly] open their
        lips, they shake their head, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CHe trusted and committed himself to the Lord, let Him save
        him.Let Him rescue him, because He delights in him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Yet You are He who pulled me out of the womb;You made me trust when
        on my mother\u2019s breasts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I was cast upon You from birth;From my mother\u2019s womb You have
        been my God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Do not be far from me, for trouble is near;And there is no one to
        help.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Many [enemies like] bulls have surrounded me;Strong bulls of Bashan
        have encircled me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They open wide their mouths against me,Like a ravening and a roaring
        lion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I am poured out like water,And all my bones are out of joint.My heart
        is like wax;It is melted [by anguish] within me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'My strength is dried up like a fragment of clay pottery;And my [dry]
        tongue clings to my jaws;And You have laid me in the dust of death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For [a pack of] dogs have surrounded me;A gang of evildoers has encircled
        me,They pierced my hands and my feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I can count all my bones;They look, they stare at me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They divide my clothing among themAnd cast lots for my garment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But You, O Lord, do not be far from me;O You my help, come quickly
        to my assistance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Rescue my life from the sword,My only life from the paw of the dog
        (the executioner).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Save me from the lion\u2019s mouth;From the horns of the wild oxen
        You answer me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'I will tell of Your name to my countrymen;In the midst of the congregation
        I will praise You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'You who fear the Lord [with awe-inspired reverence], praise Him!All
        you descendants of Jacob, honor Him.Fear Him [with submissive wonder], all
        you descendants of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For He has not despised nor detested the suffering of the afflicted;Nor
        has He hidden His face from him;But when he cried to Him for help, He listened.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'My praise will be of You in the great assembly.I will pay my vows
        [made in the time of trouble] before those who [reverently] fear Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The afflicted will eat and be satisfied;Those who [diligently] seek
        Him and require Him [as their greatest need] will praise the Lord.May your
        hearts live forever!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'All the ends of the earth will remember and turn to the Lord,And
        all the families of the nations will bow down and worship before You,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For the kingship and the kingdom are the Lord\u2019sAnd He rules
        over the nations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'All the prosperous of the earth will eat and worship;All those who
        go down to the dust (the dead) will bow before Him,Even he who cannot keep
        his soul alive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Posterity will serve Him;They will tell of the Lord to the next generation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "They will come and declare His righteousnessTo a people yet to be
        born\u2014that He has done it [and that it is finished]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 23The Lord, the Psalmist\u2019s Shepherd.A Psalm of David."
      title: "PSALM 23The Lord, the Psalmist\u2019s Shepherd.A Psalm of David."
      number: 1
      content: '  The Lord is my Shepherd [to feed, to guide and to shield me],I
        shall not want.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He lets me lie down in green pastures;He leads me beside the still
        and quiet waters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He refreshes and restores my soul (life);He leads me in the paths
        of righteousnessfor His name\u2019s sake.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Even though I walk through the [sunless] valley of the shadow of
        death,I fear no evil, for You are with me;Your rod [to protect] and Your
        staff [to guide], they comfort and console me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies.You have
        anointed and refreshed my head with oil;My cup overflows.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Surely goodness and mercy and unfailing love shall follow me all the
        days of my life,And I shall dwell forever [throughout all my days] in the
        house and in the presence of the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 24The King of Glory Entering Zion.  In the Talmud it is said
        that the Levites sang a particular psalm for every day of the week, and this
        was the psalm for the first day.A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 24The King of Glory Entering Zion.  In the Talmud it is said that
        the Levites sang a particular psalm for every day of the week, and this was
        the psalm for the first day.A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: "  The earth is the Lord\u2019s, and the fullness of it,The world,
        and those who dwell in it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For He has founded it upon the seasAnd established it upon the streams
        and the rivers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Who may ascend onto the mountain of the Lord?And who may stand in
        His holy place?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He who has clean hands and a pure heart,Who has not lifted up his
        soul to what is false,Nor has sworn [oaths] deceitfully.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He shall receive a blessing from the Lord,And righteousness from
        the God of his salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'This is the generation (description) of those who diligently seek
        Him and require Him as their greatest need,Who seek Your face, even [as did]
        Jacob. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Lift up your heads, O gates,And be lifted up, ancient doors,That
        the King of glory may come in.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who is the King of glory?The Lord strong and mighty,The Lord mighty
        in battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Lift up your heads, O gates,And lift them up, ancient doors,That
        the King of glory may come in.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Who is [He then] this King of glory?The Lord of hosts,He is the King
        of glory [who rules over all creation with His heavenly armies]. Selah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 25Prayer for Protection, Guidance and Pardon.  A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 25Prayer for Protection, Guidance and Pardon.  A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  To You, O Lord, I lift up my soul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'O my God, in You I [have unwavering] trust [and I rely on You with
        steadfast confidence],Do not let me be ashamed or my hope in You be disappointed;Do
        not let my enemies triumph over me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Indeed, none of those who [expectantly] wait for You will be ashamed;Those
        who turn away from what is right and deal treacherously without cause will
        be ashamed (humiliated, embarrassed).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Let me know Your ways, O Lord;Teach me Your paths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Guide me in Your truth and teach me,For You are the God of my salvation;For
        You [and only You] I wait [expectantly] all the day long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Remember, O Lord, Your [tender] compassion and Your lovingkindnesses,For
        they have been from of old.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Do not remember the sins of my youth or my transgressions;According
        to Your lovingkindness remember me,For Your goodness\u2019 sake, O Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Good and upright is the Lord;Therefore He instructs sinners in the
        way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He leads the humble in justice,And He teaches the humble His way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'All the paths of the Lord are lovingkindness and goodness and truth
        and faithfulnessTo those who keep His covenant and His testimonies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For Your name\u2019s sake, O Lord,Pardon my wickedness and my guilt,
        for they are great.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Who is the man who fears the Lord [with awe-inspired reverence and
        worships Him with submissive wonder]?He will teach him [through His word]
        in the way he should choose.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'His soul will dwell in prosperity and goodness,And his descendants
        will inherit the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The secret [of the wise counsel] of the Lord is for those who fear
        Him,And He will let them know His covenant and reveal to them [through His
        word] its [deep, inner] meaning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'My eyes are continually toward the Lord,For He will bring my feet
        out of the net.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Turn to me [Lord] and be gracious to me,For I am alone and afflicted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The troubles of my heart are multiplied;Bring me out of my distresses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Look upon my affliction and my trouble,And forgive all my sins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Look upon my enemies, for they are many;They hate me with cruel and
        violent hatred.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Guard my soul and rescue me;Do not let me be ashamed or disappointed,For
        I have taken refuge in You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Let integrity and uprightness protect me,For I wait [expectantly]
        for You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: O God, redeem Israel,Out of all his troubles.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 26Protestation of Integrity and Prayer for Protection.  A Psalm
        of David.'
      title: PSALM 26Protestation of Integrity and Prayer for Protection.  A Psalm
        of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Vindicate me, O Lord, for I have walked in my integrity;I have
        [relied on and] trusted [confidently] in the Lord without wavering and I
        shall not slip.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Examine me, O Lord, and try me;Test my heart and my mind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For Your lovingkindness is before my eyes,And I have walked [faithfully]
        in Your truth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I do not sit with deceitful or unethical or worthless men,Nor seek
        companionship with pretenders (self-righteous hypocrites).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I hate the company of evildoers,And will not sit with the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will wash my hands in innocence,And I will go about Your altar,
        O Lord,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'That I may proclaim with the voice of thanksgivingAnd declare all
        Your wonders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O Lord, I love the habitation of Your houseAnd the place where Your
        glory dwells.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not sweep my soul away with sinners,Nor [sweep away] my life with
        men of bloodshed,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In whose hands is a wicked scheme,And whose right hand is full of
        bribes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But as for me, I shall walk in my integrity;Redeem me and be merciful
        and gracious to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: My foot stands on a level place;In the congregations I will bless
        the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 27A Psalm of Fearless Trust in God.  A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 27A Psalm of Fearless Trust in God.  A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: "  The Lord is my light and my salvation\u2014Whom shall I fear?The
        Lord is the refuge and fortress of my life\u2014Whom shall I dread?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When the wicked came against me to eat up my flesh,My adversaries
        and my enemies, they stumbled and fell.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Though an army encamp against me,My heart will not fear;Though war
        arise against me,Even in this I am confident.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'One thing I have asked of the Lord, and that I will seek:That I may
        dwell in the house of the Lord [in His presence] all the days of my life,To
        gaze upon the beauty [the delightful loveliness and majestic grandeur] of
        the LordAnd to meditate in His temple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For in the day of trouble He will hide me in His shelter;In the secret
        place of His tent He will hide me;He will lift me up on a rock.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And now my head will be lifted up above my enemies around me,In His
        tent I will offer sacrifices with shouts of joy;I will sing, yes, I will
        sing praises to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Hear, O Lord, when I cry aloud;Be gracious and compassionate to me
        and answer me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  When You said, \u201CSeek My face [in prayer, require My presence
        as your greatest need],\u201D my heart said to You,\u201CYour face, O Lord,
        I will seek [on the authority of Your word].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not hide Your face from me,Do not turn Your servant away in anger;You
        have been my help;Do not abandon me nor leave me,O God of my salvation!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Although my father and my mother have abandoned me,Yet the Lord will
        take me up [adopt me as His child].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Teach me Your way, O Lord,And lead me on a level pathBecause of my
        enemies [who lie in wait].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Do not give me up to the will of my adversaries,For false witnesses
        have come against me;They breathe out violence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  I would have despaired had I not believed that I would see the
        goodness of the LordIn the land of the living.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Wait for and confidently expect the Lord;Be strong and let your heart
        take courage;Yes, wait for and confidently expect the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 28A Prayer for Help, and Praise for Its Answer.  A Psalm of
        David.'
      title: PSALM 28A Prayer for Help, and Praise for Its Answer.  A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  To you I call, O Lord,My rock, do not be deaf to me,For if You
        are silent to me,I will become like those who go down to the pit (grave).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Hear the voice of my supplication (specific requests, humble entreaties)
        as I cry to You for help,As I lift up my hands and heart toward Your innermost
        sanctuary (Holy of Holies).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Do not drag me away with the wickedAnd with those who do evil,Who
        speak peace with their neighbors,While malice and mischief are in their hearts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Repay them according to their work and according to the evil of their
        practices;Repay them according to the deeds of their hands;Repay them what
        they deserve.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Because they have no regard for the works of the LordNor the deeds
        of His hands,He will tear them down and not rebuild them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Blessed be the Lord,Because He has heard the voice of my supplication.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The Lord is my strength and my [impenetrable] shield;My heart trusts
        [with unwavering confidence] in Him, and I am helped;Therefore my heart greatly
        rejoices,And with my song I shall thank Him and praise Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord is their [unyielding] strength,And He is the fortress of
        salvation to His anointed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Save Your people and bless Your inheritance;Be their shepherd also,
        and carry them forever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 29The Voice of the Lord in the Storm.A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 29The Voice of the Lord in the Storm.A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '    Ascribe to the Lord, O sons of the mighty,Ascribe to the Lord
        glory and strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Ascribe to the Lord the glory due His name;Worship the Lord in the
        beauty and majesty of His holiness [as the creator and source of holiness].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The voice of the Lord is upon the waters;The God of glory thunders;The
        Lord is over many waters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The voice of the Lord is powerful;The voice of the Lord is full of
        majesty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The voice of the Lord breaks the cedars;Yes, the Lord breaks in pieces
        the cedars of Lebanon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He makes Lebanon skip like a calf,And Sirion (Mount Hermon) like
        a young, wild ox.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The voice of the Lord rakes flames of fire (lightning).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The voice of the Lord shakes the wilderness;The Lord shakes the wilderness
        of Kadesh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The voice of the Lord  makes the doe labor and give birthAnd strips
        the forests bare;And in His temple all are saying, \u201CGlory!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The Lord sat as King at the flood;Yes, the Lord sits as King forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The Lord will give [unyielding and impenetrable] strength to His people;The
        Lord will bless His people with peace.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 30Thanksgiving for Deliverance from Death.A Psalm; a Song at
        the Dedication of the House (Temple). A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 30Thanksgiving for Deliverance from Death.A Psalm; a Song at the
        Dedication of the House (Temple). A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  I will extol and praise You, O Lord, for You have lifted me up,And
        have not let my enemies rejoice over me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'O Lord my God,I cried to You for help, and You have healed me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'O Lord, You have brought my life up from Sheol (the nether world,
        the place of the dead);You have kept me alive, so that I would not go down
        to the pit (grave).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Sing to the Lord, O you His godly ones,And give thanks at the mention
        of His holy name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For His anger is but for a moment,  His favor is for a lifetime.Weeping
        may endure for a night,But a shout of joy comes in the morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "As for me, in my prosperity I said,\u201CI shall never be moved.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'By Your favor and grace, O Lord, you have made my mountain stand
        strong;You hid Your face, and I was horrified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I called to You, O Lord,And to the Lord I made supplication (specific
        request).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhat profit is there in my blood (death), if I go down to the
        pit (grave)?Will the dust praise You? Will it declare Your faithfulness [to
        man]?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CHear, O Lord, be gracious and show favor to me;O Lord, be my
        helper.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You have turned my mourning into dancing for me;You have taken off
        my sackcloth and clothed me with joy,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: That my soul may sing praise to You and not be silent.O Lord my God,
        I will give thanks to You forever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 31A Psalm of Complaint and of Praise.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 31A Psalm of Complaint and of Praise.To the Chief Musician. A
        Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  In You, O Lord, I have placed my trust and taken refuge;Let me
        never be ashamed;In Your righteousness rescue me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Incline Your ear to me, deliver me quickly;Be my rock of refuge,And
        a strong fortress to save me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Yes, You are my rock and my fortress;For Your name\u2019s sake You
        will lead me and guide me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You will draw me out of the net that they have secretly laid for
        me,For You are my strength and my stronghold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Into Your hand I commit my spirit;You have redeemed me, O Lord,
        the God of truth and faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I hate those who pay regard to vain (empty, worthless) idols;But
        I trust in the Lord [and rely on Him with unwavering confidence].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I will rejoice and be glad in Your steadfast love,Because You have
        seen my affliction;You have taken note of my life\u2019s distresses,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And You have not given me into the hand of the enemy;You have set
        my feet in a broad place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Be gracious and compassionate to me, O Lord, for I am in trouble;My
        eye is clouded and weakened by grief, my soul and my body also.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For my life is spent with sorrowAnd my years with sighing;My strength
        has failed because of my iniquity,And even my body has wasted away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Because of all my enemies I have become a reproach and disgrace,Especially
        to my neighbors,And an object of dread to my acquaintances;Those who see
        me on the street run from me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I am forgotten like a dead man, out of mind;I am like a broken vessel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For I have heard the slander and whispering of many,Terror is on
        every side;While they schemed together against me,They plotted to take away
        my life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But as for me, I trust [confidently] in You and Your greatness, O
        Lord;I said, \u201CYou are my God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'My times are in Your hands;Rescue me from the hand of my enemies
        and from those who pursue and persecute me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Make Your face shine upon Your servant;Save me in Your lovingkindness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Let me not be put to shame, O Lord, for I call on You;Let the wicked
        (godless) be put to shame, let them be silent in Sheol (the nether world,
        the place of the dead).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Let the lying lips be mute,Which speak insolently and arrogantly
        against the [consistently] righteousWith pride and contempt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'How great is Your goodness,Which You have stored up for those who
        [reverently] fear You,Which You have prepared for those who take refuge in
        You,  Before the sons of man!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In the secret place of Your presence You hide them from the plots
        and conspiracies of man;You keep them secretly in a shelter (pavilion) from
        the strife of tongues.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Blessed be the Lord,For He has shown His marvelous favor and lovingkindness
        to me [when I was assailed] in a besieged city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "As for me, I said in my alarm,\u201CI am cut off from Your eyes.\u201DNevertheless
        You heard the voice of my supplications (specific requests)When I cried to
        You [for help].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'O love the Lord, all you His godly ones!The Lord preserves the faithful
        [those with moral and spiritual integrity]And fully repays the [self-righteousness
        of the] arrogant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Be strong and let your hearts take courage,All you who wait for and
        confidently expect the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 32Blessedness of Forgiveness and of Trust in God.  A Psalm
        of David. A skillful Meaning uncertain.song, or a didactic or reflective
        poem.'
      title: PSALM 32Blessedness of Forgiveness and of Trust in God.  A Psalm of
        David. A skillful Meaning uncertain.song, or a didactic or reflective poem.
      number: 1
      content: '  Blessed [fortunate, prosperous, favored by God] is he whose transgression
        is forgiven,And whose sin is covered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Blessed is the man to whom the Lord does not impute wickedness,And
        in whose spirit there is no deceit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When I kept silent about my sin, my body wasted awayThrough my groaning
        all the day long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For day and night Your hand [of displeasure] was heavy upon me;My
        energy (vitality, strength) was drained away as with the burning heat of
        summer. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I acknowledged my sin to You,And I did not hide my wickedness;I said,
        \u201CI will confess [all] my transgressions to the Lord\u201D;And You forgave
        the guilt of my sin. Selah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore, let everyone who is godly pray to You [for forgiveness]
        in a time when You [are near and] may be found;Surely when the great waters
        [of trial and distressing times] overflow they will not reach [the spirit
        in] him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You are my hiding place; You, Lord, protect me from trouble;You surround
        me with songs and shouts of deliverance. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will instruct you and teach you in the way you should go;I will
        counsel you [who are willing to learn] with My eye upon you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not be like the horse or like the mule which have no understanding,Whose
        trappings include bridle and rein to hold them in check,  Otherwise they
        will not come near to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Many are the sorrows of the wicked,But he who trusts in and relies
        on the Lord shall be surrounded with compassion and lovingkindness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Be glad in the Lord and rejoice, you righteous [who actively seek
        right standing with Him];Shout for joy, all you upright in heart.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 33Praise to the Creator and Preserver.'
      title: PSALM 33Praise to the Creator and Preserver.
      number: 1
      content: "  Rejoice in the Lord, you righteous ones;Praise is becoming and
        appropriate for those who are upright [in heart\u2014those with moral integrity
        and godly character].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Give thanks to the Lord with the lyre;Sing praises to Him with the
        harp of ten strings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Sing to Him a new song;Play skillfully [on the strings] with a loud
        and joyful sound.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the word of the Lord is right;And all His work is done in faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He loves righteousness and justice;The earth is full of the lovingkindness
        of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'By the word of the Lord were the heavens made,And all their host
        by the breath of His mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He gathers the waters of the sea together as in a wineskin;He puts
        the deeps in storehouses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Let all the earth fear and worship the Lord;Let all the inhabitants
        of the world stand in awe of Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For He spoke, and it was done;He commanded, and it stood fast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The Lord nullifies the counsel of the nations;He makes the thoughts
        and plans of the people ineffective.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The counsel of the Lord stands forever,The thoughts and plans of
        His heart through all generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Blessed [fortunate, prosperous, and favored by God] is the nation
        whose God is the Lord,The people whom He has chosen as His own inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The Lord looks [down] from heaven;He sees all the sons of man;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "From His dwelling place He looks closelyUpon all the inhabitants
        of the earth\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He who fashions the hearts of them all,Who considers and understands
        all that they do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The king is not saved by the great size of his army;A warrior is
        not rescued by his great strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'A horse is a false hope for victory;Nor does it deliver anyone by
        its great strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Behold, the eye of the Lord is upon those who fear Him [and worship
        Him with awe-inspired reverence and obedience],On those who hope [confidently]
        in His compassion and lovingkindness,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'To rescue their lives from deathAnd keep them alive in famine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'We wait [expectantly] for the Lord;He is our help and our shield.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For in Him our heart rejoices,Because we trust [lean on, rely on,
        and are confident] in His holy name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Let Your [steadfast] lovingkindness, O Lord, be upon us,In proportion
        as we have hoped in You.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 34The Lord, a Provider and the One Who Rescues Me.  A Psalm
        of David; when he pretended to be insane before Abimelech, who drove him
        out, and he went away.'
      title: PSALM 34The Lord, a Provider and the One Who Rescues Me.  A Psalm of
        David; when he pretended to be insane before Abimelech, who drove him out,
        and he went away.
      number: 1
      content: '  I will bless the Lord at all times;His praise shall continually
        be in my mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'My soul makes its boast in the Lord;The humble and downtrodden will
        hear it and rejoice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'O magnify the Lord with me,And let us lift up His name together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I sought the Lord [on the authority of His word], and He answered
        me,And delivered me from all my fears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They looked to Him and were radiant;Their faces will never blush
        in shame or confusion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'This poor man cried, and the Lord heard himAnd saved him from all
        his troubles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The angel of the Lord encamps around those who fear Him [with awe-inspired
        reverence and worship Him with obedience],And He rescues [each of] them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O taste and see that the Lord [our God] is good;How blessed [fortunate,
        prosperous, and favored by God] is the man who takes refuge in Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'O [reverently] fear the Lord, you His saints (believers, holy ones);For
        to those who fear Him there is no want.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The young lions lack [food] and grow hungry,But they who seek the
        Lord will not lack any good thing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Come, you children, listen to me;I will teach you to fear the Lord
        [with awe-inspired reverence and worship Him with obedience].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Who is the man who desires lifeAnd loves many days, that he may see
        good?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Keep your tongue from evilAnd your lips from speaking deceit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Turn away from evil and do good;Seek peace and pursue it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The eyes of the Lord are toward the righteous [those with moral courage
        and spiritual integrity]And His ears are open to their cry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The face of the Lord is against those who do evil,To cut off the
        memory of them from the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When the righteous cry [for help], the Lord hearsAnd rescues them
        from all their distress and troubles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The Lord is near to the heartbrokenAnd He saves those who are crushed
        in spirit (contrite in heart, truly sorry for their sin).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Many hardships and perplexing circumstances confront the righteous,But
        the Lord rescues him from them all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He keeps all his bones;Not one of them is broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Evil will cause the death of the wicked,And those who hate the righteous
        will be held guilty and will be condemned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: The Lord redeems the soul of His servants,And none of those who take
        refuge in Him will be condemned.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 35Prayer for Rescue from Enemies.  A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 35Prayer for Rescue from Enemies.  A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Contend, O Lord, with those who contend with me;Fight against those
        who fight against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Take hold of shield and buckler (small shield),And stand up for my
        help.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Draw also the spear and javelin to meet those who pursue me.Say to
        my soul, \u201CI am your salvation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Let those be ashamed and dishonored who seek my life;Let those be
        turned back [in defeat] and humiliated who plot evil against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Let them be [blown away] like chaff before the wind [worthless, without
        substance],With the angel of the Lord driving them on.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Let their way be dark and slippery,With the angel of the Lord pursuing
        and harassing them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For without cause they hid their net for me;Without cause they dug
        a pit [of destruction] for my life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Let destruction come upon my enemy by surprise;Let the net he hid
        for me catch him;Into that very destruction let him fall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then my soul shall rejoice in the Lord;It shall rejoice in His salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "All my bones will say, \u201CLord, who is like You,Who rescues the
        afflicted from him who is too strong for him [to resist alone],And the afflicted
        and the needy from him who robs him?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Malicious witnesses rise up;They ask me of things that I do not know.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They repay me evil for good,To the sorrow of my soul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But as for me, when they were sick, my clothing was sackcloth (mourning
        garment);I humbled my soul with fasting,And I prayed with my head bowed on
        my chest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I behaved as if grieving for my friend or my brother;I bowed down
        in mourning, as one who sorrows for his mother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But in my stumbling they rejoiced and gathered together [against
        me];The slanderers whom I did not know gathered against me;They slandered
        and reviled me without ceasing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Like godless jesters at a feast,They gnashed at me with their teeth
        [in malice].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Lord, how long will You look on [without action]?Rescue my life from
        their destructions,My only life from the young lions.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I will give You thanks in the great congregation;I will praise You
        among a mighty people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Do not let those who are wrongfully my enemies rejoice over me;Nor
        let those who hate me without cause wink their eye [maliciously].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For they do not speak peace,But they devise deceitful words [half-truths
        and lies] against those who are quiet in the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "They open their mouths wide against me;They say, \u201CAha, aha,
        our eyes have seen it!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You have seen this, O Lord; do not keep silent.O Lord, do not be
        far from me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Wake Yourself up, and arise to my rightAnd to my cause, my God and
        my Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Judge me, O Lord my God, according to Your righteousness and justice;And
        do not let them rejoice over me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Do not let them say in their heart, \u201CAha, that is what we wanted!\u201DDo
        not let them say, \u201CWe have swallowed him up and destroyed him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Let those be ashamed and humiliated together who rejoice at my distress;Let
        those be clothed with shame and dishonor who magnify themselves over me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Let them shout for joy and rejoice, who favor my vindication and
        want what is right for me;Let them say continually, \u201CLet the Lord be
        magnified, who delights and takes pleasure in the prosperity of His servant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: And my tongue shall declare Your righteousness (justice),And Your
        praise all the day long.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 36Wickedness of Men and Lovingkindness of God.To the Chief
        Musician. A Psalm of David the servant of the Lord.'
      title: PSALM 36Wickedness of Men and Lovingkindness of God.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David the servant of the Lord.
      number: 1
      content: '  Transgression speaks [like an oracle] to the wicked (godless) [deep]
        within his heart;There is no fear (dread) of God before his eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For he flatters and deceives himself in his own eyes  Thinking that
        his sinfulness will not be discovered and hated [by God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The words of his mouth are wicked and deceitful;He has ceased to
        be wise and to do good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He plans wrongdoing on his bed;He sets himself on a path that is
        not good;He does not reject or despise evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Your lovingkindness and graciousness, O Lord, extend to the skies,Your
        faithfulness [reaches] to the clouds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Your righteousness is like the mountains of God,Your judgments are
        like the great deep.O Lord, You preserve man and beast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'How precious is Your lovingkindness, O God!The children of men take
        refuge in the shadow of Your wings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They drink their fill of the abundance of Your house;And You allow
        them to drink from the river of Your delights.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For with You is the fountain of life [the fountain of life-giving
        water];In Your light we see light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'O continue Your lovingkindness to those who know You,And Your righteousness
        (salvation) to the upright in heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Do not let the foot of the proud [person] overtake me,And do not
        let the hand of the wicked drive me away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: There those who [are perverse and] do evil have fallen;They have been
        thrust down and cannot rise.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 37Security of Those Who Trust in the Lord, and Insecurity of
        the Wicked.  A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 37Security of Those Who Trust in the Lord, and Insecurity of the
        Wicked.  A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '    Do not worry because of evildoers,Nor be envious toward wrongdoers;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For they will wither quickly like the grass,And fade like the green
        herb.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Trust [rely on and have confidence] in the Lord and do good;Dwell
        in the land and feed [securely] on His faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Delight yourself in the Lord,And He will give you the desires and
        petitions of your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Commit your way to the Lord;Trust in Him also and He will do it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He will make your righteousness [your pursuit of right standing with
        God] like the light,And your judgment like [the shining of] the noonday [sun].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Be still before the Lord; wait patiently for Him and entrust yourself
        to Him;Do not fret (whine, agonize) because of him who prospers in his way,Because
        of the man who carries out wicked schemes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Cease from anger and abandon wrath;Do not fret; it leads only to
        evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For those who do evil will be cut off,But those who wait for the
        Lord, they will inherit the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For yet a little while and the wicked one will be gone [forever];Though
        you look carefully where he used to be, he will not be [found].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But the humble will [at last] inherit the landAnd will delight themselves
        in abundant prosperity and peace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The wicked plots against the righteousAnd gnashes at him with his
        teeth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The Lord laughs at him [the wicked one\u2014the one who oppresses
        the righteous],For He sees that his day [of defeat] is coming.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The wicked have drawn the sword and bent their bowTo cast down the
        afflicted and the needy,To slaughter those who are upright in conduct [those
        with personal integrity and godly character].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sword [of the ungodly] will enter their own heart,And their bow
        will be broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Better is the little of the righteous [who seek the will of God]Than
        the abundance (riches) of many wicked (godless).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For the arms of the wicked will be broken,But the Lord upholds and
        sustains the righteous [who seek Him].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The Lord knows the days of the blameless,And their inheritance will
        continue forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They will not be ashamed in the time of evil,And in the days of famine
        they will have plenty and be satisfied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But the wicked (ungodly) will perish,And the enemies of the Lord
        will be like the glory of the pastures and like the fat of lambs [that is
        consumed in smoke],They vanish\u2014like smoke they vanish away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The wicked borrows and does not pay back,But the righteous is gracious
        and kind and gives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For those blessed by God will [at last] inherit the land,But those
        cursed by Him will be cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The steps of a [good and righteous] man are directed and established
        by the Lord,And He delights in his way [and blesses his path].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When he falls, he will not be hurled down,Because the Lord is the
        One who holds his hand and sustains him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'I have been young and now I am old,Yet I have not seen the righteous
        (those in right standing with God) abandonedOr his descendants pleading for
        bread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'All day long he is gracious and lends,And his descendants are a blessing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Depart from evil and do good;And you will dwell [securely in the
        land] forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For the Lord delights in justiceAnd does not abandon His saints (faithful
        ones);They are preserved forever,But the descendants of the wicked will [in
        time] be cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The righteous will inherit the landAnd live in it forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The mouth of the righteous proclaims wisdom,And his tongue speaks
        justice and truth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The law of his God is in his heart;Not one of his steps will slip.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The wicked lies in wait for the righteousAnd seeks to kill him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The Lord will not leave him in his handOr let him be condemned when
        he is judged.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Wait for and expect the Lord and keep His way,And He will exalt you
        to inherit the land;[In the end] when the wicked are cut off, you will see
        it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'I have seen a wicked, violent man [with great power]Spreading and
        flaunting himself like a cedar in its native soil,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Yet he passed away, and lo, he was no more;I sought him, but he could
        not be found.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Mark the blameless man [who is spiritually complete], and behold
        the upright [who walks in moral integrity];There is a [good] future for the
        man of peace [because a life of honor blesses one\u2019s descendants].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'As for transgressors, they will be completely destroyed;The future
        of the wicked will be cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'But the salvation of the righteous is from the Lord;He is their refuge
        and stronghold in the time of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: The Lord helps them and rescues them;He rescues them from the wicked
        and saves them,Because they take refuge in Him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 38Prayer in Time of Discipline.A Psalm of David; to bring to
        remembrance.'
      title: PSALM 38Prayer in Time of Discipline.A Psalm of David; to bring to remembrance.
      number: 1
      content: '  O Lord, do not rebuke me in Your wrath,Nor discipline me in Your
        burning anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For Your arrows have sunk into me and penetrate deeply,And Your hand
        has pressed down on me and greatly disciplined me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'There is no soundness in my flesh because of Your indignation;There
        is no health in my bones because of my sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For my iniquities have gone over my head [like the waves of a flood];As
        a heavy burden they weigh too much for me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'My wounds are loathsome and foulBecause of my foolishness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I am bent over and greatly bowed down;I go about mourning all day
        long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For my sides are filled with burning,And there is no health in my
        flesh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I am numb and greatly bruised [deadly cold and completely worn out];I
        groan because of the disquiet and moaning of my heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Lord, all my desire is before You;And my sighing is not hidden from
        You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'My heart throbs violently, my strength fails me;And as for the light
        of my eyes, even that has also gone from me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'My loved ones and my friends stand aloof from my plague;And my neighbors
        stand far away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Those who seek my life lay snares for me,And those who seek to injure
        me threaten mischievous things and destruction;They devise treachery all
        the day long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But I, like a deaf man, do not hear;I am like a mute man who does
        not open his mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Yes, I am like a man who does not hear,In whose mouth are no arguments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For in You, O Lord, I hope;You will answer, O Lord my God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For I pray, \u201CMay they not rejoice over me,Who, when my foot
        slips, would boast against me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For I am ready to fall;My sorrow is continually before me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For I do confess my guilt and iniquity;I am filled with anxiety because
        of my sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But my [numerous] enemies are vigorous and strong,And those who hate
        me without cause are many.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They repay evil for good, they attack and try to kill me,Because
        I follow what is good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Do not abandon me, O Lord;O my God, do not be far from me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Make haste to help me,O Lord, my Salvation.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 39The Vanity of Life.To the Chief Musician; for Jeduthun. A
        Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 39The Vanity of Life.To the Chief Musician; for Jeduthun. A Psalm
        of David.
      number: 1
      content: "  I said, \u201CI will guard my waysThat I may not sin with my tongue;I
        will muzzle my mouthWhile the wicked are in my presence.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I was mute and silent [before my enemies],I refrained even from good,And
        my distress grew worse.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'My heart was hot within me.While I was musing the fire burned;Then
        I spoke with my tongue:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CLord, let me know my [life\u2019s] endAnd [to appreciate] the
        extent of my days;Let me know how frail I am [how transient is my stay here].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Behold, You have made my days as [short as] hand widths,And my lifetime
        is as nothing in Your sight.Surely every man at his best is a mere breath
        [a wisp of smoke, a vapor that vanishes]! Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Surely every man walks around like a shadow [in a charade];Surely
        they make an uproar for nothing;Each one builds up riches, not knowing who
        will receive them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAnd now, Lord, for what do I expectantly wait?My hope [my confident
        expectation] is in You.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Save me from all my transgressions;Do not make me the scorn and reproach
        of the [self-righteous, arrogant] fool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I am mute, I do not open my mouth,Because it is You who has done
        it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Remove Your plague from me;I am wasting away because of the conflict
        and opposition of Your hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'With rebukes You discipline man for sin;You consume like a moth what
        is precious to him;Surely every man is a mere breath [a wisp of smoke, a
        vapor that vanishes]. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CHear my prayer, O Lord, and listen to my cry;Do not be silent
        at my tears;For I am Your temporary guest,A sojourner like all my fathers.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "O look away from me, that I may smile and again know joyBefore I
        depart and am no more.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 40God Sustains His Servant.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of
        David.'
      title: PSALM 40God Sustains His Servant.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  I waited patiently and expectantly for the Lord;And He inclined
        to me and heard my cry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He brought me up out of a horrible pit [of tumult and of destruction],
        out of the miry clay,And He set my feet upon a rock, steadying my footsteps
        and establishing my path.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He put a new song in my mouth, a song of praise to our God;Many will
        see and fear [with great reverence]And will trust confidently in the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Blessed [fortunate, prosperous, and favored by God] is the man who
        makes the Lord his trust,And does not regard the proud nor those who lapse
        into lies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Many, O Lord my God, are the wonderful works which You have done,And
        Your thoughts toward us;There is none to compare with You.If I would declare
        and speak of your wonders,They would be too many to count.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Sacrifice and meal offering You do not desire, nor do You delight
        in them;You have opened my ears and given me the capacity to hear [and obey
        Your word];Burnt offerings and sin offerings You do not require.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then I said, \u201CBehold, I come [to the throne];In the scroll of
        the book it is written of me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I delight to do Your will, O my God;Your law is within my heart.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I have proclaimed good news of righteousness [and the joy that comes
        from obedience to You] in the great assembly;Behold, I will not restrain
        my lips [from proclaiming Your righteousness],As You know, O Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I have not concealed Your righteousness within my heart;I have proclaimed
        Your faithfulness and Your salvation.I have not concealed Your lovingkindness
        and Your truth from the great assembly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Do not withhold Your compassion and tender mercy from me, O Lord;Your
        lovingkindness and Your truth will continually preserve me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For innumerable evils have encompassed me;My sins have overtaken
        me, so that I am not able to see.They are more numerous than the hairs of
        my head,And my heart has failed me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Be pleased, O Lord, to save me;O Lord, make haste to help me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Let those be ashamed and humiliated togetherWho seek my life to destroy
        it;Let those be turned back [in defeat] and dishonoredWho delight in my hurt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Let those be appalled and desolate because of their shameWho say
        to me, \u201CAha, aha [rejoicing in my misfortune]!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Let all who seek You rejoice and be glad in You;Let those who love
        Your salvation say continually,\u201CThe Lord be magnified!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Even though I am afflicted and needy,Still the Lord takes thought
        and is mindful of me.You are my help and my rescuer.O my God, do not delay.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 41The Psalmist in Sickness Complains of Enemies and False Friends.To
        the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 41The Psalmist in Sickness Complains of Enemies and False Friends.To
        the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: "  Blessed [by God\u2019s grace and compassion] is he who considers
        the helpless;The Lord will save him in the day of trouble.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord will protect him and keep him alive;And he will be called
        blessed in the land;You do not hand him over to the desire of his enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Lord will sustain and strengthen him on his sickbed;In his illness,
        You will restore him to health.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "As for me, I said, \u201CO Lord, be gracious to me;Heal my soul,
        for I have sinned against You.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "My enemies speak evil of me, saying,\u201CWhen will he die and his
        name perish?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when one comes to see me, he speaks empty words,While his heart
        gathers malicious gossip [against me];When he goes away, he tells it [everywhere].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All who hate me whisper together about me;Against me they devise
        my hurt [imagining the worst for me], saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CA wicked thing is poured out upon him and holds him;And when
        he lies down, he will not rise up again.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Even my own close friend in whom I trusted,Who ate my bread,Has lifted
        up his heel against me [betraying me].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But You, O Lord, be gracious to me and restore me [to health],So
        that I may repay them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'By this I know that You favor and delight in me,Because my enemy
        does not shout in triumph over me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'As for me, You uphold me in my integrity,And You set me in Your presence
        forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Blessed be the Lord, the God of Israel,From everlasting to everlasting
        [from this age to the next, and forever].Amen and Amen (so be it).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: BOOK TWOPSALM 42Thirsting for God in Trouble and Exile.To the Chief
        Musician. A skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem, of the sons
        of Korah.'
      title: BOOK TWOPSALM 42Thirsting for God in Trouble and Exile.To the Chief
        Musician. A skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem, of the sons
        of Korah.
      number: 1
      content: '  As the deer pants [longingly] for the water brooks,So my soul pants
        [longingly] for You, O God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'My soul (my life, my inner self) thirsts for God, for the living
        God.When will I come and see the face of God?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "My tears have been my food day and night,While they say to me all
        day long, \u201CWhere is your God?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'These things I [vividly] remember as I pour out my soul;How I used
        to go along before the great crowd of people and lead them in procession
        to the house of God [like a choirmaster before his singers, timing the steps
        to the music and the chant of the song],With the voice of joy and thanksgiving,
        a great crowd keeping a festival.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Why are you in despair, O my soul?And why have you become restless
        and disturbed within me?Hope in God and wait expectantly for Him, for I shall
        again praise HimFor the help of His presence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'O my God, my soul is in despair within me [the burden more than I
        can bear];Therefore I will [fervently] remember You from the land of the
        JordanAnd the peaks of [Mount] Hermon, from Mount Mizar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Deep calls to deep at the [thundering] sound of Your waterfalls;All
        Your breakers and Your waves have rolled over me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Yet the Lord will command His lovingkindness in the daytime,And in
        the night His song will be with me,A prayer to the God of my life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "I will say to God my rock, \u201CWhy have You forgotten me?Why do
        I go mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "As a crushing of my bones [with a sword], my adversaries taunt me,While
        they say continually to me, \u201CWhere is your God?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Why are you in despair, O my soul?Why have you become restless and
        disquieted within me?Hope in God and wait expectantly for Him, for I shall
        yet praise Him,The help of my countenance and my God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 43Prayer for Rescue.'
      title: PSALM 43Prayer for Rescue.
      number: 1
      content: '  Judge and vindicate me, O God; plead my case against an ungodly
        nation.O rescue me from the deceitful and unjust man!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For You are the God of my strength [my stronghold\u2014in whom I
        take refuge]; why have You rejected me?Why do I go mourning because of the
        oppression of the enemy?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'O send out Your light and Your truth, let them lead me;Let them bring
        me to Your holy hillAnd to Your dwelling places.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then I will go to the altar of God,To God, my exceeding joy;With
        the lyre I will praise You, O God, my God!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Why are you in despair, O my soul?And why are you restless and disturbed
        within me?Hope in God and wait expectantly for Him, for I shall again praise
        Him,The help of my [sad] countenance and my God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 44Former Times of Help and Present Troubles.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of the sons of Korah. A skillful song, or a didactic or reflective
        poem.'
      title: PSALM 44Former Times of Help and Present Troubles.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of the sons of Korah. A skillful song, or a didactic or reflective
        poem.
      number: 1
      content: '  We have heard with our ears, O God,Our fathers have told usThe
        work You did in their days,In the days of old.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You drove out the [pagan] nations with Your own hand;Then you planted
        and established them (Israel);[It was by Your power that] You uprooted the
        [pagan] peoples,Then You spread them abroad.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For our fathers did not possess the land [of Canaan] by their own
        sword,Nor did their own arm save them,But Your right hand and Your arm and
        the light of Your presence,Because You favored and delighted in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You are my King, O God;Command victories and deliverance for Jacob
        (Israel).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Through You we will gore our enemies [like a bull];Through Your name
        we will trample down those who rise up against us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For I will not trust in my bow,Nor will my sword save me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But You have saved us from our enemies,And You have put them to shame
        and humiliated those who hate us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In God we have boasted all the day long,And we will praise and give
        thanks to Your name forever. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But now You have rejected us and brought us to dishonor,And You do
        not go out with our armies [to lead us to victory].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You make us turn back from the enemy,And those who hate us have taken
        spoil for themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You have made us like sheep to be eaten [as mutton]And have scattered
        us [in exile] among the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You sell Your people cheaply,And have not increased Your wealth by
        their sale.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You have made us the reproach and taunt of our neighbors,A scoffing
        and a derision to those around us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You make us a byword among the nations,A laughingstock among the
        people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'My dishonor is before me all day long,And humiliation has covered
        my face,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Because of the voice of the taunter and reviler,Because of the presence
        of the enemy and the avenger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'All this has come upon us, yet we have not forgotten You,Nor have
        we been false to Your covenant [which You made with our fathers].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Our heart has not turned back,Nor have our steps wandered from Your
        path,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Yet You have [distressingly] crushed us in the place of jackalsAnd
        covered us with [the deep darkness of] the shadow of death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'If we had forgotten the name of our GodOr stretched out our hands
        to a strange god,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Would not God discover this?For He knows the secrets of the heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  But for Your sake we are killed all the day long;We are considered
        as sheep to be slaughtered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Awake! Why do You sleep, O Lord?Awaken, do not reject us forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Why do You hide Your faceAnd forget our affliction and our oppression?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For our life has melted away into the dust;Our body clings to the
        ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Rise up! Come be our help,And ransom us for the sake of Your steadfast
        love.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 45A Song Celebrating the King\u2019s Marriage.To the Chief
        Musician; set to the [tune of] \u201CLilies.\u201D A Psalm of the sons of
        Korah. A skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem. A Song of Love."
      title: "PSALM 45A Song Celebrating the King\u2019s Marriage.To the Chief Musician;
        set to the [tune of] \u201CLilies.\u201D A Psalm of the sons of Korah. A
        skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem. A Song of Love."
      number: 1
      content: '    My heart overflows with a good theme;I address my psalm to the
        King.My tongue is like the pen of a skillful writer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You are fairer than the sons of men;Graciousness is poured upon Your
        lips;Therefore God has blessed You forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Strap Your sword on Your thigh, O mighty One,In Your splendor and
        Your majesty!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And in Your majesty ride on triumphantlyFor the cause of truth and
        humility and righteousness;Let Your right hand guide You to awesome things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Your arrows are sharp;The peoples (nations) fall under You;  Your
        arrows pierce the hearts of the King\u2019s enemies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Your throne, O God, is forever and ever;The scepter of uprightness
        is the scepter of Your kingdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You have loved righteousness (virtue, morality, justice) and hated
        wickedness;Therefore God, your God, has anointed YouAbove Your companions
        with the oil of jubilation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'All Your garments are fragrant with myrrh, aloes and cassia;From
        ivory palaces stringed instruments have made You glad.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Kings\u2019 daughters are among Your noble ladies;At Your right hand
        stands the queen in gold from Ophir.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Hear, O daughter, consider and incline your ear [to my instruction]:Forget
        your people and your father\u2019s house;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the King will desire your beauty;Because He is your Lord, bow
        down and honor Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The daughter of Tyre will come with a gift;The rich among the people
        will seek your favor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Glorious is the King\u2019s daughter within [the palace];Her robe
        is interwoven with gold.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'She will be brought to the King in embroidered garments;The virgins,
        her companions who follow her,Will be brought to You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "With gladness and rejoicing will they be led;They will enter into
        the King\u2019s palace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'In place of your fathers will be your sons;You shall make princes
        in all the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I will make Your name to be remembered in all generations;Therefore
        the peoples will praise and give You thanks forever and ever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 46God the Refuge of His People.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm
        of the sons of Korah, set to soprano voices. A Song.'
      title: PSALM 46God the Refuge of His People.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm
        of the sons of Korah, set to soprano voices. A Song.
      number: 1
      content: '  God is our refuge and strength [mighty and impenetrable],A very
        present and well-proved help in trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Therefore we will not fear, though the earth should changeAnd though
        the mountains be shaken and slip into the heart of the seas,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Though its waters roar and foam,Though the mountains tremble at its
        roaring. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'There is a river whose streams make glad the city of God,The holy
        dwelling places of the Most High.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'God is in the midst of her [His city], she will not be moved;God
        will help her when the morning dawns.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The nations made an uproar, the kingdoms tottered and were moved;He
        raised His voice, the earth melted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The Lord of hosts is with us;The God of Jacob is our stronghold [our
        refuge, our high tower]. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Come, behold the works of the Lord,Who has brought desolations and
        wonders on the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He makes wars to cease to the end of the earth;He breaks the bow
        into pieces and snaps the spear in two;He burns the chariots with fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CBe still and know (recognize, understand) that I am God.I will
        be exalted among the nations! I will be exalted in the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The Lord of hosts is with us;The God of Jacob is our stronghold [our
        refuge, our high tower]. Selah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 47God the King of the Earth.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm
        of the sons of Korah.'
      title: PSALM 47God the King of the Earth.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of
        the sons of Korah.
      number: 1
      content: '  O clap your hands, all you people;Shout to God with the voice of
        triumph and songs of joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the Lord Most High is to be feared [and worshiped with awe-inspired
        reverence and obedience];He is a great King over all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He subdues peoples under usAnd nations under our feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He chooses our inheritance for us,The glory and excellence of Jacob
        whom He loves. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'God has ascended amid shouting,The Lord with the sound of a trumpet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Sing praises to God, sing praises;Sing praises to our King, sing
        praises.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For God is the King of all the earth;Sing praises in a skillful psalm
        and with understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'God reigns over the nations;God sits on His holy throne.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The princes of the people have gathered together as the people of
        the God of Abraham,For the shields of the earth belong to God;He is highly
        exalted.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 48The Beauty and Glory of Zion.A Song; a Psalm of the sons
        of Korah.'
      title: PSALM 48The Beauty and Glory of Zion.A Song; a Psalm of the sons of
        Korah.
      number: 1
      content: '  Great is the Lord, and greatly to be praised,In the city of our
        God, His holy mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Fair and beautiful in elevation, the joy of all the earth,Is Mount
        Zion [the City of David] in the far north,The city of the great King.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'God, in her palaces,Has made Himself known as a stronghold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For, lo, the kings assembled themselves,They [came and] passed by
        together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They saw it, then they were amazed;They were stricken with terror,
        they fled in alarm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Panic seized them there,And pain, as that of a woman in childbirth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'With the east windYou shattered the ships of Tarshish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'As we have heard, so have we seenIn the city of the Lord of hosts,
        in the city of our God:God will establish her forever. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'We have thought of Your lovingkindness, O God,In the midst of Your
        temple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'As is Your name, O God,So is Your praise to the ends of the earth;Your
        right hand is full of righteousness (rightness, justice).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Let Mount Zion be glad,Let the daughters of Judah rejoiceBecause
        of Your [righteous] judgments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Walk about Zion, go all around her;Count her towers,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Consider her ramparts,Go through her palaces,That you may tell the
        next generation [about her glory].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For this is God,Our God forever and ever;He will be our guide even
        until death.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 49The Folly of Trusting in Riches.To the Chief Musician. A
        Psalm of the sons of Korah.'
      title: PSALM 49The Folly of Trusting in Riches.To the Chief Musician. A Psalm
        of the sons of Korah.
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear this, all peoples;Listen carefully, all inhabitants of the
        world,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Both low and high,Rich and poor together:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'My mouth will speak wisdom,And the meditation of my heart will be
        understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will incline my ear and consent to a proverb;On the lyre I will
        unfold my riddle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Why should I fear in the days of evil,When the wickedness of those
        who would betray me surrounds me [on every side],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Even those who trust in and rely on their wealthAnd boast of the
        abundance of their riches?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "None of them can by any means redeem [either himself or] his brother,Nor
        give to God a ransom for him\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For the ransom of his soul is too costly,And he should cease trying
        forever\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So that he should live on eternally,That he should never see the
        pit (grave) and undergo decay.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For he sees that even wise men die;The fool and the stupid alike
        perishAnd leave their wealth to others.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Their inward thought is that their houses will continue forever,And
        their dwelling places to all generations;They have named their lands after
        their own names [ignoring God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But man, with all his [self] honor and pomp, will not endure;He is
        like the beasts that perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'This is the fate of those who are foolishly confident,And of those
        after them who approve [and are influenced by] their words. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Like sheep they are appointed for Sheol (the nether world, the place
        of the dead);Death will be their shepherd;And the upright shall rule over
        them in the morning,And their form and beauty shall be for Sheol to consume,So
        that they have no dwelling [on earth].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But God will redeem my life from the power of Sheol,For He will receive
        me. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Be not afraid when [an ungodly] man becomes rich,When the wealth
        and glory of his house are increased;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For when he dies he will carry nothing away;His glory will not descend
        after him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Though while he lives he counts himself happy and prosperous\u2014And
        though people praise you when you do well for yourself\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He shall go to the generation of his fathers;They shall never again
        see the light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: A man [who is held] in honor,Yet who lacks [spiritual] understanding
        and a teachable heart, is like the beasts that perish.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 50God the Judge of the Righteous and the Wicked.A Psalm of
        Asaph was a Levite and one of the leaders of David\u2019s choir. He was the
        head of one of the three families permanently in charge of the temple music.
        His family formed a guild that bore his name and is frequently mentioned
        (2\u2009Chr 20:14; 29:13, 30). Twelve psalms (50; 73-83) are attributed in
        the titles to the family of Asaph. A hundred and twenty-eight of Asaph\u2019s
        family members, all singers, came back from Babylon and took part when the
        foundations of Zerubbabel\u2019s temple were laid (Ezra 2:41; 3:10).Asaph"
      title: "PSALM 50God the Judge of the Righteous and the Wicked.A Psalm of Asaph
        was a Levite and one of the leaders of David\u2019s choir. He was the head
        of one of the three families permanently in charge of the temple music. His
        family formed a guild that bore his name and is frequently mentioned (2\u2009Chr
        20:14; 29:13, 30). Twelve psalms (50; 73-83) are attributed in the titles
        to the family of Asaph. A hundred and twenty-eight of Asaph\u2019s family
        members, all singers, came back from Babylon and took part when the foundations
        of Zerubbabel\u2019s temple were laid (Ezra 2:41; 3:10).Asaph"
      number: 1
      content: '  The mighty One, God, the Lord, has spoken,And summoned the earth
        from the rising of the sun to its setting [from east to west].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty,God has shone forth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'May our God come and not keep silent;Fire devours before Him,And
        around Him a mighty tempest rages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He summons the heavens above,And the earth, to judge His people:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CGather My godly ones to Me,Those who have made a covenant with
        Me by sacrifice.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the heavens declare His righteousness,For God Himself is judge.
        Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CHear, O My people, and I will speak;O Israel, I will testify
        against you:I am God, your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I do not reprove you for your sacrifices;Your burnt offerings are
        continually before Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will accept no young bull from your houseNor male goat from your
        folds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For every beast of the forest is Mine,And the cattle on a thousand
        hills.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I know every bird of the mountains,And everything that moves in the
        field is Mine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'If I were hungry, I would not tell you,For the world and all it contains
        are Mine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Shall I eat the flesh of bullsOr drink the blood of male goats?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Offer to God the sacrifice of thanksgivingAnd pay your vows to the
        Most High;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Call on Me in the day of trouble;I will rescue you, and you shall
        honor and glorify Me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But to the wicked God says:\u201CWhat right have you to recite My
        statutesOr to take My covenant on your lips?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For you hate instruction and disciplineAnd cast My words behind you
        [discarding them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When you see a thief, you are pleased with him and condone his behavior,And
        you associate with adulterers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You give your mouth to evilAnd your tongue frames deceit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "You sit and speak against your brother;You slander your own mother\u2019s
        son.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'These things you have done and I kept silent;You thought that I was
        just like you.Now I will reprimand and denounce you and state the case in
        order before your eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CNow consider this, you who forget God,Or I will tear you in
        pieces, and there will be no one to rescue [you].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He who offers a sacrifice of praise and thanksgiving honors Me;And
        to him who orders his way rightly [who follows the way that I show him],I
        shall show the salvation of God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 51A Contrite Sinner\u2019s Prayer for Pardon.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David; when Nathan the prophet came to him after he had sinned
        with Bathsheba."
      title: "PSALM 51A Contrite Sinner\u2019s Prayer for Pardon.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David; when Nathan the prophet came to him after he had sinned
        with Bathsheba."
      number: 1
      content: '  Have mercy on me, O God, according to Your lovingkindness;According
        to the greatness of Your compassion blot out my transgressions.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Wash me thoroughly from my wickedness and guiltAnd cleanse me from
        my sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For I am conscious of my transgressions and I acknowledge them;My
        sin is always before me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Against You, You only, have I sinnedAnd done that which is evil in
        Your sight,So that You are justified when You speak [Your sentence]And faultless
        in Your judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I was brought forth in [a state of] wickedness;In sin my mother conceived
        me [and from my beginning I, too, was sinful].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Behold, You desire truth in the innermost being,And in the hidden
        part [of my heart] You will make me know wisdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Purify me with hyssop, and I will be clean;Wash me, and I will be
        whiter than snow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Make me hear joy and gladness and be satisfied;Let the bones which
        You have broken rejoice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Hide Your face from my sinsAnd blot out all my iniquities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Create in me a clean heart, O God,And renew a right and steadfast
        spirit within me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Do not cast me away from Your presenceAnd do not take Your Holy Spirit
        from me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Restore to me the joy of Your salvationAnd sustain me with a willing
        spirit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then I will teach transgressors Your ways,And sinners shall be converted
        and return to You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Rescue me from bloodguiltiness, O God, the God of my salvation;Then
        my tongue will sing joyfully of Your righteousness and Your justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'O Lord, open my lips,That my mouth may declare Your praise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For You do not delight in sacrifice, or else I would give it;You
        are not pleased with burnt offering.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'My [only] sacrifice [acceptable] to God is a broken spirit;A broken
        and contrite heart [broken with sorrow for sin, thoroughly penitent], such,
        O God, You will not despise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'By Your favor do good to Zion;May You rebuild the walls of Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Then will You delight in the sacrifices of righteousness,In burnt
        offering and whole burnt offering;Then young bulls will be offered on Your
        altar.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 52Futility of Boastful Wickedness.To the Chief Musician. A
        skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem. A Psalm of David, when Doeg
        the Edomite came and told Saul, \u201CDavid has come to the house of Ahimelech.\u201D"
      title: "PSALM 52Futility of Boastful Wickedness.To the Chief Musician. A skillful
        song, or a didactic or reflective poem. A Psalm of David, when Doeg the Edomite
        came and told Saul, \u201CDavid has come to the house of Ahimelech.\u201D"
      number: 1
      content: '  Why do you boast of evil, O mighty man?The lovingkindness of God
        endures all day long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Your tongue devises destruction,Like a sharp razor, working deceitfully.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You love evil more than good,And falsehood more than speaking what
        is right. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You love all words that devour,O deceitful tongue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But God will break you down forever;He will take you away and tear
        you away from your tent,And uproot you from the land of the living. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The righteous will see it and fear,And will [scoffingly] laugh, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CLook, [this is] the man who would not make God his strength
        [his stronghold and fortress],But trusted in the abundance of his riches,Taking
        refuge in his wealth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But as for me, I am like a green olive tree in the house of God;I
        trust [confidently] in the lovingkindness of God forever and ever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: I will thank You forever, because You have done it, [You have rescued
        me and kept me safe].I will wait on Your name, for it is good, in the presence
        of Your godly ones.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 53Folly and Wickedness of Men.To the Chief Musician; in a mournful
        strain. A skillful song, or didactic or reflective poem of David.'
      title: PSALM 53Folly and Wickedness of Men.To the Chief Musician; in a mournful
        strain. A skillful song, or didactic or reflective poem of David.
      number: 1
      content: "  The [empty-headed] fool has said in his heart, \u201CThere is no
        God.\u201DThey are corrupt and evil, and have committed repulsive injustice;There
        is no one who does good.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'God has looked down from heaven upon the children of menTo see if
        there is anyone who understands,Who seeks after God [who requires Him, who
        longs for Him as essential to life].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Every one of them has turned aside and fallen away;Together they
        have become filthy and corrupt;There is no one who does good, no, not even
        one.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Have workers of wickedness no knowledge or no understanding?They
        eat up My people as though they ate breadAnd have not called upon God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'There they were, in great terror and dread, where there had been
        no terror or dread;For God scattered the bones of him who besieged you;You
        have put them to shame, because God has rejected them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Oh, that the salvation of Israel would come out of Zion!When God restores
        [the fortunes of] His people,Let Jacob rejoice, let Israel be glad.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 54Prayer for Defense against Enemies.To the Chief Musician;
        with stringed instruments. A skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem,
        of David, when the Ziphites went and told Saul, \u201CDavid is hiding among
        us.\u201D"
      title: "PSALM 54Prayer for Defense against Enemies.To the Chief Musician; with
        stringed instruments. A skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem,
        of David, when the Ziphites went and told Saul, \u201CDavid is hiding among
        us.\u201D"
      number: 1
      content: '  Save me, O God, by Your name;And vindicate me by Your [wondrous]
        power.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Hear my prayer, O God;Listen to the words of my mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For strangers have risen against meAnd violent men have sought my
        life;They have not set God before them. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Behold, God is my helper and ally;The Lord is the sustainer of my
        soul [my upholder].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He will pay back the evil to my enemies;In Your faithfulness destroy
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'With a freewill offering I will sacrifice to You;I will give thanks
        and praise Your name, O Lord, for it is good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: For He has rescued me from every trouble,And my eye has looked with
        satisfaction (triumph) on my enemies.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 55Prayer for the Destruction of the Treacherous.To the Chief
        Musician; with stringed instruments. A skillful song, or a didactic or reflective
        poem, of David.'
      title: PSALM 55Prayer for the Destruction of the Treacherous.To the Chief Musician;
        with stringed instruments. A skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem,
        of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Listen to my prayer, O God,And do not hide Yourself from my plea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Listen to me and answer me;I am restless and distraught in my complaint
        and distracted  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Because of the voice of the enemy,Because of the pressure of the
        wicked;For they bring down trouble on me,And in anger they persecute me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'My heart is in anguish within me,And the terrors of death have fallen
        upon me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Fear and trembling have come upon me;Horror has overwhelmed me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And I say, \u201COh, that I had wings like a dove!I would fly away
        and be at rest.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I would wander far away,I would lodge in the [peace of the] wilderness.
        Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I would hurry to my refuge [my tranquil shelter far away]From the
        stormy wind and from the tempest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Confuse [my enemies], O Lord, divide their tongues [destroying
        their schemes],For I have seen violence and strife in the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Day and night they go around her walls;Wickedness and mischief are
        in her midst.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Destruction is within her;Oppression and deceit do not depart from
        her streets and market places.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For it is not an enemy who taunts me\u2014Then I could bear it;Nor
        is it one who has hated me who insolently exalts himself against me\u2014Then
        I could hide from him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But it is you, a man my equal and my counsel,My companion and my
        familiar friend;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'We who had sweet fellowship together,Who walked to the house of God
        in company.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Let death come deceitfully upon them;Let them go down alive to Sheol
        (the nether world, the place of the dead),For evil [of every kind] is in
        their dwelling and in their hearts, in their midst.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'As for me, I shall call upon God,And the Lord will save me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Evening and morning and at noon I will complain and murmur,And He
        will hear my voice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He has redeemed my life in peace from the battle that was against
        me,For there were many against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "God will hear and humble them,Even He who sits enthroned from old\u2014
        Selah.Because in them there has been no change [of heart],And they do not
        fear God [at all].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He [my companion] has put out his hands against those who were at
        peace with him;He has broken his covenant [of friendship and loyalty].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The words of his mouth were smoother than butter,But his heart was
        hostile;His words were softer than oil,Yet they were drawn swords.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Cast your burden on the Lord [release it] and He will sustain and
        uphold you;He will never allow the righteous to be shaken (slip, fall, fail).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: But You, O God, will bring down the wicked to the pit of destruction;Men
        of blood and treachery will not live out half their days.But I will [boldly
        and unwaveringly] trust in You.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 56Supplication for Rescue and Grateful Trust in God.To the
        Chief Musician; set to [the tune of] \u201CSilent Dove Among Those Far Away.\u201D
        A Mikhtam of David. [A record of memorable thoughts] when the Philistines
        seized him in Gath."
      title: "PSALM 56Supplication for Rescue and Grateful Trust in God.To the Chief
        Musician; set to [the tune of] \u201CSilent Dove Among Those Far Away.\u201D
        A Mikhtam of David. [A record of memorable thoughts] when the Philistines
        seized him in Gath."
      number: 1
      content: '  Be gracious to me, O God, for man has trampled on me;All day long
        the adversary oppresses and torments me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'My enemies have trampled upon me all day long,For they are many who
        fight proudly against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When I am afraid,I will put my trust and faith in You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'In God, whose word I praise;In God I have put my trust;I shall not
        fear.What can mere man do to me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All day long they twist my words and say hurtful things;All their
        thoughts are against me for evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They attack, they hide and lurk,They watch my steps,As they have
        [expectantly] waited to take my life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Cast them out because of their wickedness.In anger bring down the
        peoples, O God!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You have taken account of my wanderings;Put my tears in Your bottle.Are
        they not recorded in Your book?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then my enemies will turn back in the day when I call;This I know,
        that God is for me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In God, whose word I praise,In the Lord, whose word I praise,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'In God have I put my trust and confident reliance; I will not be
        afraid.What can man do to me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Your vows are binding upon me, O God;I will give thank offerings
        to You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: For You have rescued my soul from death,Yes, and my feet from stumbling,So
        that I may walk before GodIn the light of life.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 57Prayer for Rescue from Persecutors.To the Chief Musician;
        set to [the tune of] \u201CDo Not Destroy.\u201D A Mikhtam of David. [A record
        of memorable thoughts of David] when he fled from Saul in the cave."
      title: "PSALM 57Prayer for Rescue from Persecutors.To the Chief Musician; set
        to [the tune of] \u201CDo Not Destroy.\u201D A Mikhtam of David. [A record
        of memorable thoughts of David] when he fled from Saul in the cave."
      number: 1
      content: '  Be gracious to me, O God, be gracious and merciful to me,For my
        soul finds shelter and safety in You,And in the shadow of Your wings I will
        take refuge and be confidently secureUntil destruction passes by.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will cry to God Most High,Who accomplishes all things on my behalf
        [for He completes my purpose in His plan].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He will send from heaven and save me;He calls to account him who
        tramples me down. Selah.God will send out His lovingkindness and His truth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "My life is among lions;I must lie among those who breathe out fire\u2014The
        sons of men whose teeth are spears and arrows,And their tongue a sharp sword.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Be exalted above the heavens, O God;Let Your glory and majesty be
        over all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They set a net for my steps;My very life was bowed down.They dug
        a pit before me;Into the midst of it they themselves have fallen. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'My heart is steadfast, O God, my heart is steadfast and confident!I
        will sing, yes, I will sing praises [to You]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Awake, my glory!Awake, harp and lyre!I will awaken the dawn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will praise and give thanks to You, O Lord, among the people;I
        will sing praises to You among the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For Your faithfulness and lovingkindness are great, reaching to the
        heavens,And Your truth to the clouds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Be exalted above the heavens, O God;Let Your glory and majesty be
        over all the earth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 58Prayer for the Punishment of the Wicked.To the Chief Musician;
        set to [the tune of] \u201CDo Not Destroy.\u201D A Mikhtam of David. [A record
        of memorable thoughts of David]."
      title: "PSALM 58Prayer for the Punishment of the Wicked.To the Chief Musician;
        set to [the tune of] \u201CDo Not Destroy.\u201D A Mikhtam of David. [A record
        of memorable thoughts of David]."
      number: 1
      content: '  Do you indeed speak righteousness, O gods (heavenly beings)?Do
        you judge fairly, O sons of men?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'No, in your heart you devise wrongdoing;On earth you deal out the
        violence of your hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The wicked are estranged from the womb;These go astray from birth,
        speaking lies [even twisted partial truths].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Their poison is like the venom of a serpent;They are like the deaf
        horned viper that stops up its ear,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So that it does not listen to the voice of charmers,Or of the skillful
        enchanter casting [cunning] spells.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'O God, break their teeth in their mouth;Break out the fangs of the
        young lions, O Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Let them flow away like water that runs off;When he aims his arrows,
        let them be as headless shafts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Let them be as a snail which melts away (secretes slime) as it
        goes along,Like the miscarriage of a woman which never sees the sun.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Before your cooking pots can feel the fire of thorns [burning under
        them as fuel],He will sweep them away with a whirlwind, the green and the
        burning ones alike.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The [unyieldingly] righteous will rejoice when he sees the vengeance
        [of God];He will wash his feet in the blood of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Men will say, \u201CSurely there is a reward for the righteous;Surely
        there is a God who judges on the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 59Prayer for Rescue from Enemies.To the Chief Musician; set
        to [the tune of] \u201CDo Not Destroy.\u201D A Mikhtam of David, [a record
        of memorable thoughts] when Saul sent men to watch his house in order to
        kill him."
      title: "PSALM 59Prayer for Rescue from Enemies.To the Chief Musician; set to
        [the tune of] \u201CDo Not Destroy.\u201D A Mikhtam of David, [a record of
        memorable thoughts] when Saul sent men to watch his house in order to kill
        him."
      number: 1
      content: '  Deliver me from my enemies, O my God;Set me securely on an inaccessibly
        high place away from those who rise up against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Deliver me from those who practice wrongdoing,And save me from bloodthirsty
        men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Look! They lie in wait for my life;Fierce and powerful men [are uniting
        together to] launch an attack against me,Not for my wrongdoing nor for any
        sin of mine, O Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They run and set themselves against me though there is no guilt in
        me;Stir Yourself to meet and help me, and see [what they are doing]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You, O Lord God of hosts, the God of Israel,Arise to punish all the
        nations;Spare no one and do not be merciful to any who treacherously plot
        evil. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They return at evening, they howl and snarl like dogs,And go [prowling]
        around the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Look how they belch out [insults] with their mouths;Swords [of sarcasm,
        ridicule, slander, and lies] are in their lips,For they say, \u201CWho hears
        us?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But You, O Lord, will laugh at them [in scorn];You scoff at and deride
        all the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'O [God] my strength, I will watch for You;For God is my stronghold
        [my refuge, my protector, my high tower].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'My God in His [steadfast] lovingkindness will meet me;God will let
        me look triumphantly on my enemies [who lie in wait for me].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Do not kill them, or my people will forget;Scatter them and make
        them wander [endlessly] back and forth by Your power, and bring them down,O
        Lord our shield!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the sin of their mouths and the words of their lips,Let them
        even be trapped in their pride,And on account of the curses and lies which
        they tell.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Destroy them in wrath, destroy them so that they may be no more;Let
        them know that God rules over Jacob (Israel)To the ends of the earth. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They return at evening, they howl and snarl like dogs,And go [prowling]
        around the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They wander around for food [to devour]And growl all night if they
        are not satisfied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But as for me, I will sing of Your mighty strength and power;Yes,
        I will sing joyfully of Your lovingkindness in the morning;For You have been
        my strongholdAnd a refuge in the day of my distress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: To You, O [God] my strength, I will sing praises;For God is my stronghold
        [my refuge, my protector, my high tower], the God who shows me [steadfast]
        lovingkindness.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 60Lament over Defeat in Battle, and Prayer for Help.To the
        Chief Musician; set to [the tune of] \u201CThe Lily of the Testimony.\u201D
        A Mikhtam of David [intended to record memorable thoughts and] to teach;
        when he struggled with the Arameans of Mesopotamia and the Arameans of Zobah,
        and when Joab returned and struck twelve thousand Edomites in the Valley
        of Salt."
      title: "PSALM 60Lament over Defeat in Battle, and Prayer for Help.To the Chief
        Musician; set to [the tune of] \u201CThe Lily of the Testimony.\u201D A Mikhtam
        of David [intended to record memorable thoughts and] to teach; when he struggled
        with the Arameans of Mesopotamia and the Arameans of Zobah, and when Joab
        returned and struck twelve thousand Edomites in the Valley of Salt."
      number: 1
      content: '  O God, You have rejected us and cast us off. You have broken [down
        our defenses and scattered] us;You have been angry; O restore us and turn
        again to us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You have made the land quake, You have split it open;Heal its rifts,
        for it shakes and totters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You have made Your people experience hardship;You have given us wine
        to drink that makes us stagger and fall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You have set up a banner for those who fear You [with awe-inspired
        reverence and submissive wonder\u2014a banner to shield them from attack],A
        banner that may be displayed because of the truth. Selah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'That Your beloved ones may be rescued,Save with Your right hand and
        answer us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "God has spoken in His holiness [in His promises]:\u201CI will rejoice,
        I will divide [the land of] Shechem and measure out the Valley of Succoth
        [west to east].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Gilead is Mine, and Manasseh is Mine;Ephraim is My helmet;Judah is
        My scepter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Moab is My washbowl;Over Edom I shall throw My shoe [in triumph];Over
        Philistia I raise the shout [of victory].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Who will bring me into the besieged city [of Petra]?Who will lead
        me to Edom?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Have You not rejected us, O God?And will You not go out with our
        armies?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Give us help against the enemy,For the help of man is worthless (ineffectual,
        without purpose).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Through God we will have victory,For He will trample down our enemies.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 61Confidence in God\u2019s Protection.To the Chief Musician;
        on stringed instruments. A Psalm of David."
      title: "PSALM 61Confidence in God\u2019s Protection.To the Chief Musician;
        on stringed instruments. A Psalm of David."
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear my cry, O God;Listen to my prayer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'From the end of the earth I call to You, when my heart is overwhelmed
        and weak;Lead me to the rock that is higher than I [a rock that is too high
        to reach without Your help].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For You have been a shelter and a refuge for me,A strong tower against
        the enemy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Let me dwell in Your tent forever;Let me take refuge in the shelter
        of Your wings. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For You have heard my vows, O God;You have given me the inheritance
        of those who fear Your name [with reverence].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "You will prolong the king\u2019s life [adding days upon days];His
        years will be like many generations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He will sit enthroned forever before [the face of] God;Appoint lovingkindness
        and truth to watch over and preserve him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: So I will sing praise to Your name forever,Paying my vows day by day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 62God Alone a Refuge from Treachery and Oppression.To the Chief
        Musician; to Jeduthun [Ethan, the noted musician, founder of an official
        musical family]. A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 62God Alone a Refuge from Treachery and Oppression.To the Chief
        Musician; to Jeduthun [Ethan, the noted musician, founder of an official
        musical family]. A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  For God alone my soul waits in silence;From Him comes my salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He alone is my rock and my salvation,My defense and my strong tower;
        I will not be shaken or disheartened.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'How long will you attack a manSo that you may murder him, all of
        you,Like a leaning wall, like a tottering fence?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They consult only to throw him down from his high position [to dishonor
        him];They delight in lies.They bless with [the words of] their mouths,But
        inwardly they curse. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For God alone my soul waits in silence and quietly submits to Him,For
        my hope is from Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He only is my rock and my salvation;My fortress and my defense, I
        will not be shaken or discouraged.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'On God my salvation and my glory rest;He is my rock of [unyielding]
        strength, my refuge is in God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Trust [confidently] in Him at all times, O people;Pour out your heart
        before Him.God is a refuge for us. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Men of low degree are only a breath (emptiness), and men of [high]
        rank are a lie (delusion).In the balances they go up [because they have no
        measurable weight or value];They are together lighter than a breath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Do not trust in oppression,And do not vainly hope in robbery;If riches
        increase, do not set your heart on them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'God has spoken once,Twice I have heard this:That power belongs to
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Also to You, O Lord, belong lovingkindness and compassion,For You
        compensate every man according to [the value of] his work.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 63The Thirsting Soul Satisfied in God.A Psalm of David; when
        he was in the wilderness of Judah.'
      title: PSALM 63The Thirsting Soul Satisfied in God.A Psalm of David; when he
        was in the wilderness of Judah.
      number: 1
      content: '  O God, You are my God; with deepest longing I will seek You;My
        soul [my life, my very self] thirsts for You, my flesh longs and sighs for
        You,In a dry and weary land where there is no water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I have gazed upon You in the sanctuary,To see Your power and Your
        glory.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Because Your lovingkindness is better than life,My lips shall praise
        You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So will I bless You as long as I live;I will lift up my hands in
        Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'My soul [my life, my very self] is satisfied as with marrow and fatness,And
        my mouth offers praises [to You] with joyful lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When I remember You on my bed,I meditate and thoughtfully focus on
        You in the night watches,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For You have been my help,And in the shadow of Your wings [where
        I am always protected] I sing for joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'My soul [my life, my very self] clings to You;Your right hand upholds
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But those who seek my life to destroy itWill [be destroyed and] go
        into the depths of the earth [into the underworld].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They will be given over to the power of the sword;They will be a
        prey for foxes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: But the king will rejoice in God;Everyone who swears by Him [honoring
        the true God, acknowledging His authority and majesty] will glory,For the
        mouths of those who speak lies will be stopped.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 64Prayer for Protection from Secret Enemies.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 64Prayer for Protection from Secret Enemies.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear my voice, O God, in my complaint;Guard my life from the terror
        of the enemy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Hide me from the secret counsel and conspiracy of the ungodly,From
        the scheming of those who do wrong,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Who have sharpened their tongues like a sword.They aim venomous words
        as arrows,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'To shoot from ambush at the blameless [one];Suddenly they shoot at
        him, without fear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They encourage themselves in [their pursuit of] an evil agenda;They
        talk of laying snares secretly;They say, \u201CWho will discover us?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They devise acts of injustice, saying,\u201CWe are ready with a well-conceived
        plan.\u201DFor the inward thought and the heart of a man are deep (mysterious,
        unsearchable).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But God will shoot them with an [unexpected] arrow;Suddenly they
        will be wounded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So they will be caused to stumble;Their own tongue is against them;All
        who gaze at them will shake the head [in scorn].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then all men will fear [God\u2019s judgment];They will declare the
        work of God,And they will consider and wisely acknowledge what He has done.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The righteous will rejoice in the Lord and take refuge in Him;All
        the upright in heart will glory and offer praise.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 65God\u2019s Abundant Favor to Earth and Man.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David. A Song."
      title: "PSALM 65God\u2019s Abundant Favor to Earth and Man.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David. A Song."
      number: 1
      content: '  To You belongs silence [the submissive wonder of reverence], and
        [it bursts into] praise in Zion, O God;And to You the vow shall be performed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'O You who hear prayer,To You all mankind comes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Wickedness and guilt prevail against me;Yet as for our transgressions,You
        forgive them [removing them from Your sight].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Blessed is the one whom You choose and bring nearTo dwell in Your
        courts.We will be filled with the goodness of Your house,Your holy temple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'By awesome and wondrous things You answer us in righteousness, O
        God of our salvation,You who are the trust and hope of all the ends of the
        earth and of the farthest sea;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Who creates the mountains by His strength,Being clothed with power,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Who stills the roaring of the seas,The roaring of their waves,And
        the tumult of the peoples,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So they who dwell at the ends of the earth stand in awe of Your signs
        [the evidence of Your presence].You make the dawn and the sunset shout for
        joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You visit the earth and make it overflow [with water];You greatly
        enrich it;The stream of God is full of water;You provide their grain, when
        You have prepared the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You water its furrows abundantly,You smooth its ridges;You soften
        it with showers,You bless its growth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You crown the year with Your bounty,And Your paths overflow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The pastures of the wilderness drip [with dew],And the hills are
        encircled with joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The meadows are clothed with flocksAnd the valleys are covered with
        grain;They shout for joy and they sing.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 66Praise for God\u2019s Mighty Deeds and for His Answer to
        Prayer.To the Chief Musician. A Song. A Psalm."
      title: "PSALM 66Praise for God\u2019s Mighty Deeds and for His Answer to Prayer.To
        the Chief Musician. A Song. A Psalm."
      number: 1
      content: '  Shout joyfully to God, all the earth;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Sing of the honor and glory and magnificence of His name;Make His
        praise glorious.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Say to God, \u201CHow awesome and fearfully glorious are Your works!Because
        of the greatness of Your power Your enemies will pretend to be obedient to
        You.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "All the earth will [bow down to] worship You [in submissive wonder],And
        will sing praises to You;They will praise Your name in song.\u201D Selah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Come and see the works of God,He is awesome in His deeds toward the
        children of men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He turned the sea into dry land;They crossed through the river on
        foot;There we rejoiced in Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Who rules by His might forever,His eyes keep watch on the nations;Do
        not let the rebellious exalt themselves. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Bless our God, O peoples,And make the sound of His praise be heard
        abroad,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Who keeps us among the living,And does not allow our feet to slip
        or stumble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For You have tested us, O God;You have refined us as silver is refined.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You brought us into the net;You laid a heavy burden [of servitude]
        on us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You made men (charioteers) ride over our heads [in defeat];We went
        through fire and through water,Yet You brought us out into a [broad] place
        of abundance [to be refreshed].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I shall come into Your house with burnt offerings;I shall pay You
        my vows,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Which my lips utteredAnd my mouth spoke as a promise when I was in
        distress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I shall offer to You burnt offerings of fat lambs,With the [sweet]
        smoke of rams;I will offer bulls with male goats. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Come and hear, all who fear God [and worship Him with awe-inspired
        reverence and obedience],And I will tell what He has done for me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I cried aloud to Him;He was highly praised with my tongue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'If I regard sin and baseness in my heart [that is, if I know it is
        there and do nothing about it],The Lord will not hear [me];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But certainly God has heard [me];He has given heed to the voice of
        my prayer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Blessed be God,Who has not turned away my prayerNor His lovingkindness
        from me.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 67The Nations Exhorted to Praise God.To the Chief Musician;
        on stringed instruments. A Psalm. A Song.'
      title: PSALM 67The Nations Exhorted to Praise God.To the Chief Musician; on
        stringed instruments. A Psalm. A Song.
      number: 1
      content: "  God be gracious and kind-hearted to us and bless us,And make His
        face shine [with favor] on us\u2014 Selah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'That Your way may be known on earth,Your salvation and deliverance
        among all nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Let the peoples praise You, O God;Let all the peoples praise You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Let the nations be glad and sing for joy,For You will judge the people
        fairlyAnd guide the nations on earth. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Let the peoples praise You, O God;Let all the peoples praise You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The earth has yielded its harvest [as evidence of His approval];God,
        our God, blesses us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: God blesses us,And all the ends of the earth shall fear Him [with
        awe-inspired reverence and submissive wonder].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 68The God of Sinai and of the Sanctuary.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David. A Song.'
      title: PSALM 68The God of Sinai and of the Sanctuary.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David. A Song.
      number: 1
      content: '  Let God arise, and His enemies be scattered;Let those who hate
        Him flee before Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'As smoke is driven away, so drive them away;As wax melts before the
        fire,So let the wicked and guilty perish before [the presence of] God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But let the righteous be glad; let them be in good spirits before
        God,Yes, let them rejoice with delight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Sing to God, sing praises to His name;Lift up a song for Him who
        rides through the desert\u2014His name is the Lord\u2014be in good spirits
        before Him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'A father of the fatherless and a judge and protector of the widows,Is
        God in His holy habitation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'God makes a home for the lonely;He leads the prisoners into prosperity,Only
        the stubborn and rebellious dwell in a parched land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'O God, when You went out before Your people,When You marched through
        the wilderness, Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The earth trembled;The heavens also poured down rain at the presence
        of God;Sinai itself trembled at the presence of God, the God of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You, O God, sent abroad plentiful rain;You confirmed Your inheritance
        when it was parched and weary.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Your flock found a dwelling place in it;O God, in Your goodness You
        provided for the poor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The Lord gives the command [to take Canaan];The women who proclaim
        the good news are a great host (army);  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThe kings of the [enemies\u2019] armies flee, they flee,And
        the beautiful woman who remains at home divides the spoil [left behind].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When you lie down [to rest] among the sheepfolds,You [Israel] are
        like the wings of a dove [of victory] overlaid with silver,Its feathers glistening
        with gold [trophies taken from the enemy].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When the Almighty scattered [the Canaanite] kings in the land of
        Canaan,It was snowing on Zalmon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'A mountain of God is the mountain of Bashan;A [high] mountain of
        many summits is Mount Bashan [rising east of the Jordan].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Why do you look with envy, mountains with many peaks,At the mountain
        [of the city of Zion] which God has desired for His dwelling place?Yes, the
        Lord will dwell there forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The chariots of God are myriads, thousands upon thousands;The Lord
        is among them as He was at Sinai, in holiness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You have ascended on high, You have led away captive Your captives;You
        have received gifts among men,Even from the rebellious also, that the Lord
        God may dwell there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Blessed be the Lord, who bears our burden day by day,The God who
        is our salvation! Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'God is to us a God of acts of salvation;And to God the Lord belong
        escapes from death [setting us free].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Surely God will shatter the head of His enemies,The hairy scalp of
        one who goes on in his guilty ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The Lord said, \u201CI will bring your enemies back from Bashan;I
        will bring them back from the depths of the [Red] Sea,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "That your foot may crush them in blood,That the tongue of your dogs
        may have its share from your enemies.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'They have seen Your [solemn] procession, O God,The procession of
        my God, my King, into the sanctuary [in holiness].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The singers go in front, the players of instruments last;Between
        them the maidens playing on tambourines.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Bless God in the congregations, [give thanks, gratefully praise Him],The
        Lord, you who are from [Jacob] the fountain of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The youngest is there, Benjamin, ruling them,The princes of Judah
        and their company [the southern tribes],The princes of Zebulun and the princes
        of Naphtali [the northern tribes].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Your God has commanded your strength [your power in His service and
        your resistance to temptation];Show Yourself strong, O God, who acted on
        our behalf.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Because of Your temple at Jerusalem[Pagan] kings will bring gifts
        to You [out of respect].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Rebuke the beasts [living] among the reeds [in Egypt],The herd of
        bulls (the leaders) with the calves of the peoples;Trampling underfoot the
        pieces of silver;He has scattered the peoples who delight in war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Princes and envoys shall come from Egypt;Ethiopia will quickly stretch
        out her hands [with the offerings of submission] to God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Sing to God, O kingdoms of the earth,Sing praises to the Lord! Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'To Him who rides in the highest heavens, the ancient heavens,Behold,
        He sends out His voice, a mighty and majestic voice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Ascribe strength to God;His majesty is over IsraelAnd His strength
        is in the skies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: O God, You are awesome and profoundly majestic from Your sanctuary;The
        God of Israel gives strength and power to His people.Blessed be God!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 69A Cry of Distress and Imprecation on Adversaries.To the Chief
        Musician; set to [the tune of] \u201CLilies.\u201D A Psalm of David."
      title: "PSALM 69A Cry of Distress and Imprecation on Adversaries.To the Chief
        Musician; set to [the tune of] \u201CLilies.\u201D A Psalm of David."
      number: 1
      content: '  Save me, O God,For the waters have threatened my life [they have
        come up to my neck].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I have sunk in deep mire, where there is no foothold;I have come
        into deep waters, where a flood overwhelms me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I am weary with my crying; my throat is parched;My eyes fail while
        I wait [with confident expectation] for my God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Those who hate me without cause are more than the hairs of my head;Those
        who would destroy me are powerful, being my enemies wrongfully;I am forced
        to restore what I did not steal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'O God, You know my folly;My wrongs are not hidden from You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Do not let those who wait [confidently] for You be ashamed through
        me, O Lord God of hosts;Do not let those who seek You [as necessary for life
        itself] be dishonored through me, O God of Israel,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Because for Your sake I have borne reproach;Confusion and dishonor
        have covered my face.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I have become estranged from my brothersAnd an alien to my mother\u2019s
        sons.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For zeal for Your house has consumed me,And the [mocking] insults
        of those who insult You have fallen on me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When I wept and humbled myself with fasting,It became my reproach.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When I made sackcloth my clothing [as one in mourning],I became a
        byword [a mere object of scorn] to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They who sit in the [city\u2019s] gate talk about me and mock me,And
        I am the song of the drunkards.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But as for me, my prayer is to You, O Lord, at an acceptable and
        opportune time;O God, in the greatness of Your favor and in the abundance
        of Your lovingkindness,Answer me with truth [that is, the faithfulness of
        Your salvation].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Rescue me from the mire and do not let me sink;Let me be rescued
        from those who hate me and from the deep waters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Do not let the floodwater overwhelm me,Nor the deep waters swallow
        me up,Nor the pit [of Sheol] shut its mouth over me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Answer me, O Lord, for Your lovingkindness is sweet and good and
        comforting;According to the greatness of Your compassion, turn to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Do not hide Your face from Your servant,For I am in distress; answer
        me quickly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Draw near to my soul and redeem it;Ransom me because of my enemies
        [so that they do not delight in my distress].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You know my reproach and my shame and my dishonor [how I am insulted];My
        adversaries are all before You [each one fully known].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Reproach and insults have broken my heart and I am so sick.I looked
        for sympathy, but there was none,And for comforters, but I found none.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They (self-righteous hypocrites) also gave me gall [poisonous and
        bitter] for my food,And for my thirst they gave me vinegar to drink.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'May their table [with all its abundance and luxury] become a snare
        [to them];And when they are in peace [secure at their sacrificial feasts],
        may it become a trap.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'May their eyes be dimmed so that they cannot see,And make their loins
        shake continually [in terror and weakness].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Pour out Your indignation on them,And let [the fierceness of] Your
        burning anger overtake them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'May their encampment be desolate;May no one dwell in their tents.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For they have persecuted him whom You have struck,And they tell of
        the pain of those whom You have pierced and wounded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Add [unforgiven] iniquity to their iniquity [in Your book],And may
        they not come into Your righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'May they be blotted out of the book of life [and their lives come
        to an end]And may they not be recorded with the righteous (those in right
        standing with God).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'But I am sorrowful and in pain;May Your salvation, O God, set me
        [securely] on high.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'I will praise the name of God with songAnd magnify Him with thanksgiving.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And it will please the Lord better than an oxOr a young bull with
        horns and hoofs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The humble have seen it and are glad;You who seek God [requiring
        Him as your greatest need], let your heart revive and live.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'For the Lord hears the needyAnd does not despise His who are prisoners.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Let heaven and earth praise Him,The seas and everything that moves
        in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'For God will save Zion and rebuild the cities of Judah,That His servants
        may remain there and possess it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: The descendants of His servants will inherit it,And those who love
        His name will dwell in it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 70Prayer for Help against Persecutors.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David, to bring to remembrance.'
      title: PSALM 70Prayer for Help against Persecutors.To the Chief Musician. A
        Psalm of David, to bring to remembrance.
      number: 1
      content: '  O God, come quickly to save me;O Lord, come quickly to help me!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Let those be ashamed and humiliatedWho seek my life;Let them be turned
        back and humiliatedWho delight in my hurt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Let them be turned back because of their shame and disgraceWho say,
        \u201CAha, aha!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "May all those who seek You [as life\u2019s first priority] rejoice
        and be glad in You;May those who love Your salvation say continually,\u201CLet
        God be magnified!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But I am afflicted and needy;Come quickly to me, O God!You are my
        help and my rescuer;O Lord, do not delay.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 71Prayer of an Old Man for Rescue.'
      title: PSALM 71Prayer of an Old Man for Rescue.
      number: 1
      content: '  In you, O Lord, I have put my trust and confidently taken refuge;Let
        me never be put to shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'In Your righteousness deliver me and rescue me;Incline Your ear to
        me and save me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Be to me a rock of refuge and a sheltering stronghold to which I
        may continually come;You have given the commandment to save me,For You are
        my rock and my fortress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Rescue me, O my God, from the hand of the wicked (godless),From the
        grasp of the unrighteous and ruthless man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For You are my hope;O Lord God, You are my trust and the source of
        my confidence from my youth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Upon You have I relied and been sustained from my birth;You are He
        who took me from my mother\u2019s womb and You have been my benefactor from
        that day.My praise is continually of You.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I am as a wonder to many,For You are my strong refuge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'My mouth is filled with Your praiseAnd with Your glory all day long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not cast me off nor send me away in the time of old age;Do not
        abandon me when my strength fails and I am weak.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For my enemies have spoken against me;Those who watch for my life
        have consulted together,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Saying, \u201CGod has abandoned him;Pursue and seize him, for there
        is no one to rescue him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'O God, do not be far from me;O my God, come quickly to help me!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Let those who attack my life be ashamed and consumed;Let them be
        covered with reproach and dishonor, who seek to injure me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But as for me, I will wait and hope continually,And will praise You
        yet more and more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'My mouth shall tell of Your righteousnessAnd of Your [deeds of] salvation
        all day long,For their number is more than I know.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I will come with the mighty acts of the Lord God [and in His strength];I
        will make mention of Your righteousness, Yours alone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'O God, You have taught me from my youth,And I still declare Your
        wondrous works and miraculous deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And even when I am old and gray-headed, O God, do not abandon me,Until
        I declare Your [mighty] strength to this generation,Your power to all who
        are to come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Your righteousness, O God, reaches to the [height of the] heavens,You
        who have done great things;O God, who is like You, [who is Your equal]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You who have shown me many troubles and distressesWill revive and
        renew me again,And will bring me up again from the depths of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'May You increase my greatness (honor)And turn to comfort me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'I will also praise You with the harp,Your truth and faithfulness,
        O my God;To You I will sing praises with the lyre,O Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'My lips will shout for joy when I sing praises to You,And my soul,
        which You have redeemed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: My tongue also will speak of Your righteousness all day long;For they
        are ashamed, for they are humiliated who seek my injury.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 72The Reign of the Righteous King.A Psalm of Solomon.'
      title: PSALM 72The Reign of the Righteous King.A Psalm of Solomon.
      number: 1
      content: "  Give the king [knowledge of] Your judgments, O God,And [the spirit
        of] Your righteousness to the king\u2019s son [to guide all his ways].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'May he judge Your people with righteousness,And Your afflicted with
        justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The mountains will bring peace and prosperity to the people,And the
        hills, in [the establishment of] righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'May he bring justice to the poor among the people,Save the children
        of the needyAnd crush the oppressor,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Let them fear You [with awe-inspired reverence and worship You with
        obedience] while the sun endures,And as long as the moon [reflects light],
        throughout all generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'May he come down like rain on the mown grass,Like showers that water
        the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In his days may the righteous flourish,And peace abound until the
        moon is no more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'May he also rule from sea to seaAnd from the River [Euphrates] to
        the ends of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The nomads of the desert will bow before him,And his enemies will
        lick the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The kings of Tarshish and of the islands will bring offerings;The
        kings of Sheba and Seba will offer gifts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Yes, all kings will bow down before him,All nations will serve him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For he will rescue the needy when he cries for help,The afflicted
        and abused also, and him who has no helper.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He will have compassion on the poor and needy,And he will save the
        lives of the needy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He will redeem their life from oppression and fraud and violence,And
        their blood will be precious in His sight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So may he live, and may the gold of Sheba be given to him;And let
        them pray for him continually;Let them bless and praise him all day long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'There will be an abundance of grain in the soil on the top of the
        mountains;Its fruit will wave like [the cedars of] Lebanon,And those of the
        city will flourish like grass of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'May his name endure forever;May his name continue as long as the
        sun;And let men bless themselves by him;Let all nations call him blessed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Blessed be the Lord God, the God of Israel,Who alone does wonderful
        things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Blessed be His glorious name forever;And may the whole earth be filled
        with His glory.Amen and Amen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The prayers of David son of Jesse are ended.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: BOOK THREEPSALM 73The End of the Wicked Contrasted with That of the
        Righteous.A Psalm of Asaph.'
      title: BOOK THREEPSALM 73The End of the Wicked Contrasted with That of the
        Righteous.A Psalm of Asaph.
      number: 1
      content: '  Truly God is good to Israel,To those who are pure in heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But as for me, my feet came close to stumbling,My steps had almost
        slipped.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For I was envious of the arrogantAs I saw the prosperity of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For there are no pains in their death,Their body is fat and pampered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They are not in trouble as other men,Nor are they plagued like mankind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore pride is their necklace;Violence covers them like a garment
        [like a long, luxurious robe].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Their eye bulges from fatness [they have more than the heart desires];The
        imaginations of their mind run riot [with foolishness].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They mock and wickedly speak of oppression;They speak loftily [with
        malice].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They set their mouth against the heavens,And their tongue swaggers
        through the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Therefore his people return to this place,And waters of abundance
        [offered by the irreverent] are [blindly] drunk by them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "They say, \u201CHow does God know?Is there knowledge [of us] with
        the Most High?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Behold, these are the ungodly,Who always prosper and are at ease
        [in the world]; they have increased in wealth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Surely then in vain I have cleansed my heartAnd washed my hands in
        innocence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For all the day long have I been stricken,And punished every morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "If I had said, \u201CI will say this,\u201D [and expressed my feelings],I
        would have betrayed the generation of Your children.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When I considered how to understand this,It was too great an effort
        for me and too painful  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Until I came into the sanctuary of God;Then I understood [for I considered]
        their end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Surely You set the wicked-minded and immoral on slippery places;You
        cast them down to destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'How they are destroyed in a moment!They are completely swept away
        by sudden terrors!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Like a dream [which seems real] until one awakens,O Lord, when stirred,
        [You observe the wicked], You will despise their image.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When my heart was embitteredAnd I was pierced within [as with the
        fang of an adder],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then I was senseless and ignorant;I was like a beast before You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Nevertheless I am continually with You;You have taken hold of my
        right hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You will guide me with Your counsel,And afterward receive me to honor
        and glory.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Whom have I in heaven [but You]?And besides You, I desire nothing
        on earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'My flesh and my heart may fail,But God is the rock and strength of
        my heart and my portion forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For behold, those who are far from You will perish;You have destroyed
        all those who are unfaithful and have abandoned You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: But as for me, it is good for me to draw near to God;I have made the
        Lord God my refuge and placed my trust in Him,That I may tell of all Your
        works.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 74An Appeal against the Devastation of the Land by the Enemy.A
        skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem, of Asaph.'
      title: PSALM 74An Appeal against the Devastation of the Land by the Enemy.A
        skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem, of Asaph.
      number: 1
      content: '  O God, why have You rejected us forever?Why does Your anger smoke
        against the sheep of Your pasture?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Remember Your congregation, which You have purchased of old,Which
        You have redeemed to be the tribe of Your inheritance;Remember Mount Zion,
        where You have dwelt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Turn your footsteps [quickly] toward the perpetual ruins;The enemy
        has damaged everything within the sanctuary.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'In the midst of Your meeting place Your enemies have roared [with
        their battle cry];They have set up their own emblems for signs [of victory].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'It seems as if one had lifted upAn axe in a forest of trees [to set
        a record of destruction].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And now all the carved work [of the meeting place]They smash with
        hatchets and hammers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They have burned Your sanctuary to the ground;They have profaned
        the dwelling place of Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They said in their heart, \u201CLet us completely subdue them.\u201DThey
        have burned all the meeting places of God in the land.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'We do not see our symbols;There is no longer any prophet [to guide
        us],Nor does any among us know for how long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'O God, how long will the adversary scoff?Is the enemy to revile Your
        name forever?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Why do You withdraw Your hand, even Your right hand [from judging
        the enemy]?  Remove Your hand from Your chest, destroy them!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Yet God is my King of old,Working salvation in the midst of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You divided the [Red] Sea by Your strength;You broke the heads of
        the sea monsters in the waters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You crushed the heads of Leviathan (Egypt);You gave him as food for
        the creatures of the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You broke open fountains and streams;You dried up ever-flowing rivers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The day is Yours, the night also is Yours;You have established and
        prepared the [heavenly] light and the sun.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You have defined and established all the borders of the earth [the
        divisions of land and sea and of the nations];You have made summer and winter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Remember this, O Lord, the enemy has scoffed,And a foolish and impious
        people has spurned Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Oh, do not hand over the soul of your turtledove to the wild beast;Do
        not forget the life of Your afflicted forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Consider the covenant [You made with Abraham],For the dark places
        of the land are full of the habitations of violence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Let not the oppressed return dishonored;Let the afflicted and needy
        praise Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Arise, O God, plead Your own cause;Remember how the foolish man scoffs
        at You all day long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Do not forget the [clamoring] voices of Your adversaries,The uproar
        of those who rise against You, which ascends continually [to Your ears].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 75God Abases the Proud, but Exalts the Righteous.To the Chief
        Musician; set to [the tune of] \u201CDo Not Destroy.\u201D A Psalm of Asaph.
        A Song."
      title: "PSALM 75God Abases the Proud, but Exalts the Righteous.To the Chief
        Musician; set to [the tune of] \u201CDo Not Destroy.\u201D A Psalm of Asaph.
        A Song."
      number: 1
      content: '  We give thanks and praise to You, O God, we give thanks,For Your
        [wonderful works declare that Your] name is near;People declare Your wonders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWhen I select an appointed time,I will judge with equity,\u201D
        [says the Lord].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CThe earth and all the inhabitants of it melt [in tumultuous
        times].It is I who will steady its pillars. Selah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I said to the arrogant, \u2018Do not boast;\u2019And to the wicked,
        \u2018Do not lift up the horn [of self-glorification].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Do not lift up your [defiant and aggressive] horn on high,Do not
        speak with a stiff neck.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For not from the east, nor from the west,Nor from the desert comes
        exaltation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But God is the Judge;He puts down one and lifts up another.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For a cup [of His wrath] is in the hand of the Lord, and the wine
        foams;It is well mixed and fully spiced, and He pours out from it;And all
        the wicked of the earth must drain it and drink down to its dregs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But as for me, I will declare it and rejoice forever;I will sing
        praises to the God of Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: All the horns of the wicked He will cut off,But the horns of the righteous
        will be lifted up.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 76The Victorious Power of the God of Jacob.To the Chief Musician;
        on stringed instruments. A Psalm of Asaph. A Song.'
      title: PSALM 76The Victorious Power of the God of Jacob.To the Chief Musician;
        on stringed instruments. A Psalm of Asaph. A Song.
      number: 1
      content: '  God is known in Judah;His name is great in Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'His tabernacle is in Salem (Jerusalem);His dwelling place is in Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'There He broke the flaming arrows,The shield, the sword, and the
        weapons of war. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You are glorious and resplendent,More majestic than the mountains
        of prey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The stouthearted have been stripped of their spoil,They have slept
        the sleep [of death];And none of the warriors could use his hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'At Your rebuke, O God of Jacob,Both rider and horse were cast into
        a dead sleep [of death].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You, even You, are to be feared [with the submissive wonder of reverence];Who
        may stand in Your presence when once You are angry?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You caused judgment to be heard from heaven;The earth feared and
        was quiet  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When God arose to [establish] judgment,To save all the humble of
        the earth. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the wrath of man shall praise You;With a remnant of wrath You
        will clothe and arm Yourself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Make vows to the Lord your God and fulfill them;Let all who are around
        Him bring gifts to Him who is to be feared [with awe-inspired reverence].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: He will cut off the spirit of princes;He is awesome and feared by
        the kings of the earth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 77Comfort in Trouble from Recalling God\u2019s Mighty Deeds.To
        the Chief Musician; according to Jeduthun [one of David\u2019s three chief
        musicians, founder of an official musical family]. A Psalm of Asaph."
      title: "PSALM 77Comfort in Trouble from Recalling God\u2019s Mighty Deeds.To
        the Chief Musician; according to Jeduthun [one of David\u2019s three chief
        musicians, founder of an official musical family]. A Psalm of Asaph."
      number: 1
      content: '  My voice rises to God, and I will cry aloud;My voice rises to God,
        and He will hear me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'In the day of my trouble I [desperately] sought the Lord;In the night
        my hand was stretched out [in prayer] without weariness;My soul refused to
        be comforted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I remember God; then I am disquieted and I groan;I sigh [in prayer],
        and my spirit grows faint. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You have held my eyelids open;I am so troubled that I cannot speak.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I have considered the ancient days,The years [of prosperity] of long,
        long ago.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will remember my song in the night;I will meditate with my heart,And
        my spirit searches:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Will the Lord reject forever?And will He never be favorable again?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Has His lovingkindness ceased forever?Have His promises ended for
        all time?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Has God forgotten to be gracious?Or has He in anger withdrawn His
        compassion? Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And I said, \u201CThis is my grief,That the right hand of the Most
        High has changed [and His lovingkindness is withheld].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I will [solemnly] remember the deeds of the Lord;Yes, I will [wholeheartedly]
        remember Your wonders of old.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will meditate on all Your worksAnd thoughtfully consider all Your
        [great and wondrous] deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Your way, O God, is holy [far from sin and guilt].What god is great
        like our God?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You are the [awesome] God who works [powerful] wonders;You have demonstrated
        Your power among the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You have with Your [great] arm redeemed Your people,The sons of Jacob
        and Joseph. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The waters [of the Red Sea] saw You, O God;The waters saw You, they
        were in anguish;The deeps also trembled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The clouds poured down water;The skies sent out a sound [of rumbling
        thunder];Your arrows (lightning) flashed here and there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The voice of Your thunder was in the whirlwind;The lightnings illumined
        the world;The earth trembled and shook.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Your way [of escape for Your people] was through the sea,And Your
        paths through the great waters,And Your footprints were not traceable.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: You led Your people like a flockBy the hand of Moses and Aaron [to
        the promised goal].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 78God\u2019s Guidance of His People in Spite of Their Unfaithfulness.A
        skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem, of Asaph."
      title: "PSALM 78God\u2019s Guidance of His People in Spite of Their Unfaithfulness.A
        skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem, of Asaph."
      number: 1
      content: '  Listen, O my people, to my teaching;Incline your ears to the words
        of my mouth [and be willing to learn].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I will open my mouth in a parable [to instruct using examples];I
        will utter dark and puzzling sayings of old [that contain important truth]\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Which we have heard and known,And our fathers have told us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'We will not hide them from their children,But [we will] tell to the
        generation to come the praiseworthy deeds of the Lord,And [tell of] His great
        might and power and the wonderful works that He has done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For He established a testimony (a specific precept) in JacobAnd appointed
        a law in Israel,Which He commanded our fathersThat they should teach to their
        children [the great facts of God\u2019s transactions with Israel],  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'That the generation to come might know them, that the children still
        to be bornMay arise and recount them to their children,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'That they should place their confidence in GodAnd not forget the
        works of God,But keep His commandments,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And not be like their fathers\u2014A stubborn and rebellious generation,A
        generation that did not prepare its heart to know and follow God,And whose
        spirit was not faithful to God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sons of Ephraim were armed as archers and carrying bows,  Yet
        they turned back in the day of battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They did not keep the covenant of GodAnd refused to walk according
        to His law;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they forgot His [incredible] worksAnd His miraculous wonders
        that He had shown them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He did marvelous things in the sight of their fathersIn the land
        of Egypt, in the field of Zoan [where Pharaoh resided].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He divided the [Red] Sea and allowed them to pass through it,And
        He made the waters stand up like [water behind] a dam.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In the daytime He led them with a cloudAnd all the night with a light
        of fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He split rocks in the wildernessAnd gave them abundant [water to]
        drink like the ocean depths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He brought streams also from the rock [at Rephidim and Kadesh]And
        caused waters to run down like rivers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Yet they still continued to sin against HimBy rebelling against the
        Most High in the desert.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And in their hearts they put God to the testBy asking for food according
        to their [selfish] appetite.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then they spoke against God;They said, \u201CCan God prepare [food
        for] a table in the wilderness?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Behold, He struck the rock so that waters gushed outAnd the streams
        overflowed;Can He give bread also?Or will He provide meat for His people?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Therefore, when the Lord heard, He was full of wrath;A fire was kindled
        against Jacob,And His anger mounted up against Israel,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Because they did not believe in God [they did not rely on Him, they
        did not adhere to Him],And they did not trust in His salvation (His power
        to save).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Yet He commanded the clouds from aboveAnd opened the doors of heaven;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And He rained down manna upon them to eatAnd gave them the grain
        of heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Man ate the bread of angels;God sent them provision in abundance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He caused the east wind to blow in the heavensAnd by His [unlimited]
        power He guided the south wind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He rained meat upon them like the dust,And winged birds (quail) like
        the sand of the seas.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And He let them fall in the midst of their camp,Around their tents.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So they ate and were well filled,He gave them what they craved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Before they had satisfied their desire,And while their food was in
        their mouths,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The wrath of God rose against themAnd killed some of the strongest
        of them,And subdued the choice young men of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'In spite of all this they still sinned,For they did not believe in
        His wonderful and extraordinary works.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Therefore He consumed their days like a breath [in emptiness and
        futility]And their years in sudden terror.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'When He killed [some of] them, then those remaining sought Him,And
        they returned [to Him] and searched diligently for God [for a time].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And they remembered that God was their rock,And the Most High God
        their Redeemer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Nevertheless they flattered Him with their mouthsAnd lied to Him
        with their tongues.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'For their heart was not steadfast toward Him,Nor were they faithful
        to His covenant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '  But He, the source of compassion and lovingkindness, forgave their
        wickedness and did not destroy them;Many times He restrained His angerAnd
        did not stir up all His wrath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'For He [graciously] remembered that they were mere [human] flesh,A
        wind that goes and does not return.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'How often they rebelled against Him in the wildernessAnd grieved
        Him in the desert!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Again and again they tempted God,And distressed the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'They did not remember [the miracles worked by] His [powerful] hand,Nor
        the day when He redeemed them from the enemy,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'How He worked His miracles in EgyptAnd His wonders in the field of
        Zoan [where Pharaoh resided],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And turned their rivers into blood,And their streams, so that they
        could not drink.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'He sent among them swarms of flies which devoured them,And frogs
        which destroyed them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'He also gave their crops to the grasshopper,And the fruit of their
        labor to the locust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'He destroyed their vines with [great] hailstonesAnd their sycamore
        trees with frost.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'He gave over their cattle also to the hailstones,And their flocks
        and herds to thunderbolts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'He sent upon them His burning anger,His fury and indignation and
        distress,A band of angels of destruction [among them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'He leveled a path for His anger [to give it free run];He did not
        spare their souls from death,But turned over their lives to the plague.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'He killed all the firstborn in Egypt,The first and best of their
        strength in the tents [of the land of the sons] of Ham.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'But God led His own people forward like sheepAnd guided them in the
        wilderness like [a good shepherd with] a flock.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'He led them safely, so that they did not fear;But the sea engulfed
        their enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'So He brought them to His holy land,To this mountain [Zion] which
        His right hand had acquired.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'He also drove out the nations before the sons of IsraelAnd allotted
        their land as an inheritance, measured out and partitioned;And He had the
        tribes of Israel dwell in their tents [the tents of those who had been dispossessed].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'Yet they tempted and rebelled against the Most High GodAnd did not
        keep His testimonies (laws).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "They turned back and acted unfaithfully like their fathers;They were
        twisted like a warped bow [that will not respond to the archer\u2019s aim].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'For they provoked Him to [righteous] anger with their high places
        [devoted to idol worship]And moved Him to jealousy with their carved images
        [by denying Him the love, worship, and obedience that is rightfully and uniquely
        His].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'When God heard this, He was filled with [righteous] wrath;And utterly
        rejected Israel, [greatly hating her ways],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'So that He abandoned the tabernacle at Shiloh,The tent in which He
        had dwelled among men,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'And gave up His strength and power (the ark of the covenant) into
        captivity,And His glory into the hand of the enemy (the Philistines).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'He also handed His people over to the sword,And was infuriated with
        His inheritance (Israel).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'The fire [of war] devoured His young men,And His [bereaved] virgins
        had no wedding songs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'His priests [Hophni and Phinehas] fell by the sword,And His widows
        could not weep.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'Then the Lord awakened as from sleep,Like a [mighty] warrior who
        awakens from the sleep of wine [fully conscious of his power].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'He drove His enemies backward;He subjected them to lasting shame
        and dishonor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: 'Moreover, He rejected the tent of Joseph,And did not choose the tribe
        of Ephraim [in which the tabernacle stood].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: "But He chose the tribe of Judah [as Israel\u2019s leader],Mount Zion,
        which He loved [to replace Shiloh as His capital].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: 'And He built His sanctuary [exalted] like the heights [of the heavens],Like
        the earth which He has established forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: 'He also chose David His servantAnd took him from the sheepfolds;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: '  From tending the ewes with nursing young He brought himTo shepherd
        Jacob His people,And Israel His inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '72: '
      title: 
      number: 72
      content: So David shepherded them according to the integrity of his heart;And
        guided them with his skillful hands.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 79A Lament over the Destruction of Jerusalem, and Prayer for
        Help.A Psalm of Asaph.'
      title: PSALM 79A Lament over the Destruction of Jerusalem, and Prayer for Help.A
        Psalm of Asaph.
      number: 1
      content: '  O God, the nations have invaded [the land of Your people] Your
        inheritance;They have defiled Your sacred temple;They have laid Jerusalem
        in ruins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They have given the dead bodies of Your servants as food to the birds
        of the heavens,The flesh of Your godly ones to the beasts of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They have poured out their blood like water all around Jerusalem,And
        there was no one to bury them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'We have become an object of taunting to our neighbors [because of
        our humiliation],A derision and mockery to those who encircle us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'How long, O Lord? Will You be angry forever?Will Your jealousy [which
        cannot endure a divided allegiance] burn like fire?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Pour out Your wrath on the [Gentile] nations that do not know You,And
        on the kingdoms that do not call on Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For they have devoured JacobAnd made his pasture desolate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O do not remember against us the sins and guilt of our forefathers.Let
        Your compassion and mercy come quickly to meet us,For we have been brought
        very low.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Help us, O God of our salvation, for the glory of Your name;Rescue
        us, forgive us our sins for Your name\u2019s sake.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Why should the [Gentile] nations say, \u201CWhere is their God?\u201DLet
        there be known [without delay] among the nations in our sight [and to this
        generation],Your vengeance for the blood of Your servants which has been
        poured out.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Let the groaning and sighing of the prisoner come before You;According
        to the greatness of Your power keep safe those who are doomed to die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And return into the lap of our neighbors sevenfoldThe taunts with
        which they have taunted You, O Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: So we Your people, the sheep of Your pasture,Will give You thanks
        forever;We will declare and publish Your praise from generation to generation.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 80God Implored to Rescue His People from Their Calamities.To
        the Chief Musician; set to [the tune of] \u201CLilies, a Testimony.\u201D
        A Psalm of Asaph."
      title: "PSALM 80God Implored to Rescue His People from Their Calamities.To
        the Chief Musician; set to [the tune of] \u201CLilies, a Testimony.\u201D
        A Psalm of Asaph."
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear us O Shepherd of Israel,You who lead Joseph like a flock;You
        who sit enthroned above the cherubim [of the ark of the covenant], shine
        forth!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Before Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh, stir up Your powerAnd come
        to save us!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Restore us, O God;Cause Your face to shine on us [with favor and
        approval], and we will be saved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'O Lord God of hosts,How long will You be angry with the prayers of
        Your people?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You have fed them the bread of tears,And You have made them drink
        [bitter] tears in abundance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You make us an object of contention to our neighbors,And our enemies
        laugh [at our suffering] among themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Restore us, O God of hosts;And cause Your face to shine on us [with
        favor and approval], and we will be saved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You uprooted a vine (Israel) from Egypt;You drove out the [Canaanite]
        nations and planted the vine [in Canaan].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You cleared away the ground before it,And it took deep root and filled
        the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The mountains were covered with its shadow,And its branches were
        like the cedars of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Israel sent out its branches to the [Mediterranean] Sea,And its branches
        to the [Euphrates] River.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Why have You broken down its walls and hedges,So that all who pass
        by pick its fruit?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'A boar from the woods eats it away,And the insects of the field feed
        on it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Turn again [in favor to us], O God of hosts;Look down from heaven
        and see, and take care of this vine,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Even the stock which Your right hand has planted,And [look down on]
        the son that You have reared and strengthened for Yourself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'It is burned with fire, it is cut down;They perish at the rebuke
        of Your [angry] appearance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Let Your hand be upon the man of Your right hand,Upon the son of
        man whom You have made strong for Yourself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then we shall not turn back from You;Revive us and we will call on
        Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Restore us, O Lord God of hosts;Cause Your face to shine on us [in
        favor and approval], and we shall be saved.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 81God\u2019s Goodness and Israel\u2019s Waywardness.To the
        Chief Musician; set to the A technical musical term, meaning uncertain.Philistine
        lute. A Psalm of Asaph."
      title: "PSALM 81God\u2019s Goodness and Israel\u2019s Waywardness.To the Chief
        Musician; set to the A technical musical term, meaning uncertain.Philistine
        lute. A Psalm of Asaph."
      number: 1
      content: '  Sing aloud to God our strength;Shout for joy to the God of Jacob
        (Israel).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Raise a song, sound the timbrel,The sweet sounding lyre with the
        harp.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Blow the trumpet at the New Moon,At the full moon, on our feast day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For this is a statute for Israel,An ordinance of the God of Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He established it for a testimony in JosephWhen He went throughout
        the land of Egypt.I heard the language [of One whom] I did not know, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI removed the burden from his shoulder;His hands were freed
        from the basket.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You called in [the time of] trouble and I rescued you;I answered
        you in the secret place of thunder;I tested you at the waters of Meribah.
        Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Hear, O My people, and I will admonish you\u2014O Israel, if you
        would listen to Me!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Let there be no strange god among you,Nor shall you worship any foreign
        god.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I am the Lord your God,Who brought you up from the land of Egypt.Open
        your mouth wide and I will fill it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBut My people would not listen to My voice,And Israel did not
        [consent to] obey Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So I gave them up to the stubbornness of their heart,To walk in [the
        path of] their own counsel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Oh, that My people would listen to Me,That Israel would walk in My
        ways!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then I would quickly subdue and humble their enemiesAnd turn My hand
        against their adversaries;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Those who hate the Lord would pretend obedience to Him and cringe
        before Him,And their time of punishment would be forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But I would feed Israel with the finest of the wheat;And with honey
        from the rock I would satisfy you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 82Unjust Judgments Rebuked.A Psalm of Asaph.'
      title: PSALM 82Unjust Judgments Rebuked.A Psalm of Asaph.
      number: 1
      content: '  God stands in the divine assembly;He judges among the gods (divine
        beings).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'How long will you judge unjustlyAnd show partiality to the wicked?
        Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Vindicate the weak and fatherless;Do justice and maintain the rights
        of the afflicted and destitute.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Rescue the weak and needy;Rescue them from the hand of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The rulers do not know nor do they understand;They walk on in the
        darkness [of complacent satisfaction];All the foundations of the earth [the
        fundamental principles of the administration of justice] are shaken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I said, \u201CYou are gods;Indeed, all of you are sons of the Most
        High.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Nevertheless you will die like menAnd fall like any one of the princes.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Arise, O God, judge the earth!For to You belong all the nations.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 83God Implored to Confound His Enemies.A Song. A Psalm of Asaph.'
      title: PSALM 83God Implored to Confound His Enemies.A Song. A Psalm of Asaph.
      number: 1
      content: '  Do not keep silent, O God;Do not hold Your peace or be still, O
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For behold, Your enemies are in tumult,And those who hate You have
        raised their heads [in hatred of You].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They concoct crafty schemes against Your people,And conspire together
        against Your hidden and precious ones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They have said, \u201CCome, and let us wipe them out as a nation;Let
        the name of Israel be remembered no more.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For they have conspired together with one mind;Against You they make
        a covenant\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The tents of Edom and the Ishmaelites,Of Moab and the Hagrites,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Gebal and Ammon and Amalek,Philistia with the inhabitants of Tyre.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Assyria also has joined with them;They have helped the children of
        Lot [the Ammonites and the Moabites] and have been an arm [of strength] to
        them. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Deal with them as [You did] with Midian,As with Sisera and Jabin
        at the brook of Kishon,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Who were destroyed at En-dor,Who became like dung for the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Make their nobles like Oreb and ZeebAnd all their princes like Zebah
        and Zalmunna,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Who said, \u201CLet us possess for ourselvesThe pastures of God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'O my God, make them like whirling dust,Like chaff before the wind
        [worthless and without substance].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Like fire consumes the forest,And like the flame sets the mountains
        on fire,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So pursue them with Your tempestAnd terrify them with [the violence
        of] Your storm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Fill their faces with shame and disgrace,That they may [persistently]
        seek Your name, O Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Let them be ashamed and dismayed forever;Yes, let them be humiliated
        and perish,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: That they may know that You alone, whose name is the Lord,Are the
        Most High over all the earth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 84Longing for the Temple Worship.To the Chief Musician; set
        to a A technical musical term, meaning uncertain.Philistine lute. A Psalm
        of the sons of Korah.'
      title: PSALM 84Longing for the Temple Worship.To the Chief Musician; set to
        a A technical musical term, meaning uncertain.Philistine lute. A Psalm of
        the sons of Korah.
      number: 1
      content: '  How lovely are Your dwelling places,O Lord of hosts!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'My soul (my life, my inner self) longs for and greatly desires the
        courts of the Lord;My heart and my flesh sing for joy to the living God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The bird has found a house,And the swallow a nest for herself, where
        she may lay her young\u2014Even Your altars, O Lord of hosts,My King and
        my God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Blessed and greatly favored are those who dwell in Your house and
        Your presence;They will be singing Your praises all the day long. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Blessed and greatly favored is the man whose strength is in You,In
        whose heart are the highways to Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Passing through the Valley of Weeping (Baca), they make it a place
        of springs;The early rain also covers it with blessings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They go from strength to strength [increasing in victorious power]; 
        Each of them appears before God in Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O Lord God of hosts, hear my prayer;Listen, O God of Jacob! Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'See our shield, O God,And look at the face of Your anointed [the
        king as Your representative].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For a day in Your courts is better than a thousand [anywhere else];I
        would rather stand [as a doorkeeper] at the threshold of the house of my
        GodThan to live [at ease] in the tents of wickedness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For the Lord God is a sun and shield;The Lord bestows grace and favor
        and honor;No good thing will He withhold from those who walk uprightly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: O Lord of hosts,How blessed and greatly favored is the man who trusts
        in You [believing in You, relying on You, and committing himself to You with
        confident hope and expectation].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 85Prayer for God\u2019s Mercy upon the Nation.To the Chief
        Musician. A Psalm of the sons of Korah."
      title: "PSALM 85Prayer for God\u2019s Mercy upon the Nation.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of the sons of Korah."
      number: 1
      content: '  O Lord, You have [at last] shown favor to Your land [of Canaan];You
        have restored [from Babylon] the captives of Jacob (Israel).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You have forgiven the wickedness of Your people;You have covered
        all their sin. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You have withdrawn all Your wrath,You have turned away from Your
        burning anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Restore us, O God of our salvation,And cause Your indignation toward
        us to cease.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Will You be angry with us forever?Will You prolong Your anger to
        all generations?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Will You not revive us and bring us to life again,That Your people
        may rejoice in You?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Show us Your lovingkindness, O Lord,And grant us Your salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I will hear [with expectant hope] what God the Lord will say,For
        He will speak peace to His people, to His godly ones\u2014But let them not
        turn again to folly.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Surely His salvation is near to those who [reverently] fear Him [and
        obey Him with submissive wonder],That glory [the manifest presence of God]
        may dwell in our land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Steadfast love and truth and faithfulness meet together;Righteousness
        and peace kiss each other.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Truth springs from the earth,And righteousness looks down from heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Indeed, the Lord will give what is good,And our land will yield its
        produce.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Righteousness will go before HimAnd will make His footsteps into a
        way [in which to walk].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 86A Psalm of Supplication and Trust.A Prayer of David.'
      title: PSALM 86A Psalm of Supplication and Trust.A Prayer of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Incline Your ear, O Lord, and answer me,For I am distressed and
        needy [I long for Your help].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Protect my life (soul), for I am godly and faithful;O You my God,
        save Your servant, who trusts in You [believing in You and relying on You,
        confidently committing everything to You].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Be gracious and merciful to me, O Lord,For to You I cry out all the
        day long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Make Your servant rejoice,For to You, O Lord, I lift up my soul [all
        that I am\u2014in prayer].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For You, O Lord, are good, and ready to forgive [our sins, sending
        them away, completely letting them go forever and ever];And abundant in lovingkindness
        and overflowing in mercy to all those who call upon You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Hear, O Lord, my prayer;And listen attentively to the voice of my
        supplications (specific requests)!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In the day of my trouble I will call upon You,For You will answer
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'There is no one like You among the gods, O Lord,Nor are there any
        works [of wonder and majesty] like Yours.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'All nations whom You have made shall come and kneel down in worship
        before You, O Lord,And they shall glorify Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For You are great and do wondrous works!You alone are God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Teach me Your way, O Lord,I will walk and live in Your truth;Direct
        my heart to fear Your name [with awe-inspired reverence and submissive wonder].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will give thanks and praise You, O Lord my God, with all my heart;And
        will glorify Your name forevermore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For great is Your lovingkindness and graciousness toward me;And You
        have rescued my life from the depths of Sheol [from death].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'O God, arrogant and insolent men have risen up against me;A band
        of violent men have sought my life,And they have not set You before them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But You, O Lord, are a God [who protects and is] merciful and gracious,Slow
        to anger and abounding in lovingkindness and truth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Turn to me, and be gracious to me;Grant Your strength [Your might
        and the power to resist temptation] to Your servant,And save the son of Your
        handmaid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Show me a sign of [Your] goodwill,That those who hate me may see it
        and be ashamed,Because You, O Lord, helped and comforted me.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 87The Privileges of Citizenship in Zion.A Psalm of the sons
        of Korah. A Song.'
      title: PSALM 87The Privileges of Citizenship in Zion.A Psalm of the sons of
        Korah. A Song.
      number: 1
      content: '  His foundation is on the holy mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord loves the gates of ZionMore than all the dwellings of Jacob
        (Israel).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Glorious things are spoken of you,O city of God [Jerusalem]. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI will mention Rahab (Egypt) and Babylon among those who know
        Me\u2014Behold, Philistia and Tyre with Ethiopia (Cush)\u2014\u2018This one
        was born there.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But of Zion it will be said, \u201CThis one and that one were born
        in her,\u201DAnd the Most High Himself will establish her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The Lord will count, when He registers the peoples,\u201CThis one
        was born there.\u201D Selah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The singers as well as the players of flutes will say,\u201CAll my
        springs and sources of joy are in you [Jerusalem, city of God].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 88A Petition to Be Saved from Death.A Song. A Psalm of the
        sons of Korah. To the Chief Musician; set to chant mournfully. A didactic
        or reflective poem of Heman the Ezrahite.'
      title: PSALM 88A Petition to Be Saved from Death.A Song. A Psalm of the sons
        of Korah. To the Chief Musician; set to chant mournfully. A didactic or reflective
        poem of Heman the Ezrahite.
      number: 1
      content: '  O Lord, the God of my salvation,I have cried out [for help] by
        day and in the night before You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Let my prayer come before You and enter into Your presence;Incline
        Your ear to my cry!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For my soul is full of troubles,And my life draws near the grave
        (Sheol, the place of the dead).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I am counted among those who go down to the pit (grave);I am like
        a man who has no strength [a mere shadow],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Cast away [from the living] and abandoned among the dead,Like the
        slain who lie in a [nameless] grave,Whom You no longer remember,And they
        are cut off from Your hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You have laid me in the lowest pit,In dark places, in the depths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Your wrath has rested heavily upon me,And You have afflicted me with
        all Your waves. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You have put my friends far from me;You have made me an object of
        loathing to them.I am shut up and I cannot go out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'My eye grows dim with sorrow.O Lord, I have called on You every day;I
        have spread out my hands to You [in prayer].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Will You perform wonders for the dead?Shall the departed spirits
        arise and praise You? Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Will Your lovingkindness be declared in the graveOr Your faithfulness
        in Abaddon (the underworld)?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Will Your wonders be known in the darkness?And Your righteousness
        in the land of forgetfulness [where the dead forget and are forgotten]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But I have cried out to You, O Lord, for help;And in the morning
        my prayer will come to You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'O Lord, why do You reject me?Why do You hide Your face from me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I was afflicted and close to death from my youth on;I suffer Your
        terrors; I am overcome.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Your fierce wrath has swept over me;Your terrors have destroyed me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They have surrounded me like flood waters all day long;They have
        completely encompassed me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Lover and friend You have placed far from me;My familiar friends are
        in darkness.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 89The Lord\u2019s Covenant with David, and Israel\u2019s Afflictions.A
        skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem, of Ethan the Ezrahite."
      title: "PSALM 89The Lord\u2019s Covenant with David, and Israel\u2019s Afflictions.A
        skillful song, or a didactic or reflective poem, of Ethan the Ezrahite."
      number: 1
      content: '  I will sing of the goodness and lovingkindness of the Lord forever;With
        my mouth I will make known Your faithfulness from generation to generation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For I have said, \u201CGoodness and lovingkindness will be built
        up forever;In the heavens [unchangeable and majestic] You will establish
        Your faithfulness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "[God has said] \u201CI have made a covenant with My chosen one;I
        have sworn to David My servant,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I will establish your seed foreverAnd I will build up your throne
        for all generations.\u201D Selah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The heavens (angels) praise Your wonders, O Lord,Your faithfulness
        also in the assembly of the holy ones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For who in the heavens can be compared to the Lord?Who among the
        divine beings is like the Lord,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'A God greatly feared and reverently worshiped in the council of the
        holy [angelic] ones,And awesome above all those who are around Him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O Lord God of hosts, who is like You, O mighty Lord?Your faithfulness
        surrounds You [as an intrinsic, unchangeable part of Your very being].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You rule the swelling of the sea;When its waves rise, You still them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You have crushed Rahab (Egypt) like one who is slain;You have scattered
        Your enemies with Your mighty arm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The heavens are Yours, the earth also is Yours;The world and all
        that is in it, You have founded and established them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The north and the south, You have created them;Mount Tabor and Mount
        Hermon shout for joy at Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You have a strong arm;Mighty is Your hand, Your right hand is exalted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Righteousness and justice are the foundation of Your throne;Lovingkindness
        and truth go before You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Blessed and happy are the people who know the joyful sound [of the
        trumpet\u2019s blast]!They walk, O Lord, in the light and favor of Your countenance!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'In Your name they rejoice all the day,And in Your righteousness they
        are exalted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For You are the glory of their strength [their proud adornment],And
        by Your favor our horn is exalted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For our shield belongs to the Lord,And our king to the Holy One of
        Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Once You spoke in a vision to Your godly ones,And said, \u201CI have
        given help to one who is mighty [giving him the power to be a champion for
        Israel];I have exalted one chosen from the people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I have found David My servant;With My holy oil I have anointed him,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'With whom My hand shall be established and steadfast;My arm also
        shall strengthen him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The enemy will not outwit him,Nor will the wicked man afflict or
        humiliate him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I will crush his adversaries before him,And strike those who hate
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'My faithfulness and My steadfast lovingkindness shall be with him,And
        in My name shall his horn be exalted [great power and prosperity shall be
        conferred upon him].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'I will also set his hand on the [Mediterranean] sea,And his right
        hand on the rivers [the tributaries of the Euphrates].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "He will cry to Me, \u2018You are my Father,My God, and the rock of
        my salvation.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'I will also make him My firstborn (preeminent),The highest of the
        kings of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'My lovingkindness I will keep for him forevermore,And My covenant
        will be confirmed to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'His descendants I will establish forever,And his throne [will endure]
        as the days of heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CIf his children turn away from My lawAnd do not walk in My
        ordinances,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'If they break My statutesAnd do not keep My commandments,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then I will punish their transgression with the rod [of discipline],And
        [correct] their wickedness with stripes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Nevertheless, I will not break off My lovingkindness from him,Nor
        allow My faithfulness to fail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'My covenant I will not violate,Nor will I alter the utterance of
        My lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Once [for all] I have sworn by My holiness, [My vow which cannot
        be violated];I will not lie to David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'His descendants shall endure foreverAnd his throne [will continue]
        as the sun before Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "It shall be established forever like the moon,And the witness in
        the heavens is ever faithful.\u201D Selah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'But [in apparent contradiction of all this] You [the faithful Lord]
        have cast off and rejected;You have been full of wrath against Your anointed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'You have spurned and repudiated the covenant with Your servant;You
        have profaned his crown [by casting it] in the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'You have broken down all his [city] walls;You have brought his strongholds
        to ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'All who pass along the road rob him;He has become the scorn of his
        neighbors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'You have exalted the right hand of his foes;You have made all his
        enemies rejoice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Also, You have turned back the edge of his swordAnd have not made
        him [strong enough] to stand in battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'You have put an end to his splendorAnd have hurled his throne to
        the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'You have shortened the days of his youth;You have covered him with
        shame. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'How long, O Lord?Will You hide Yourself forever?Will Your wrath burn
        like fire?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Remember how fleeting my lifetime is;For what vanity, [for what emptiness,
        for what futility, for what wisp of smoke] You have created all the sons
        of men!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'What man can live and not see death?Can he rescue his soul from the
        [powerful] hand of Sheol (the nether world, the place of the dead)? Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'O Lord, where are Your former lovingkindnesses [so abundant in the
        days of David and Solomon],Which You swore to David in Your faithfulness?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Remember, O Lord, the reproach of Your servants [scorned, insulted,
        and disgraced];How I bear in my heart the reproach of all the many peoples,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'With which Your enemies have taunted, O Lord,With which they have
        mocked the footsteps of Your anointed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: Blessed be the Lord forevermore!Amen and Amen.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: BOOK FOURPSALM 90God\u2019s Eternity and Man\u2019s Transitoriness.A
        Prayer of Moses the man of God."
      title: "BOOK FOURPSALM 90God\u2019s Eternity and Man\u2019s Transitoriness.A
        Prayer of Moses the man of God."
      number: 1
      content: '  Lord, You have been our dwelling place [our refuge, our sanctuary,
        our stability] in all generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Before the mountains were bornOr before You had given birth to the
        earth and the world,Even from everlasting to everlasting, You are [the eternal]
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You turn man back to dust,And say, \u201CReturn [to the earth], O
        children of [mortal] men!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For a thousand years in Your sightAre like yesterday when it is past,Or
        as a watch in the night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "You have swept them away like a flood, they fall asleep [forgotten
        as soon as they are gone];In the morning they are like grass which grows
        anew\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In the morning it flourishes and springs up;In the evening it wilts
        and withers away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For we have been consumed by Your angerAnd by Your wrath we have
        been terrified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You have placed our wickedness before you,Our secret sins [which
        we tried to conceal, You have placed] in the [revealing] light of Your presence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For all our days pass away in Your wrath;We have finished our years
        like a whispered sigh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The days of our life are seventy years\u2014Or even, if because of
        strength, eighty years;Yet their pride [in additional years] is only labor
        and sorrow,For it is soon gone and we fly away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Who understands the power of Your anger? [Who connects this brevity
        of life among us with Your judgment of sin?]And Your wrath, [who connects
        it] with the [reverent] fear that is due You?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So teach us to number our days,That we may cultivate and bring to
        You a heart of wisdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Turn, O Lord [from Your fierce anger]; how long will it be?Be compassionate
        toward Your servants\u2014revoke Your sentence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'O satisfy us with Your lovingkindness in the morning [now, before
        we grow older],That we may rejoice and be glad all our days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Make us glad in proportion to the days You have afflicted us,And
        the years we have suffered evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Let Your work [the signs of Your power] be revealed to Your servantsAnd
        Your [glorious] majesty to their children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And let the [gracious] favor of the Lord our God be on us;Confirm
        for us the work of our hands\u2014Yes, confirm the work of our hands."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 91Security of the One Who Trusts in the Lord.'
      title: PSALM 91Security of the One Who Trusts in the Lord.
      number: 1
      content: '  He who dwells in the shelter of the Most HighWill remain secure
        and rest in the shadow of the Almighty [whose power no enemy can withstand].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I will say of the Lord, \u201CHe is my refuge and my fortress,My
        God, in whom I trust [with great confidence, and on whom I rely]!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For He will save you from the trap of the fowler,And from the deadly
        pestilence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He will cover you and completely protect you with His pinions,And
        under His wings you will find refuge;His faithfulness is a shield and a wall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You will not be afraid of the terror of night,Nor of the arrow that
        flies by day,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Nor of the pestilence that stalks in darkness,Nor of the destruction
        (sudden death) that lays waste at noon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'A thousand may fall at your sideAnd ten thousand at your right hand,But
        danger will not come near you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You will only [be a spectator as you] look on with your eyesAnd witness
        the [divine] repayment of the wicked [as you watch safely from the shelter
        of the Most High].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Because you have made the Lord, [who is] my refuge,Even the Most
        High, your dwelling place,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'No evil will befall you,Nor will any plague come near your tent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For He will command His angels in regard to you,To protect and defend
        and guard you in all your ways [of obedience and service].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They will lift you up in their hands,So that you do not [even] strike
        your foot against a stone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You will tread upon the lion and cobra;The young lion and the serpent
        you will trample underfoot.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CBecause he set his love on Me, therefore I will save him;I
        will set him [securely] on high, because he knows My name [he confidently
        trusts and relies on Me, knowing I will never abandon him, no, never].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He will call upon Me, and I will answer him;I will be with him in
        trouble;I will rescue him and honor him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "With a long life I will satisfy himAnd I will let him see My salvation.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 92Praise for the Lord\u2019s Goodness.A Psalm. A Song for the
        Sabbath day."
      title: "PSALM 92Praise for the Lord\u2019s Goodness.A Psalm. A Song for the
        Sabbath day."
      number: 1
      content: '  It is a good and delightful thing to give thanks to the Lord,To
        sing praises to Your name, O Most High,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'To declare Your lovingkindness in the morningAnd Your faithfulness
        by night,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'With an instrument of ten strings and with the harp,With a solemn
        sound on the lyre.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For You, O Lord, have made me glad by Your works;At the works of
        Your hands I joyfully sing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "How great are Your works, O Lord!Your thoughts are very deep [beyond
        man\u2019s understanding].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'A senseless man [in his crude and uncultivated state] knows nothing,Nor
        does a [self-righteous] fool understand this:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'That though the wicked sprout up like grassAnd all evildoers flourish,They
        will be destroyed forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But You, Lord, are on high forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For behold, Your enemies, O Lord,For behold, Your enemies will perish;All
        who do evil will be scattered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But my horn [my emblem of strength and power] You have exalted like
        that of a wild ox;I am anointed with fresh oil [for Your service].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'My eye has looked on my foes;My ears hear of the evildoers who rise
        up against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The righteous will flourish like the date palm [long-lived, upright
        and useful];They will grow like a cedar in Lebanon [majestic and stable].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Planted in the house of the Lord,They will flourish in the courts
        of our God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '[Growing in grace] they will still thrive and bear fruit and prosper
        in old age;They will flourish and be vital and fresh [rich in trust and love
        and contentment];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '[They are living memorials] to declare that the Lord is upright and
        faithful [to His promises];He is my rock, and there is no unrighteousness
        in Him.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 93The Majesty of the Lord.'
      title: PSALM 93The Majesty of the Lord.
      number: 1
      content: '  The Lord reigns, He is clothed with majesty and splendor;The Lord
        has clothed and encircled Himself with strength;the world is firmly established,
        it cannot be moved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Your throne is established from of old;You are from everlasting.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The floods have lifted up, O Lord,The floods have lifted up their
        voice;The floods lift up their pounding waves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'More than the sounds of many waters,More than the mighty breakers
        of the sea,The Lord on high is mighty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Your precepts are fully confirmed and completely reliable;Holiness
        adorns Your house,O Lord, forever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 94The Lord Implored to Avenge His People.'
      title: PSALM 94The Lord Implored to Avenge His People.
      number: 1
      content: '  O Lord God, You to whom vengeance belongs,O God, You to whom vengeance
        belongs, shine forth [in judgment]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Rise up, O Judge of the earth;Give to the proud a fitting compensation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'O Lord, how long will the wicked,How long will the wicked rejoice
        in triumph?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They pour out words, speaking arrogant things;All who do evil boast
        proudly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They crush Your people, O Lord,And afflict and abuse Your heritage.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  They kill the widow and the alienAnd murder the fatherless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Yet they say, \u201CThe Lord does not see,Nor does the God of Jacob
        (Israel) notice it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Consider thoughtfully, you senseless (stupid ones) among the people;And
        you [dull-minded] fools, when will you become wise and understand?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He who made the ear, does He not hear?He who formed the eye, does
        He not see?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He who instructs the nations,Does He not rebuke and punish,He who
        teaches man knowledge?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The Lord knows the thoughts of man,That they are a mere breath (vain,
        empty, futile).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Blessed [with wisdom and prosperity] is the man whom You discipline
        and instruct, O Lord,And whom You teach from Your law,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'That You may grant him [power to calm himself and find] peace in
        the days of adversity,Until the pit is dug for the wicked and ungodly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For the Lord will not abandon His people,Nor will He abandon His
        inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For judgment will again be righteous,And all the upright in heart
        will follow it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Who will stand up for me against the evildoers?Who will take a stand
        for me against those who do wickedness?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'If the Lord had not been my help,I would soon have dwelt in [the
        land of] silence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "If I say, \u201CMy foot has slipped,\u201DYour compassion and lovingkindness,
        O Lord, will hold me up.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When my anxious thoughts multiply within me,Your comforts delight
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Can a throne of destruction be allied with You,One which frames and
        devises mischief by decree [under the sacred name of law]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They band themselves together against the life of the righteousAnd
        condemn the innocent to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But the Lord has become my high tower and defense,And my God the
        rock of my refuge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: He has turned back their own wickedness upon themAnd will destroy
        them by means of their own evil;The Lord our God will wipe them out.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 95Praise to the Lord, and Warning against Unbelief.'
      title: PSALM 95Praise to the Lord, and Warning against Unbelief.
      number: 1
      content: '  O come, let us sing joyfully to the Lord;Let us shout joyfully
        to the rock of our salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Let us come before His presence with a song of thanksgiving;Let us
        shout joyfully to Him with songs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For the Lord is a great GodAnd a great King above all gods,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'In whose hand are the depths of the earth;The peaks of the mountains
        are His also.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The sea is His, for He made it [by His command];And His hands formed
        the dry land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'O come, let us worship and bow down,Let us kneel before the Lord
        our Maker [in reverent praise and prayer].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For He is our GodAnd we are the people of His pasture and the sheep
        of His hand.Today, if you will hear His voice,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Do not harden your hearts and become spiritually dull as at Meribah
        [the place of strife],And as at Massah [the place of testing] in the wilderness,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhen your fathers tested Me,They tried Me, even though they
        had seen My work [of miracles].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For forty years I was grieved and disgusted with that generation,And
        I said, \u2018They are a people who err in their heart,And they do not acknowledge
        or regard My ways.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore I swore [an oath] in My wrath,\u2018They absolutely shall
        not enter My rest [the land of promise].\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 96A Call to Worship the Lord the Righteous Judge.'
      title: PSALM 96A Call to Worship the Lord the Righteous Judge.
      number: 1
      content: '  O sing to the Lord a new song;Sing to the Lord, all the earth!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Sing to the Lord, bless His name;Proclaim good news of His salvation
        from day to day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Declare His glory among the nations,His marvelous works and wonderful
        deeds among all the peoples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For great is the Lord and greatly to be praised;He is to be feared
        above all gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For all the gods of the peoples are [worthless, lifeless] idols,But
        the Lord made the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Splendor and majesty are before Him;Strength and beauty are in His
        sanctuary.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Ascribe to the Lord, O families of the peoples,Ascribe to the Lord
        glory and strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ascribe to the Lord the glory of His name;Bring an offering and come
        into His courts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Worship the Lord in the splendor of holiness;Tremble [in submissive
        wonder] before Him, all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Say among the nations, \u201CThe Lord reigns;Indeed, the world is
        firmly and securely established, it shall not be moved;He will judge and
        rule the people with fairness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Let the heavens be glad, and let the earth rejoice;Let the sea roar,
        and all the things it contains;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Let the field be exultant, and all that is in it.Then all the trees
        of the forest will sing for joy  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Before the Lord, for He is coming,For He is coming to judge the earth.He
        will judge the world with righteousnessAnd the peoples in His faithfulness.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 97The Lord\u2019s Power and Dominion."
      title: "PSALM 97The Lord\u2019s Power and Dominion."
      number: 1
      content: '  The Lord reigns, let the earth rejoice;Let the many islands and
        coastlands be glad.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Clouds and thick darkness surround Him [as at Sinai];Righteousness
        and justice are the foundation of His throne.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Fire goes before HimAnd burns up His adversaries on all sides.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'His lightnings have illuminated the world;The earth has seen and
        trembled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The mountains melted like wax at the presence of the Lord,At the
        presence of the Lord of the whole earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The heavens declare His righteousness,And all the peoples see His
        glory and brilliance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Let all those be [deeply] ashamed who serve carved images,Who boast
        in idols.Worship Him, all you gods!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Zion heard this and was glad,And the daughters (cities) of Judah
        rejoiced [in relief]Because of Your judgments, O Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For You are the Lord Most High over all the earth;You are exalted
        far above all gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You who love the Lord, hate evil;He protects the souls of His godly
        ones (believers),He rescues them from the hand of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Light is sown [like seed] for the righteous and illuminates their
        path,And [irrepressible] joy [is spread] for the upright in heart [who delight
        in His favor and protection].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Rejoice in the Lord, you righteous ones [those whose moral and spiritual
        integrity places them in right standing with God],And praise and give thanks
        at the remembrance of His holy name.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 98A Call to Praise the Lord for His Righteousness.A The ancient
        rabbis called this song \u201Corphaned\u201D because it is anonymous and
        has no description with the word \u201CPsalm\u201D (e.g. \u201CA Psalm of
        Thanksgiving\u201D).Psalm."
      title: "PSALM 98A Call to Praise the Lord for His Righteousness.A The ancient
        rabbis called this song \u201Corphaned\u201D because it is anonymous and
        has no description with the word \u201CPsalm\u201D (e.g. \u201CA Psalm of
        Thanksgiving\u201D).Psalm."
      number: 1
      content: '  O sing to the Lord a new song,For He has done marvelous and wonderful
        things;His right hand and His holy arm have gained the victory for Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord has made known His salvation;He has [openly] revealed His
        righteousness in the sight of the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He has [graciously] remembered His lovingkindness and His faithfulness
        to the house of Israel;All the ends of the earth have witnessed the salvation
        of our God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Shout joyfully to the Lord, all the earth;Shout [in jubilation] and
        sing for joy and sing praises.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Sing praises to the Lord with the lyre,With the lyre and the sound
        of melody.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'With trumpets and the sound of the hornShout with joy before the
        King, the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Let the sea thunder and roar, and all the things it contains,The
        world and those who dwell in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Let the rivers clap their hands;Let the mountains sing together for
        joy and delight  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Before the Lord, for He is coming to judge the earth;He will judge
        the world with righteousnessAnd the peoples with fairness.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 99Praise to the Lord for His Fidelity to Israel.'
      title: PSALM 99Praise to the Lord for His Fidelity to Israel.
      number: 1
      content: '  The Lord reigns, let the peoples tremble [with submissive wonder]!He
        sits enthroned above the cherubim, let the earth shake!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord is great in Zion,And He is exalted and magnified above all
        the peoples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Let them [reverently] praise Your great and awesome name;Holy is
        He.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The strength of the King loves justice and righteous judgment;You
        have established fairness;You have executed justice and righteousness in
        Jacob (Israel).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Exalt the Lord our GodAnd worship at His footstool;Holy is He.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Moses and Aaron were among His priests,And Samuel was among those
        who called on His name;They called upon the Lord and He answered them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He spoke to them in the pillar of cloud;They kept His testimoniesAnd
        the statutes that He gave them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You answered them, O Lord our God;You were a forgiving God to them,And
        yet an avenger of their evil practices.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Exalt the Lord our GodAnd worship at His holy hill [Zion, the temple
        mount],For the Lord our God is holy.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 100All Men Exhorted to Praise God.A Psalm of Thanksgiving.'
      title: PSALM 100All Men Exhorted to Praise God.A Psalm of Thanksgiving.
      number: 1
      content: '  Shout joyfully to the Lord, all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Serve the Lord with gladness and delight;Come before His presence
        with joyful singing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Know and fully recognize with gratitude that the Lord Himself is
        God;It is He who has made us, not we ourselves [and we are His].  We are
        His people and the sheep of His pasture.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Enter His gates with a song of thanksgivingAnd His courts with praise.Be
        thankful to Him, bless and praise His name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: For the Lord is good;His mercy and lovingkindness are everlasting,His
        faithfulness [endures] to all generations.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 101The Psalmist\u2019s Profession of Uprightness.A Psalm of
        David."
      title: "PSALM 101The Psalmist\u2019s Profession of Uprightness.A Psalm of David."
      number: 1
      content: '  I will sing of [steadfast] lovingkindness and justice;To You, O
        Lord, I will sing praises.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will behave wisely and follow the way of integrity.When will You
        come to me?I will walk in my house in integrity and with a blameless heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I will set no worthless or wicked thing before my eyes.I hate the
        practice of those who fall away [from the right path];It will not grasp hold
        of me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'A perverse heart shall depart from me;I will not tolerate evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Whoever secretly slanders his neighbor, him I will silence;The one
        who has a haughty look and a proud (arrogant) heart I will not tolerate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'My eyes will be on the faithful (honorable) of the land, that they
        may dwell with me;He who walks blamelessly is the one who will minister to
        and serve me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He who practices deceit will not dwell in my house;He who tells lies
        and half-truths will not continue [to remain] in my presence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Morning after morning I will destroy all the wicked in the land,That
        I may cut off from the city of the Lord all those who do evil.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 102Prayer of an Afflicted Man for Mercy on Himself and on Zion.A
        Prayer of the afflicted; when he is overwhelmed and pours out his complaint
        to God.'
      title: PSALM 102Prayer of an Afflicted Man for Mercy on Himself and on Zion.A
        Prayer of the afflicted; when he is overwhelmed and pours out his complaint
        to God.
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear my prayer, O Lord,And let my cry for help come to You!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Do not hide Your face from me in the day of my distress!Incline Your
        ear to me;In the day when I call, answer me quickly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For my days have vanished in smoke,And my bones have been scorched
        like a hearth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'My heart has been struck like grass and withered,Indeed, [absorbed
        by my heartache] I forget to eat my food.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Because of the sound of my groaning [in suffering and trouble]My
        bones cling to my flesh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I am like a [mournful] vulture of the wilderness;I am like a [desolate]
        owl of the wasteland.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I am sleepless and lie awake [mourning],I have become like a lonely
        bird on a housetop.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'My enemies taunt me all day long;Those who ridicule me use my name
        as a curse.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For I have eaten ashes like bread,And have mingled my drink with
        tears  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Because of Your indignation and Your wrath,For You have lifted me
        up and thrown me away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'My days are like an evening shadow that lengthens and vanishes [with
        the sun];And as for me, I wither away like grass.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But You, O Lord, are enthroned forever [ruling eternally as sovereign];And
        [the fame and glory of] Your name [endures] to all generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You will arise and have compassion on Zion,For it is time to be gracious
        and show favor to her;Yes, the appointed time [the moment designated] has
        come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For Your servants find [melancholy] pleasure in the stones [of her
        ruins]And feel pity for her dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the nations will fear the name of the Lord,And all the kings of
        the earth [will recognize] Your glory.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For the Lord has built up Zion;He has appeared in His glory and brilliance;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He has regarded the prayer of the destitute,And has not despised
        their prayer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Let this be recorded for the generation to come,That a people yet
        to be created will praise the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For He looked down from His holy height [of His sanctuary],From heaven
        the Lord gazed on the earth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'To hear the sighing of the prisoner,To set free those who were doomed
        to death,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So that people may declare the name of the Lord in ZionAnd His praise
        in Jerusalem,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When the peoples are gathered together,And the kingdoms, to serve
        the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He has exhausted my strength [humbling me with sorrow] in the way;He
        has shortened my days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "I said, \u201CO my God, do not take me away in the midst of my days;Your
        years are [eternal] throughout all generations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'At the beginning You founded the earth;The heavens are the work of
        Your hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Even they will perish, but You endure;Yes, all of them will wear
        out like a garment.Like clothing You will change them and they shall be changed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But You remain the same,And Your years will never end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The children of Your servants will continue,And their descendants
        will be established before You.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 103Praise for the Lord\u2019s Mercies.  A Psalm of David."
      title: "PSALM 103Praise for the Lord\u2019s Mercies.  A Psalm of David."
      number: 1
      content: '  Bless and affectionately praise the Lord, O my soul,And all that
        is [deep] within me, bless His holy name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Bless and affectionately praise the Lord, O my soul,And do not forget
        any of His benefits;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Who forgives all your sins,Who heals all your diseases;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Who redeems your life from the pit,Who crowns you [lavishly] with
        lovingkindness and tender mercy;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Who satisfies your years with good things,So that your youth is renewed
        like the [soaring] eagle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The Lord executes righteousnessAnd justice for all the oppressed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He made known His ways [of righteousness and justice] to Moses,His
        acts to the children of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord is merciful and gracious,Slow to anger and abounding in
        compassion and lovingkindness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He will not always strive with us,Nor will He keep His anger forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He has not dealt with us according to our sins [as we deserve],Nor
        rewarded us [with punishment] according to our wickedness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For as the heavens are high above the earth,So great is His lovingkindness
        toward those who fear and worship Him [with awe-filled respect and deepest
        reverence].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'As far as the east is from the west,So far has He removed our transgressions
        from us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Just as a father loves his children,So the Lord loves those who fear
        and worship Him [with awe-filled respect and deepest reverence].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For He knows our [mortal] frame;He remembers that we are [merely]
        dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'As for man, his days are like grass;Like a flower of the field, so
        he flourishes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For the wind passes over it and it is no more,And its place knows
        it no longer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But the lovingkindness of the Lord is from everlasting to everlasting
        on those who [reverently] fear Him,And His righteousness to children\u2019s
        children,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'To those who honor and keep His covenant,And remember to do His commandments
        [imprinting His word on their hearts].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The Lord has established His throne in the heavens,And His sovereignty
        rules over all [the universe].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Bless the Lord, you His angels,You mighty ones who do His commandments,Obeying
        the voice of His word!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Bless the Lord, all you His hosts,You who serve Him and do His will.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Bless the Lord, all you works of His, in all places of His dominion;Bless
        and affectionately praise the Lord, O my soul!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 104The Lord\u2019s Care over All His Works."
      title: "PSALM 104The Lord\u2019s Care over All His Works."
      number: 1
      content: '  Bless and affectionately praise the Lord, O my soul!O Lord my God,
        You are very great;You are clothed with splendor and majesty,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '[You are the One] who covers Yourself with light as with a garment,Who
        stretches out the heavens like a tent curtain,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Who lays the beams of His upper chambers in the waters [above the
        firmament],Who makes the clouds His chariot,Who walks on the wings of the
        wind,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Who makes winds His messengers,Flames of fire His ministers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He established the earth on its foundations,So that it will not be
        moved forever and ever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You covered it with the deep as with a garment;The waters were standing
        above the mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'At Your rebuke they fled;At the sound of Your thunder they hurried
        away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The mountains rose, the valleys sank downTo the place which You established
        for them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You set a boundary [for the waters] that they may not cross over,So
        that they will not return to cover the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You send springs into the valleys;Their waters flow among the mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They give drink to every beast of the field;The wild donkeys quench
        their thirst there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Beside them the birds of the heavens have their nests;They lift up
        their voices and sing among the branches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He waters the mountains from His upper chambers;The earth is satisfied
        with the fruit of His works.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He causes grass to grow for the cattle,And all that the earth produces
        for cultivation by man,So that he may bring food from the earth\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And wine which makes the heart of man glad,So that he may make his
        face glisten with oil,And bread to sustain and strengthen man\u2019s heart.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The trees of the Lord drink their fill,The cedars of Lebanon which
        He has planted,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Where the birds make their nests;As for the stork, the fir trees
        are her house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The high mountains are for the wild goats;The rocks are a refuge
        for the shephanim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He made the moon for the seasons;The sun knows the [exact] place
        of its setting.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You [O Lord] make darkness and it becomes night,In which prowls about
        every wild beast of the forest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The young lions roar after their preyAnd seek their food from God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When the sun arises, they withdrawAnd lie down in their dens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Man goes out to his workAnd remains at his labor until evening.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'O Lord, how many and varied are Your works!In wisdom You have made
        them all;The earth is full of Your riches and Your creatures.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'There is the sea, great and broad,In which are swarms without number,Creatures
        both small and great.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'There the ships [of the sea] sail,And Leviathan [the sea monster],
        which You have formed to play there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'They all wait for YouTo give them their food in its appointed season.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'You give it to them, they gather it up;You open Your hand, they are
        filled and satisfied with good [things].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'You hide Your face, they are dismayed;You take away their breath,
        they dieAnd return to their dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'You send out Your Spirit, they are created;You renew the face of
        the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "May the glory of the Lord endure forever;May the Lord rejoice and
        be glad in His works\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He looks at the earth, and it trembles;He touches the mountains,
        and they smoke.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'I will sing to the Lord as long as I live;I will sing praise to my
        God while I have my being.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'May my meditation be sweet and pleasing to Him;As for me, I will
        rejoice and be glad in the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: Let sinners be consumed from the earth,And let the wicked be no more.Bless
        and affectionately praise the Lord, O my soul.Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 105The Lord\u2019s Wonderful Works in Behalf of Israel."
      title: "PSALM 105The Lord\u2019s Wonderful Works in Behalf of Israel."
      number: 1
      content: '  O give thanks to the Lord, call upon His name;Make known His deeds
        among the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Sing to Him, sing praises to Him;Speak of all His wonderful acts
        and devoutly praise them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Glory in His holy name;Let the hearts of those who seek and require
        the Lord [as their most essential need] rejoice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Seek and deeply long for the Lord and His strength [His power, His
        might];Seek and deeply long for His face and His presence continually.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Remember [with awe and gratitude] the wonderful things which He has
        done,His amazing deeds and the judgments uttered by His mouth [on His enemies,
        as in Egypt],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'O you offspring of Abraham, His servant,O you sons of Jacob, His
        chosen ones!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He is the Lord our God;His judgments are in all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He has remembered His covenant forever,The word which He commanded
        and established to a thousand generations,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  The covenant which He made with Abraham,And His sworn oath to Isaac,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Which He confirmed to Jacob as a statute,To Israel as an everlasting
        covenant,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Saying, \u201CTo you I will give the land of CanaanAs the measured
        portion of your inheritance.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When there were only a few men in number,Very few [in fact], and
        strangers in it;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And they wandered from one nation to another,From one kingdom to
        another people,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He allowed no man to oppress them;He rebuked kings for their sakes,
        saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CDo not touch My anointed ones,And do My prophets no harm.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And He called for a famine upon the land [of Egypt];He cut off every
        source of bread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He sent a man before them,Joseph, who was sold as a slave.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'His feet they hurt with shackles;  He was put in chains of iron,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Until the time that his word [of prophecy regarding his brothers]
        came true,The word of the Lord tested and refined him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The king sent and released him,The ruler of the peoples [of Egypt],
        and set him free.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He made Joseph lord of his houseAnd ruler of all his possessions,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'To imprison his princes at his will,That he might teach his elders
        wisdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Israel also came into Egypt;Thus Jacob sojourned in the land of Ham.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'There the Lord greatly increased [the number of] His people,And made
        them more powerful than their enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He turned the heart [of the Egyptians] to hate His people,To deal
        craftily with His servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He sent Moses His servant,And Aaron, whom He had chosen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'They exhibited His wondrous signs among them,  Great miracles in
        the land of Ham (Egypt).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He sent [thick, oppressive] darkness and made the land dark;And Moses
        and Aaron did not rebel against His words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "He turned Egypt\u2019s waters into bloodAnd caused their fish to
        die.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Their land swarmed with frogs,Even in the chambers of their kings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'He spoke, and there came swarms of fliesAnd gnats in all their territory.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He gave them hail for rain,With flaming fire in their land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He struck their vines also and their fig trees,And shattered the
        [ice-laden] trees of their territory.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'He spoke, and the [migratory] locusts came,And the young locusts,
        even without number,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And ate up all the vegetation in their land,And devoured the fruit
        of their ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'He also struck down all the firstborn in their land,The first fruits
        and chief substance of all their strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'He brought the sons of Israel out [of Egypt] with silver and gold,And
        among their tribes there was not one who stumbled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Egypt was glad when they departed,For the dread and fear of them
        had fallen on the Egyptians.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'The Lord spread a cloud as a covering [by day],And a fire to illumine
        the night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The Israelites asked, and He brought quail,And satisfied them with
        the bread of heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'He opened the rock and water flowed out;It ran in the dry places
        like a river.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'For He remembered His holy wordTo Abraham His servant;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'He brought out His people with joy,And His chosen ones with a joyful
        shout,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "He gave them the lands of the nations [of Canaan],So that they would
        possess the fruits of those peoples\u2019 labor,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: So that they might observe His preceptsAnd keep His laws [obediently
        accepting and honoring and valuing them].Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 106Israel\u2019s Rebelliousness and the Lord\u2019s Deliverances."
      title: "PSALM 106Israel\u2019s Rebelliousness and the Lord\u2019s Deliverances."
      number: 1
      content: '  Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)Oh give thanks to the Lord, for He
        is good;For His mercy and lovingkindness endure forever!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Who can put into words the mighty deeds of the Lord?Or who can proclaim
        all His praise [that is due Him]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Blessed are those who observe justice [by honoring God\u2019s precepts],Who
        practice righteousness at all times.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Remember me, O Lord, when You favor Your people.Visit me with Your
        salvation [when You rescue them],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'That I may see the prosperity of Your chosen ones,That I may rejoice
        in the gladness of Your nation,That I may glory with Your inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'We have sinned like our fathers;We have committed iniquity, we have
        behaved wickedly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Our fathers in Egypt did not understand nor appreciate Your miracles;They
        did not remember the abundance of Your mercies nor imprint Your lovingkindnesses
        on their hearts,But they were rebellious at the sea, at the Red Sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Nevertheless He saved them for His name\u2019s sake,That He might
        make His [supreme] power known.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He rebuked the Red Sea, and it dried up;And He led them through the
        depths as through a pasture.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So He saved them from the hand of the one that hated them,And redeemed
        them from the hand of the [Egyptian] enemy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the waters covered their adversaries;Not one of them was left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Israel believed in [the validity of] His words;They sang His
        praise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But they quickly forgot His works;They did not [patiently] wait for
        His counsel and purpose [to be revealed regarding them],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But lusted intensely in the wildernessAnd tempted God [with their
        insistent desires] in the desert.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So He gave them their request,But sent a wasting disease among them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They envied Moses in the camp,And Aaron [the high priest], the holy
        one of the Lord,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore the earth opened and swallowed Dathan,And engulfed the
        company of Abiram.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And a fire broke out in their company;The flame consumed the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They made a calf in Horeb (Sinai)And worshiped a cast image.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Thus they exchanged [the true God who was] their gloryFor the image
        of an ox that eats grass.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They forgot God their Savior,Who had done such great things in Egypt,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Wonders in the land of Ham,Awesome things at the Red Sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Therefore He said He would destroy them,[And He would have done so]
        had not Moses, His chosen one, stepped into the gap before Him,To turn away
        His wrath from destroying them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then they despised the pleasant land [of Canaan];They did not believe
        in His word nor rely on it,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But they sulked and complained in their tents;They did not listen
        to the voice of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Therefore He lifted up His hand [swearing] to them,That He would
        cause them to fall in the wilderness,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And that He would cast out their descendants among the nationsAnd
        scatter them in the lands [of the earth].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They joined themselves also to [the idol] Baal of Peor,And ate sacrifices
        offered to the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Thus they provoked Him to anger with their practices,And a plague
        broke out among them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Phinehas [the priest] stood up and interceded,And so the plague
        was halted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And that was credited to him for righteousness,To all generations
        forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'They provoked Him to anger at the waters of Meribah,So that it went
        hard with Moses on their account;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Because they were rebellious against His Spirit,Moses spoke recklessly
        with his lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'They did not destroy the [pagan] peoples [in Canaan],As the Lord
        commanded them,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'But they mingled with the [idolatrous] nationsAnd learned their ways,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And served their idols,Which became a [dreadful] snare to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'They even sacrificed their sons and their daughters to demons  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And shed innocent blood,Even the blood of their sons and of their
        daughters,Whom they sacrificed to the idols of Canaan;And the land was polluted
        with their blood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "In this way they became unclean in their practices;They played the
        prostitute in their own deeds [by giving their worship, which belongs to
        God alone, to other \u201Cgods\u201D].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Therefore the anger of the Lord was kindled against His peopleAnd
        He detested His own inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'He gave them into the hands of the nations,And those who hated them
        ruled over them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Their enemies also oppressed them,And they were subdued under the
        [powerful] hand of their enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Many times He rescued them;But they were rebellious in their counsel,And
        sank down in their wickedness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Nevertheless He looked [sympathetically] at their distressWhen He
        heard their cry;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And He remembered His covenant for their sake,And relented [rescinding
        their sentence] according to the greatness of His lovingkindness [when they
        cried out to Him],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'He also made them objects of compassionAmong those who had carried
        them away captive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Save us, O Lord our God,And gather us from among the nations,That
        we may give thanks to Your holy nameAnd glory in praising You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Blessed be the Lord, the God of Israel,From everlasting even to everlasting.And
        let all the people say, \u201CAmen.\u201DPraise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: BOOK FIVEPSALM 107The Lord Rescues People from Many Troubles.'
      title: BOOK FIVEPSALM 107The Lord Rescues People from Many Troubles.
      number: 1
      content: '  O give thanks to the Lord, for He is good;For His compassion and
        lovingkindness endure forever!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Let the redeemed of the Lord say so,Whom He has redeemed from the
        hand of the adversary,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And gathered them from the lands,From the east and from the west,From
        the north and from the south.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They wandered in the wilderness in a [solitary] desert region;And
        did not find a way to an inhabited city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Hungry and thirsty,They fainted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then they cried out to the Lord in their trouble,And He rescued them
        from their distresses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He led them by the straight way,To an inhabited city [where they
        could establish their homes].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Let them give thanks to the Lord for His lovingkindness,And for His
        wonderful acts to the children of men!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For He satisfies the parched throat,And fills the hungry appetite
        with what is good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Some dwelt in darkness and in the deep (deathly) darkness,Prisoners
        [bound] in misery and chains,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Because they had rebelled against the precepts of GodAnd spurned
        the counsel of the Most High.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore He humbled their heart with hard labor;They stumbled and
        there was no one to help.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then they cried out to the Lord in their trouble,And He saved them
        from their distresses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He brought them out of darkness and the deep (deathly) darknessAnd
        broke their bonds apart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Let them give thanks to the Lord for His lovingkindness,And for His
        wonderful acts to the children of men!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For He has shattered the gates of bronzeAnd cut the bars of iron
        apart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Fools, because of their rebellious way,And because of their sins,
        were afflicted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They detested all kinds of food,And they drew near to the gates of
        death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then they cried out to the Lord in their trouble,And He saved them
        from their distresses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He sent His word and healed them,And rescued them from their destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Let them give thanks to the Lord for His lovingkindness,And for His
        wonderful acts to the children of men!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And let them offer the sacrifices of thanksgiving,And speak of His
        deeds with shouts of joy!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Those who go down to the sea in ships,Who do business on great waters;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'They have seen the works of the Lord,And His wonders in the deep.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For He spoke and raised up a stormy wind,Which lifted up the waves
        of the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'They went up toward the heavens [on the crest of the wave], they
        went down again to the depths [of the watery trough];Their courage melted
        away in their misery.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "They staggered and trembled like a drunken man,And were at their
        wits\u2019 end [all their wisdom was useless].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then they cried out to the Lord in their trouble,And He brought them
        out of their distresses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He hushed the storm to a gentle whisper,So that the waves of the
        sea were still.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then they were glad because of the calm,And He guided them to their
        desired haven (harbor).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Let them give thanks to the Lord for His lovingkindness,And for His
        wonderful acts to the children of men!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Let them exalt Him also in the congregation of the people,And praise
        Him at the seat of the elders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He turns rivers into a wilderness,And springs of water into a thirsty
        ground;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'A productive land into a [barren] salt waste,Because of the wickedness
        of those who dwell in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'He turns a wilderness into a pool of waterAnd a dry land into springs
        of water;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And there He has the hungry dwell,So that they may establish an inhabited
        city,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And sow fields and plant vineyards,And produce an abundant harvest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Also He blesses them so that they multiply greatly,And He does not
        let [the number of] their cattle decrease.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'When they are diminished and bowed down (humbled)Through oppression,
        misery, and sorrow,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'He pours contempt on princesAnd makes them wander in a pathless wasteland.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Yet He sets the needy securely on high, away from affliction,And
        makes their families like a flock.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The upright see it and rejoice;But all unrighteousness shuts its
        mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Who is wise? Let him observe and heed these things;And [thoughtfully]
        consider the lovingkindness of the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 108Praise and Supplication to God for Victory.A Song. A Psalm
        of David.'
      title: PSALM 108Praise and Supplication to God for Victory.A Song. A Psalm
        of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  O God, my heart is steadfast [with confident faith];I will sing,
        I will sing praises, even with my soul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Awake, harp and lyre;I will awaken the dawn!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I will praise and give thanks to You, O Lord, among the people;And
        I will sing praises to You among the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For Your lovingkindness is great and higher than the heavens;Your
        truth reaches to the skies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Be exalted [in majesty], O God, above the heavens,And Your glory
        above all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'That Your beloved [ones] may be rescued,Save with Your right hand,
        and answer me!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "God has spoken in His holiness:\u201CI will rejoice, I will portion
        out Shechem [as I divide Canaan among My people],And measure out the Valley
        of Succoth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Gilead is Mine, Manasseh is Mine;Ephraim also is the helmet of My
        head [My stronghold, My defense];Judah is My scepter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Moab is My washbowl;Over Edom I will throw My shoe [to show Edom
        is Mine];Over Philistia I will shout [in triumph].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Who will bring me into the fortified city [of Petra]?Who will lead
        me to Edom?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Have You not rejected us, O God?And will You not go out, O God, with
        our armies?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Give us help against the adversary,For deliverance by man is in vain
        [a worthless hope].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  With God we will do valiantly,For it is He who will trample down
        our enemies.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 109Vengeance Invoked upon Adversaries.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 109Vengeance Invoked upon Adversaries.To the Chief Musician. A
        Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  O God of my praise!Do not keep silent,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the mouth of the wicked and the mouth of the deceitful are opened
        against me;They have spoken against me with a lying tongue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They have also surrounded me with words of hatred,And have fought
        against me without a cause.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'In return for my love, they attack me,But I am in prayer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They have repaid me evil for good,And hatred for my love.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Appoint a wicked man against him,And let an attacker stand at his
        right hand [to kill him].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When he enters into dispute, let wickedness come about.Let his prayer
        [for help] result [only] in sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Let his days be few;And let another take his office.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Let his children be fatherlessAnd his wife a widow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Let his children wander and beg;Let them seek their food and be driven
        far from their ruined homes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Let the creditor seize all that he has,And let strangers plunder
        the product of his labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Let there be no one to extend kindness to him,Nor let anyone be gracious
        to his fatherless children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Let his descendants be cut off,And in the following generation let
        their name be blotted out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Let the wickedness of his fathers be remembered by the Lord;And do
        not let the sin of his mother be blotted out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Let them be before the Lord continually,That He may cut off their
        memory from the earth;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Because the man did not remember to show kindness,But persecuted
        the suffering and needy man,And the brokenhearted, to put them to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He also loved cursing, and it came [back] to him;He did not delight
        in blessing, so it was far from him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He clothed himself with cursing as with his garment,And it seeped
        into his inner self like waterAnd like [anointing] oil into his bones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Let it be to him as a robe with which he covers himself,And as a
        sash with which he is constantly bound.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Let this be the reward of my attackers from the Lord,And of those
        who speak evil against my life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But You, O God, the Lord, show kindness to me, for Your name\u2019s
        sake;Because Your lovingkindness (faithfulness, compassion) is good, O rescue
        me;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For I am suffering and needy,And my heart is wounded within me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I am vanishing like a shadow when it lengthens and fades;I am shaken
        off like the locust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'My knees are unsteady from fasting;And my flesh is gaunt and without
        fatness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'I also have become a reproach and an object of taunting to others;When
        they see me, they shake their heads [in derision].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Help me, O Lord my God;Save me according to Your lovingkindness\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And let them know that this is Your hand;You, Lord, have done it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Let them curse, but You bless.When adversaries arise, let them be
        ashamed,But let Your servant rejoice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Let my attackers be clothed with dishonor,And let them cover themselves
        with their own shame as with a robe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'I will give great praise and thanks to the Lord with my mouth;And
        in the midst of many I will praise Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: For He will stand at the right hand of the needy,To save him from
        those who judge his soul.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 110The Lord Gives Dominion to the King.A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 110The Lord Gives Dominion to the King.A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: "  The Lord (Father) says to my Lord (the Messiah, His Son),\u201CSit
        at My right handUntil I make Your enemies a footstool for Your feet [subjugating
        them into complete submission].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Lord will send the scepter of Your strength from Zion, saying,\u201CRule
        in the midst of Your enemies.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Your people will offer themselves willingly [to participate in Your
        battle] in the day of Your power;In the splendor of holiness, from the womb
        of the dawn,Your young men are to You as the dew.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The Lord has sworn [an oath] and will not change His mind:\u201CYou
        are a priest foreverAccording to the order of Melchizedek.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord is at Your right hand,He will crush kings in the day of
        His wrath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He will execute judgment [in overwhelming punishment] among the nations;He
        will fill them with corpses,He will crush the chief men over a broad country.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He will drink from the brook by the wayside;Therefore He will lift
        up His head [triumphantly].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 111The Lord Praised for His Goodness.'
      title: PSALM 111The Lord Praised for His Goodness.
      number: 1
      content: '  Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)I will give thanks to the Lord with
        all my heart,In the company of the upright and in the congregation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Great are the works of the Lord,Studied by all those who delight
        in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Splendid and majestic is His work,And His righteousness endures forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He has made His wonderful acts to be remembered;The Lord is gracious
        and merciful and full of loving compassion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He has given food to those who fear Him [with awe-inspired reverence];He
        will remember His covenant forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He has declared and made known to His people the power of His works,In
        giving them the heritage of the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The works of His hands are truth and [absolute] justice;All His precepts
        are sure (established, reliable, trustworthy).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They are upheld forever and ever;They are done in [absolute] truth
        and uprightness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He has sent redemption to His people;He has ordained His covenant
        forever;Holy and awesome is His name\u2014[inspiring reverence and godly
        fear].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The [reverent] fear of the Lord is the beginning (the prerequisite,
        the absolute essential, the alphabet) of wisdom;A good understanding and
        a teachable heart are possessed by all those who do the will of the Lord;His
        praise endures forever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 112Prosperity of the One Who Fears the Lord.'
      title: PSALM 112Prosperity of the One Who Fears the Lord.
      number: 1
      content: '  Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)Blessed [fortunate, prosperous, and
        favored by God] is the man who fears the Lord [with awe-inspired reverence
        and worships Him with obedience],Who delights greatly in His commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'His descendants will be mighty on earth;The generation of the upright
        will be blessed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Wealth and riches are in his house,And his righteousness endures
        forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Light arises in the darkness for the upright;He is gracious and compassionate
        and righteous (upright\u2014in right standing with God).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'It is well with the man who is gracious and lends;He conducts his
        affairs with justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He will never be shaken;The righteous will be remembered forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He will not fear bad news;His heart is steadfast, trusting [confidently
        relying on and believing] in the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'His heart is upheld, he will not fearWhile he looks [with satisfaction]
        on his adversaries.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He has given freely to the poor;His righteousness endures forever;His
        horn will be exalted in honor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The wicked will see it and be angered,He will gnash his teeth and
        melt away [in despair and death];The desire of the wicked will perish and
        come to nothing.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 113The Lord Exalts the Humble.'
      title: PSALM 113The Lord Exalts the Humble.
      number: 1
      content: '    Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)Praise, O servants of the Lord,Praise
        the name of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Blessed be the name of the LordFrom this time forth and forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'From the rising of the sun to its settingThe name of the Lord is
        to be praised [with awe-inspired reverence].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Lord is high above all nations,And His glory above the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Who is like the Lord our God,Who is enthroned on high,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Who humbles Himself to regardThe heavens and the earth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He raises the poor out of the dustAnd lifts the needy from the ash
        heap,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'That He may seat them with princes,With the princes of His people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: He makes the barren woman live in the houseAs a joyful mother of children.Praise
        the Lord! (Hallelujah!)
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 114God\u2019s Rescue of Israel from Egypt."
      title: "PSALM 114God\u2019s Rescue of Israel from Egypt."
      number: 1
      content: '  When Israel came out of Egypt,The house of Jacob from a people
        of strange language,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Judah became His sanctuary,And Israel His dominion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The [Red] Sea looked and fled;The Jordan turned back.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The mountains leaped like rams,The [little] hills, like lambs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'What ails you, O sea, that you flee?O Jordan, that you turn back?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'O mountains, that you leap like rams,O [little] hills, like lambs?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Tremble, O earth, at the presence of the Lord,At the presence of
        the God of Jacob (Israel),  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Who turned the rock into a pool of water,The flint into a fountain
        of water.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 115Pagan Idols Contrasted with the Lord.'
      title: PSALM 115Pagan Idols Contrasted with the Lord.
      number: 1
      content: '  Not to us, O Lord, not to us,But to Your name give gloryBecause
        of Your lovingkindness, because of Your truth and faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Why should the nations say,\u201CWhere, now, is their God?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But our God is in heaven;He does whatever He pleases.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The idols [of the nations] are silver and gold,The work of man\u2019s
        hands.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They have mouths, but they cannot speak;They have eyes, but they
        cannot see;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They have ears, but they cannot hear;They have noses, but they cannot
        smell;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They have hands, but they cannot feel;They have feet, but they cannot
        walk;Nor can they make a sound with their throats.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Those who make them will become like them,Everyone who trusts in
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'O Israel, trust and take refuge in the Lord! [Be confident in Him,
        cling to Him, rely on His word!]He is their help and their shield.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'O house of Aaron, trust in the Lord;He is their help and their shield.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You who [reverently] fear the Lord, trust in the Lord;He is their
        help and their shield.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The Lord has been mindful of us; He will bless,He will bless the
        house of Israel;He will bless the house of Aaron.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He will bless those who fear and worship the Lord [with awe-inspired
        reverence and submissive wonder],Both the small and the great.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'May the Lord give you [great] increase,You and your children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'May you be blessed of the Lord,Who made heaven and earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The heavens are the heavens of the Lord,But the earth He has given
        to the children of men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The dead do not praise the Lord,Nor do any who go down into silence;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: But as for us, we will bless and affectionately and gratefully praise
        the LordFrom this time forth and forever.Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 116Thanksgiving for Rescue from Death.'
      title: PSALM 116Thanksgiving for Rescue from Death.
      number: 1
      content: '  I love the Lord, because He hears [and continues to hear]My voice
        and my supplications (my pleas, my cries, my specific needs).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Because He has inclined His ear to me,Therefore I will call on Him
        as long as I live.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The cords and sorrows of death encompassed me,And the terrors of
        Sheol came upon me;I found distress and sorrow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then I called on the name of the Lord:\u201CO Lord, please save my
        life!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Gracious is the Lord, and [consistently] righteous;Yes, our God is
        compassionate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The Lord protects the simple (childlike);I was brought low [humbled
        and discouraged], and He saved me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Return to your rest, O my soul,For the Lord has dealt bountifully
        with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For You have rescued my life from death,My eyes from tears,And my
        feet from stumbling and falling.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will walk [in submissive wonder] before the LordIn the land of
        the living.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I believed [and clung to my God] when I said,\u201CI am greatly afflicted.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "I said in my alarm,\u201CAll men are liars.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'What will I give to the Lord [in return]For all His benefits toward
        me?[How can I repay Him for His precious blessings?]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will lift up the cup of salvationAnd call on the name of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will pay my vows to the Lord,Yes, in the presence of all His people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Precious [and of great consequence] in the sight of the LordIs
        the death of His godly ones [so He watches over them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'O Lord, truly I am Your servant;I am Your servant, the son of Your
        handmaid;You have unfastened my chains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I will offer to You the sacrifice of thanksgiving,And will call on
        the name of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I will pay my vows to the Lord,Yes, in the presence of all His people,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "In the courts of the Lord\u2019s house (temple)\u2014In the midst
        of you, O Jerusalem.Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 117A Psalm of Praise.'
      title: PSALM 117A Psalm of Praise.
      number: 1
      content: '  O praise the Lord, all you nations!Praise Him, all you people!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For His lovingkindness prevails over us [and we triumph and overcome
        through Him],And the truth of the Lord endures forever.Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 118Thanksgiving for the Lord\u2019s Saving Goodness."
      title: "PSALM 118Thanksgiving for the Lord\u2019s Saving Goodness."
      number: 1
      content: '  O give thanks to the Lord, for He is good;For His lovingkindness
        endures forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Oh let Israel say,\u201CHis lovingkindness endures forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Oh let the house of Aaron say,\u201CHis lovingkindness endures forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Oh let those who [reverently] fear the Lord, say,\u201CHis lovingkindness
        endures forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Out of my distress I called on the Lord;The Lord answered me and
        set me free.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The Lord is on my side; I will not fear.What can [mere] man do to
        me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The Lord is on my side, He is among those who help me;Therefore I
        will look [in triumph] on those who hate me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'It is better to take refuge in the LordThan to trust in man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'It is better to take refuge in the LordThan to trust in princes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'All nations encompassed me;In the name of the Lord I will surely
        cut them off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They encompassed me, yes, they surrounded me [on every side];In the
        name of the Lord I will cut them off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They swarmed around me like bees;They flare up and are extinguished
        like a fire of thorns;In the name of the Lord I will surely cut them off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You [my enemy] pushed me violently so that I was falling,But the
        Lord helped me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The Lord is my strength and song,And He has become my salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sound of joyful shouting and salvation is in the tents of the
        righteous:The right hand of the Lord does valiantly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The right hand of the Lord is exalted;The right hand of the Lord
        does valiantly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I will not die, but live,And declare the works and recount the illustrious
        acts of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The Lord has disciplined me severely,But He has not given me over
        to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Open to me the [temple] gates of righteousness;I shall enter through
        them, I shall give thanks to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'This is the gate of the Lord;The righteous will enter through it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I will give thanks to You, for You have heard and answered me;And
        You have become my salvation [my Rescuer, my Savior].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The stone which the builders rejectedHas become the chief corner
        stone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'This is from the Lord  and is His doing;It is marvelous in our eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'This [day in which God has saved me] is the day which the Lord has
        made;Let us rejoice and be glad in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'O Lord, save now, we beseech You;O Lord, we beseech You, send now
        prosperity and give us success!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Blessed is the one who comes in the name of the Lord;We have blessed
        you from the house of the Lord [you who come into His sanctuary under His
        guardianship].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The Lord is God, and He has given us light [illuminating us with
        His grace and freedom and joy].Bind the festival sacrifices with cords to
        the horns of the altar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'You are my God, and I give thanks to You;[You are] my God, I extol
        You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: O give thanks to the Lord, for He is good;For His lovingkindness endures
        forever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 119Meditations and Prayers Relating to the Law of God.  This
        long Psalm (176 verses) consists of separate units, each of which has its
        first word beginning with a consecutive letter of the Hebrew alphabet as
        a memory aid. The first verse begins with the first letter of the alphabet,
        aleph (first letter of the word blessed), and the last unit of the Psalm
        (vv 169-176) begins with tav, the last letter of the Hebrew alphabet.Aleph.'
      title: PSALM 119Meditations and Prayers Relating to the Law of God.  This long
        Psalm (176 verses) consists of separate units, each of which has its first
        word beginning with a consecutive letter of the Hebrew alphabet as a memory
        aid. The first verse begins with the first letter of the alphabet, aleph
        (first letter of the word blessed), and the last unit of the Psalm (vv 169-176)
        begins with tav, the last letter of the Hebrew alphabet.Aleph.
      number: 1
      content: '  How blessed and favored by God are those whose way is blameless
        [those with personal integrity, the upright, the guileless],Who walk in the
        law [and who are guided by the precepts and revealed will] of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Blessed and favored by God are those who keep His testimonies,And
        who [consistently] seek Him and long for Him with all their heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They do no unrighteousness;They walk in His ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You have ordained Your precepts,That we should follow them with [careful]
        diligence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Oh, that my ways may be establishedTo observe and keep Your statutes
        [obediently accepting and honoring them]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then I will not be ashamedWhen I look [with respect] to all Your
        commandments [as my guide].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will give thanks to You with an upright heart,When I learn [through
        discipline] Your righteous judgments [for my transgressions].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Beth.'
      title: Beth.
      number: 8
      content: 'I shall keep Your statutes;Do not utterly abandon me [when I fail].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'How can a young man keep his way pure?By keeping watch [on himself]
        according to Your word [conforming his life to Your precepts].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'With all my heart I have sought You, [inquiring of You and longing
        for You];Do not let me wander from Your commandments [neither through ignorance
        nor by willful disobedience].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Your word I have treasured and stored in my heart,That I may not
        sin against You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Blessed and reverently praised are You, O Lord;Teach me Your statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'With my lips I have told ofAll the ordinances of Your mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I have rejoiced in the way of Your testimonies,As much as in all
        riches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I will meditate on Your preceptsAnd [thoughtfully] regard Your ways
        [the path of life established by Your precepts].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Gimel.'
      title: Gimel.
      number: 16
      content: 'I will delight in Your statutes;I will not forget Your word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Deal bountifully with Your servant,That I may live and keep Your
        word [treasuring it and being guided by it day by day].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Open my eyes [to spiritual truth] so that I may beholdWonderful things
        from Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I am a stranger on the earth;Do not hide Your commandments from me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My soul is crushed with longingFor Your ordinances at all times.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You rebuke the presumptuous and arrogant, the cursed ones,Who wander
        from Your commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Take reproach and contempt away from me,For I observe Your testimonies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Even though princes sit and talk to one another against me,Your servant
        meditates on Your statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Daleth.'
      title: Daleth.
      number: 24
      content: 'Your testimonies also are my delightAnd my counselors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'My earthly life clings to the dust;Revive and refresh me according
        to Your word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I have told of my ways, and You have answered me;Teach me Your statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Make me understand the way of Your precepts,So that I will meditate
        (focus my thoughts) on Your wonderful works.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'My soul dissolves because of grief;Renew and strengthen me according
        to [the promises of] Your word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Remove from me the way of falsehood and unfaithfulness,And graciously
        grant me Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'I have chosen the faithful way;I have placed Your ordinances before
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'I cling tightly to Your testimonies;O Lord, do not put me to shame!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: He.'
      title: He.
      number: 32
      content: 'I will run the way of Your commandments [with purpose],For You will
        give me a heart that is willing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Teach me, O Lord, the way of Your statutes,And I will [steadfastly]
        observe it to the end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Give me understanding [a teachable heart and the ability to learn],
        that I may keep Your law;And observe it with all my heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Make me walk in the path of Your commandments,For I delight in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Incline my heart to Your testimoniesAnd not to dishonest gain and
        envy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Turn my eyes away from vanity [all those worldly, meaningless things
        that distract\u2014let Your priorities be mine],And restore me [with renewed
        energy] in Your ways.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Establish Your word and confirm Your promise to Your servant,As that
        which produces [awe-inspired] reverence for You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Turn away my reproach which I dread,For Your ordinances are good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: Vav.'
      title: Vav.
      number: 40
      content: 'I long for Your precepts;Renew me through Your righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'May Your lovingkindness also come to me, O Lord,Your salvation according
        to Your promise;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'So I will have an answer for the one who taunts me,For I trust [completely]
        in Your word [and its reliability].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And do not take the word of truth utterly out of my mouth,For I wait
        for Your ordinances.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'I will keep Your law continually,Forever and ever [writing Your precepts
        on my heart].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And I will walk at liberty,For I seek and deeply long for Your precepts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'I will also speak of Your testimonies before kingsAnd shall not be
        ashamed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'For I shall delight in Your commandments,Which I love.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: Zayin.'
      title: Zayin.
      number: 48
      content: 'And I shall lift up my hands to Your commandments,Which I love;And
        I will meditate on Your statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Remember [always] the word and promise to Your servant,In which You
        have made me hope.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'This is my comfort in my affliction,That Your word has revived me
        and given me life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'The arrogant utterly ridicule me,Yet I do not turn away from Your
        law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'I have remembered [carefully] Your ancient ordinances, O Lord,And
        I have taken comfort.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Burning indignation has seized me because of the wicked,Who reject
        Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Your statutes are my songsIn the house of my pilgrimage.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'O Lord, I remember Your name in the night,And keep Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: Heth.'
      title: Heth.
      number: 56
      content: 'This has become mine [as the gift of Your grace],That I observe Your
        precepts [accepting them with loving obedience].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'The Lord is my portion;I have promised to keep Your words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'I sought Your favor with all my heart;Be merciful and gracious to
        me according to Your promise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'I considered my waysAnd turned my feet to [follow and obey] Your
        testimonies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'I hurried and did not delayTo keep Your commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'The cords of the wicked have encircled and ensnared me,But I have
        not forgotten Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'At midnight I will rise to give thanks to YouBecause of Your righteous
        ordinances.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'I am a companion of all who [reverently] fear You,And of those who
        keep and honor Your precepts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: Teth.'
      title: Teth.
      number: 64
      content: 'The earth, O Lord, is full of Your lovingkindness and goodness;Teach
        me Your statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'You have dealt well with Your servant,O Lord, according to Your promise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'Teach me good judgment (discernment) and knowledge,For I have believed
        and trusted and relied on Your commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: 'Before I was afflicted I went astray,But now I keep and honor Your
        word [with loving obedience].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: 'You are good and do good;Teach me Your statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: 'The arrogant have forged a lie against me,But I will keep Your precepts
        with all my heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: 'Their heart is insensitive like fat [their minds are dull and brutal],But
        I delight in Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: 'It is good for me that I have been afflicted,That I may learn Your
        statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '72: Yodh.'
      title: Yodh.
      number: 72
      content: 'The law from Your mouth is better to meThan thousands of gold and
        silver pieces.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '73: '
      title: 
      number: 73
      content: 'Your hands have made me and established me;Give me understanding
        and a teachable heart, that I may learn Your commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '74: '
      title: 
      number: 74
      content: 'May those who [reverently] fear You see me and be glad,Because I
        wait for Your word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '75: '
      title: 
      number: 75
      content: 'I know, O Lord, that Your judgments are fair,And that in faithfulness
        You have disciplined me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '76: '
      title: 
      number: 76
      content: 'O may Your lovingkindness and graciousness comfort me,According to
        Your word (promise) to Your servant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '77: '
      title: 
      number: 77
      content: 'Let Your compassion come to me that I may live,For Your law is my
        delight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '78: '
      title: 
      number: 78
      content: 'Let the arrogant be ashamed and humiliated, for they sabotage me
        with a lie;But I will meditate on Your precepts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '79: '
      title: 
      number: 79
      content: 'May those who fear You [with submissive wonder] turn to me,Even those
        who have known Your testimonies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '80: Kaph.'
      title: Kaph.
      number: 80
      content: 'May my heart be blameless in Your statutes,So that I will not be
        ashamed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '81: '
      title: 
      number: 81
      content: 'My soul languishes and grows weak for Your salvation;I wait for Your
        word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '82: '
      title: 
      number: 82
      content: "My eyes fail [with longing, watching] for [the fulfillment of] Your
        promise,Saying, \u201CWhen will You comfort me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '83: '
      title: 
      number: 83
      content: 'For I have become like a wineskin [blackened and shriveled] in the
        smoke [in which it hangs],Yet I do not forget Your statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '84: '
      title: 
      number: 84
      content: 'How many are the days of Your servant [which he must endure]?When
        will You execute judgment on those who persecute me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '85: '
      title: 
      number: 85
      content: 'The arrogant (godless) have dug pits for me,Men who do not conform
        to Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '86: '
      title: 
      number: 86
      content: 'All Your commandments are faithful and trustworthy.They have persecuted
        me with a lie; help me [Lord]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '87: '
      title: 
      number: 87
      content: 'They had almost destroyed me on earth,But as for me, I did not turn
        away from Your precepts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '88: Lamedh.'
      title: Lamedh.
      number: 88
      content: 'According to Your steadfast love refresh me and give me life,So that
        I may keep and obey the testimony of Your mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '89: '
      title: 
      number: 89
      content: 'Forever, O Lord,Your word is settled in heaven [standing firm and
        unchangeable].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '90: '
      title: 
      number: 90
      content: 'Your faithfulness continues from generation to generation;You have
        established the earth, and it stands [securely].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '91: '
      title: 
      number: 91
      content: 'They continue this day according to Your ordinances,For all things
        [all parts of the universe] are Your servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '92: '
      title: 
      number: 92
      content: 'If Your law had not been my delight,Then I would have perished in
        my time of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '93: '
      title: 
      number: 93
      content: 'I will never forget Your precepts,For by them You have revived me
        and given me life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '94: '
      title: 
      number: 94
      content: 'I am Yours, save me [as Your own];For I have [diligently] sought
        Your precepts and required them [as my greatest need].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '95: '
      title: 
      number: 95
      content: 'The wicked wait for me to destroy me,But I will consider Your testimonies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '96: Mem.'
      title: Mem.
      number: 96
      content: 'I have seen that all [human] perfection has its limits [no matter
        how grand and perfect and noble];Your commandment is exceedingly broad and
        extends without limits [into eternity].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '97: '
      title: 
      number: 97
      content: 'Oh, how I love Your law!It is my meditation all the day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '98: '
      title: 
      number: 98
      content: 'Your commandments make me wiser than my enemies,For Your words are
        always with me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '99: '
      title: 
      number: 99
      content: 'I have better understanding and deeper insight than all my teachers
        [because of Your word],For Your testimonies are my meditation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '100: '
      title: 
      number: 100
      content: 'I understand more than the aged [who have not observed Your precepts],Because
        I have observed and kept Your precepts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '101: '
      title: 
      number: 101
      content: 'I have restrained my feet from every evil way,That I may keep Your
        word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '102: '
      title: 
      number: 102
      content: 'I have not turned aside from Your ordinances,For You Yourself have
        taught me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '103: '
      title: 
      number: 103
      content: 'How sweet are Your words to my taste,  Sweeter than honey to my mouth!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '104: Nun.'
      title: Nun.
      number: 104
      content: 'From Your precepts I get understanding;Therefore I hate every false
        way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '105: '
      title: 
      number: 105
      content: 'Your word is a lamp to my feetAnd a light to my path.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '106: '
      title: 
      number: 106
      content: 'I have sworn [an oath] and have confirmed it,That I will keep Your
        righteous ordinances.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '107: '
      title: 
      number: 107
      content: 'I am greatly afflicted;Renew and revive me [giving me life], O Lord,
        according to Your word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '108: '
      title: 
      number: 108
      content: 'Accept and take pleasure in the freewill offerings of my mouth, O
        Lord,And teach me Your ordinances.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '109: '
      title: 
      number: 109
      content: 'My life is continually in my hand,Yet I do not forget Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '110: '
      title: 
      number: 110
      content: 'The wicked have laid a snare for me,Yet I do not wander from Your
        precepts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '111: '
      title: 
      number: 111
      content: 'I have taken Your testimonies as a heritage forever,For they are
        the joy of my heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '112: Samekh.'
      title: Samekh.
      number: 112
      content: 'I have inclined my heart to perform Your statutesForever, even to
        the end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '113: '
      title: 
      number: 113
      content: 'I hate those who are double-minded,But I love and treasure Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '114: '
      title: 
      number: 114
      content: 'You are my hiding place and my shield;I wait for Your word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '115: '
      title: 
      number: 115
      content: 'Leave me, you evildoers,That I may keep the commandments of my God
        [honoring and obeying them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '116: '
      title: 
      number: 116
      content: 'Uphold me according to Your word [of promise], so that I may live;And
        do not let me be ashamed of my hope [in Your great goodness].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '117: '
      title: 
      number: 117
      content: 'Uphold me that I may be safe,That I may have regard for Your statutes
        continually.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '118: '
      title: 
      number: 118
      content: 'You have turned Your back on all those who wander from Your statutes,For
        their deceitfulness is useless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '119: '
      title: 
      number: 119
      content: 'You have removed all the wicked of the earth like dross [for they
        have no value];Therefore I love Your testimonies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '120: Ayin.'
      title: Ayin.
      number: 120
      content: 'My flesh trembles in [reverent] fear of You,And I am afraid and in
        awe of Your judgments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '121: '
      title: 
      number: 121
      content: 'I have done justice and righteousness;Do not leave me to those who
        oppress me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '122: '
      title: 
      number: 122
      content: 'Be the guarantee for Your servant for good [as Judah was the guarantee
        for Benjamin];Do not let the arrogant oppress me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '123: '
      title: 
      number: 123
      content: 'My eyes fail [with longing, watching] for [the fulfillment of] Your
        salvation,And for [the fulfillment of] Your righteous word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '124: '
      title: 
      number: 124
      content: 'Deal with Your servant according to Your [gracious] lovingkindness,And
        teach me Your statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '125: '
      title: 
      number: 125
      content: 'I am Your servant; give me understanding [the ability to learn and
        a teachable heart]That I may know Your testimonies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '126: '
      title: 
      number: 126
      content: 'It is time for the Lord to act;They have broken Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '127: '
      title: 
      number: 127
      content: 'Therefore I love Your commandments more than gold,Yes, more than
        refined gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '128: Pe.'
      title: Pe.
      number: 128
      content: 'Therefore I esteem as right all Your precepts concerning everything;I
        hate every false way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '129: '
      title: 
      number: 129
      content: 'Your testimonies are wonderful;Therefore my soul keeps them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '130: '
      title: 
      number: 130
      content: 'The unfolding of Your [glorious] words give light;Their unfolding
        gives understanding to the simple (childlike).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '131: '
      title: 
      number: 131
      content: 'I opened my mouth and panted [with anticipation],Because I longed
        for Your commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '132: '
      title: 
      number: 132
      content: 'Turn to me and be gracious to me and show me favor,As is Your way
        to those who love Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '133: '
      title: 
      number: 133
      content: 'Establish my footsteps in [the way of] Your word;Do not let any human
        weakness have power over me [causing me to be separated from You].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '134: '
      title: 
      number: 134
      content: 'Redeem me from the oppression of man;That I may keep Your precepts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '135: '
      title: 
      number: 135
      content: 'Make Your face shine [with pleasure] upon Your servant,And teach
        me Your statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '136: Tsadhe.'
      title: Tsadhe.
      number: 136
      content: 'My eyes weep streams of waterBecause people do not keep Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '137: '
      title: 
      number: 137
      content: 'Righteous are You, O Lord,And upright are Your judgments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '138: '
      title: 
      number: 138
      content: 'You have commanded Your testimonies in righteousnessAnd in great
        faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '139: '
      title: 
      number: 139
      content: 'My zeal has [completely] consumed me,Because my enemies have forgotten
        Your words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '140: '
      title: 
      number: 140
      content: 'Your word is very pure (refined);Therefore Your servant loves it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '141: '
      title: 
      number: 141
      content: 'I am small and despised,But I do not forget Your precepts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '142: '
      title: 
      number: 142
      content: 'Your righteousness is an everlasting righteousness,And Your law is
        truth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '143: '
      title: 
      number: 143
      content: 'Trouble and anguish have found me,Yet Your commandments are my delight
        and my joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '144: Qoph.'
      title: Qoph.
      number: 144
      content: 'Your righteous testimonies are everlasting;Give me understanding
        [the ability to learn and a teachable heart] that I may live.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '145: '
      title: 
      number: 145
      content: 'I cried with all my heart; answer me, O Lord!I will observe Your
        statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '146: '
      title: 
      number: 146
      content: 'I cried to You; save meAnd I will keep Your testimonies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '147: '
      title: 
      number: 147
      content: 'I rise before dawn and cry [in prayer] for help;I wait for Your word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '148: '
      title: 
      number: 148
      content: 'My eyes anticipate the night watches and I awake before the call
        of the watchman,That I may meditate on Your word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '149: '
      title: 
      number: 149
      content: 'Hear my voice according to Your [steadfast] lovingkindness;O Lord,
        renew and refresh me according to Your ordinances.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '150: '
      title: 
      number: 150
      content: 'Those who follow after wickedness approach;They are far from Your
        law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '151: '
      title: 
      number: 151
      content: 'You are near, O Lord,And all Your commandments are truth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '152: Resh.'
      title: Resh.
      number: 152
      content: 'Of old I have known from Your testimoniesThat You have founded them
        forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '153: '
      title: 
      number: 153
      content: 'Look upon my agony and rescue me,For I do not forget Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '154: '
      title: 
      number: 154
      content: 'Plead my cause and redeem me;Revive me and give me life according
        to [the promise of] Your word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '155: '
      title: 
      number: 155
      content: 'Salvation is far from the wicked,For they do not seek Your statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '156: '
      title: 
      number: 156
      content: 'Great are Your tender mercies and steadfast love, O Lord;Revive me
        and give me life according to Your ordinances.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '157: '
      title: 
      number: 157
      content: 'Many are my persecutors and my adversaries,Yet I do not turn away
        from Your testimonies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '158: '
      title: 
      number: 158
      content: 'I see the treacherous and loathe them,Because they do not respect
        Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '159: '
      title: 
      number: 159
      content: 'Consider how I love Your precepts;Revive me and give me life, O Lord,
        according to Your lovingkindness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '160: Shin.'
      title: Shin.
      number: 160
      content: 'The sum of Your word is truth [the full meaning of all Your precepts],And
        every one of Your righteous ordinances endures forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '161: '
      title: 
      number: 161
      content: 'Princes persecute me without cause,But my heart stands in [reverent]
        awe of Your words [so I can expect You to help me].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '162: '
      title: 
      number: 162
      content: 'I rejoice at Your word,As one who finds great treasure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '163: '
      title: 
      number: 163
      content: 'I hate and detest falsehood,But I love Your law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '164: '
      title: 
      number: 164
      content: '  Seven times a day I praise You,Because of Your righteous ordinances.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '165: '
      title: 
      number: 165
      content: 'Those who love Your law have great peace;Nothing makes them stumble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '166: '
      title: 
      number: 166
      content: 'I hope and wait [with complete confidence] for Your salvation, O
        Lord,And I do Your commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '167: '
      title: 
      number: 167
      content: 'My soul keeps Your testimonies [hearing and accepting and obeying
        them];I love them greatly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '168: Tav.'
      title: Tav.
      number: 168
      content: 'I keep Your precepts and Your testimonies,For all my ways are [fully
        known] before You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '169: '
      title: 
      number: 169
      content: 'Let my [mournful] cry come before You, O Lord;Give me understanding
        [the ability to learn and a teachable heart] according to Your word [of promise].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '170: '
      title: 
      number: 170
      content: 'Let my supplication come before You;Deliver me according to Your
        word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '171: '
      title: 
      number: 171
      content: 'Let my lips speak praise [with thanksgiving],For You teach me Your
        statutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '172: '
      title: 
      number: 172
      content: 'Let my tongue sing [praise for the fulfillment] of Your word,For
        all Your commandments are righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '173: '
      title: 
      number: 173
      content: 'Let Your hand be ready to help me,For I have chosen Your precepts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '174: '
      title: 
      number: 174
      content: 'I long for Your salvation, O Lord,And Your law is my delight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '175: '
      title: 
      number: 175
      content: 'Let my soul live that it may praise You,And let Your ordinances help
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '176: '
      title: 
      number: 176
      content: I have gone astray like a lost sheep;Seek Your servant, for I do not
        forget Your commandments.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 120Prayer for Breaking Away from the Treacherous.A Song of
        It is possible that the fifteen psalms (chs 120-134) known as the \u201CSongs
        of Degrees or Ascents\u201D were sung by the caravans of pilgrims going up
        to attend the annual feasts at Jerusalem. But it is equally possible that
        the title has reference to some peculiarity in connection with the music
        or the manner of using it.Ascents."
      title: "PSALM 120Prayer for Breaking Away from the Treacherous.A Song of It
        is possible that the fifteen psalms (chs 120-134) known as the \u201CSongs
        of Degrees or Ascents\u201D were sung by the caravans of pilgrims going up
        to attend the annual feasts at Jerusalem. But it is equally possible that
        the title has reference to some peculiarity in connection with the music
        or the manner of using it.Ascents."
      number: 1
      content: '  In my trouble I cried to the Lord,And He answered me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Rescue my soul, O Lord, from lying lips,And from a deceitful tongue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "What shall be given to you, and what more shall be done to you,You
        deceitful tongue?\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Sharp arrows of the warrior,With the burning coals of the broom tree.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Woe to me, for I sojourn in Meshech,and I live among the tents of
        Kedar [among hostile people]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Too long my soul has had its dwellingWith those who hate peace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: I am for peace, but when I speak,They are for war.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 121The Lord the Keeper of Israel.A Song of See Psalm 120 title
        note.Ascents.'
      title: PSALM 121The Lord the Keeper of Israel.A Song of See Psalm 120 title
        note.Ascents.
      number: 1
      content: "  I will lift up my eyes to the hills [of Jerusalem]\u2014From where
        shall my help come?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'My help comes from the Lord,Who made heaven and earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He will not allow your foot to slip;He who keeps you will not slumber.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Behold, He who keeps IsraelWill neither slumber [briefly] nor sleep
        [soundly].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord is your keeper;The Lord is your shade on your right hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sun will not strike you by day,Nor the moon by night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The Lord will protect you from all evil;He will keep your life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The Lord will guard your going out and your coming in [everything
        that you do]From this time forth and forever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 122Prayer for the Peace of Jerusalem.A Song of See Psalm 120
        title note.Ascents. Of David.'
      title: PSALM 122Prayer for the Peace of Jerusalem.A Song of See Psalm 120 title
        note.Ascents. Of David.
      number: 1
      content: "  I was glad when they said to me,\u201CLet us go to the house of
        the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Our feet are standingWithin your gates, O Jerusalem,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Jerusalem, that is builtAs a city that is firmly joined together;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'To which the [twelve] tribes go up, even the tribes of the Lord,[As
        was decreed as] an ordinance for Israel,To give thanks to the name of the
        Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For there the thrones of judgment were set,The thrones of the house
        of David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Pray for the peace of Jerusalem:\u201CMay they prosper who love you
        [holy city].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "May peace be within your wallsAnd prosperity within your palaces.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For the sake of my brothers and my friends,I will now say, \u201CMay
        peace be within you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For the sake of the house of the Lord our God [which is Jerusalem],I
        will seek your (the city\u2019s) good."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 123Prayer for the Lord\u2019s Help.A Song of See Psalm 120
        title note.Ascents."
      title: "PSALM 123Prayer for the Lord\u2019s Help.A Song of See Psalm 120 title
        note.Ascents."
      number: 1
      content: '  Unto you I lift up my eyes,O You who are enthroned in the heavens!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Behold, as the eyes of servants look to the hand of their master,And
        as the eyes of a maid to the hand of her mistress,So our eyes look to the
        Lord our God,Until He is gracious and favorable toward us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Be gracious to us, O Lord, be gracious and favorable toward us,For
        we are greatly filled with contempt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Our soul is greatly filledWith the scoffing of those who are at ease,And
        with the contempt of the proud [who disregard God\u2019s law]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 124Praise for Rescue from Enemies.A Song of See Psalm 120 title
        note.Ascents. Of David.'
      title: PSALM 124Praise for Rescue from Enemies.A Song of See Psalm 120 title
        note.Ascents. Of David.
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIf it had not been the Lord who was on our side,\u201DLet
        Israel now say,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CIf it had not been the Lord who was on our sideWhen men rose
        up against us,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then they would have [quickly] swallowed us alive,When their wrath
        was kindled against us;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the waters would have engulfed us,The torrent would have swept
        over our soul;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the raging waters would have swept over our soul.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Blessed be the Lord,Who has not given us as prey to be torn by their
        teeth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'We have escaped like a bird from the snare of the fowlers;The trap
        is broken and we have escaped.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Our help is in the name of the Lord,Who made heaven and earth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 125The Lord Surrounds His People.A Song of See Psalm 120 title
        note.Ascents.'
      title: PSALM 125The Lord Surrounds His People.A Song of See Psalm 120 title
        note.Ascents.
      number: 1
      content: '  Those who trust in and rely on the Lord [with confident expectation]Are
        like Mount Zion, which cannot be moved but remains forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'As the mountains surround Jerusalem,So the Lord surrounds His peopleFrom
        this time forth and forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For the scepter of wickedness shall not rest on the land of the righteous,So
        that the righteous will not reach out their hands to do wrong.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Do good, O Lord, to those who are goodAnd to those who are upright
        in their hearts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But as for those who turn aside to their crooked ways [in unresponsiveness
        to God],The Lord will lead them away with those who do evil.Peace be upon
        Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 126Thanksgiving for Return from Captivity.A Song of See Psalm
        120 title note.Ascents.'
      title: PSALM 126Thanksgiving for Return from Captivity.A Song of See Psalm
        120 title note.Ascents.
      number: 1
      content: '  When the Lord brought back the captives to Zion (Jerusalem),We
        were like those who dream [it seemed so unreal].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then our mouth was filled with laughterAnd our tongue with joyful
        shouting;Then they said among the nations,\u201CThe Lord has done great things
        for them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Lord has done great things for us;We are glad!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Restore our captivity, O Lord,As the stream-beds in the South (the
        Negev) [are restored by torrents of rain].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They who sow in tears shall reap with joyful singing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He who goes back and forth weeping, carrying his bag of seed [for
        planting],Will indeed come again with a shout of joy, bringing his sheaves
        with him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 127Prosperity Comes from the Lord.A Song of See Psalm 120 title
        note.Ascents. Of Solomon.'
      title: PSALM 127Prosperity Comes from the Lord.A Song of See Psalm 120 title
        note.Ascents. Of Solomon.
      number: 1
      content: '  Unless the Lord builds the house,They labor in vain who build it;Unless
        the Lord guards the city,The watchman keeps awake in vain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "It is vain for you to rise early,To retire late,To eat the bread
        of anxious labors\u2014For He gives [blessings] to His beloved even in his
        sleep.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Behold, children are a heritage and gift from the Lord,The fruit
        of the womb a reward.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Like arrows in the hand of a warrior,So are the children of one\u2019s
        youth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: How blessed [happy and fortunate] is the man whose quiver is filled
        with them;They will not be ashamedWhen they speak with their enemies [in
        gatherings] at the [city] gate.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 128Blessedness of the Fear of the Lord.A Song of See Psalm
        120 title note.Ascents.'
      title: PSALM 128Blessedness of the Fear of the Lord.A Song of See Psalm 120
        title note.Ascents.
      number: 1
      content: "  Blessed [happy and sheltered by God\u2019s favor] is everyone who
        fears the Lord [and worships Him with obedience],Who walks in His ways and
        lives according to His commandments.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For you shall eat the fruit of [the labor of] your hands,You will
        be happy and blessed and it will be well with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Your wife shall be like a fruitful vineWithin the innermost part
        of your house;Your children will be like olive plantsAround your table.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Behold, for so shall the man be blessed and divinely favoredWho fears
        the Lord [and worships Him with obedience].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'May the Lord bless you from Zion [His holy mountain],And may you
        see the prosperity of Jerusalem all the days of your life;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Indeed, may you see your [family perpetuated in your] children\u2019s
        children.Peace be upon Israel!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 129Prayer for the Overthrow of Zion\u2019s Enemies.A Song of
        See Psalm 120 title note.Ascents."
      title: "PSALM 129Prayer for the Overthrow of Zion\u2019s Enemies.A Song of
        See Psalm 120 title note.Ascents."
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CMany times they have persecuted me (Israel) from my youth,\u201DLet
        Israel now say,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CMany times they have persecuted me from my youth,Yet they have
        not prevailed against me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The [enemies, like] plowers plowed on my back;They made their furrows
        [of suffering] long [in Israel].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Lord is righteous;He has cut in two the [thick] cords of the
        wicked [which enslaved the people of Israel].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'May all who hate ZionBe put to shame and turned backward [in defeat].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Let them be like the grass on the housetops,Which withers before
        it grows up,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'With which the reaper does not fill his hand,Nor the binder of sheaves
        his arms,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Nor do those who pass by say,\u201CThe blessing of the Lord be upon
        you;We bless you in the name of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 130Hope in the Lord\u2019s Forgiving Love.A Song of See Psalm
        120 title note.Ascents."
      title: "PSALM 130Hope in the Lord\u2019s Forgiving Love.A Song of See Psalm
        120 title note.Ascents."
      number: 1
      content: '  Out of the depths [of distress] I have cried to You, O Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Lord, hear my voice!Let Your ears be attentiveTo the voice of my
        supplications.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'If You, Lord, should keep an account of our sins and treat us accordingly,O
        Lord, who could stand [before you in judgment and claim innocence]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But there is forgiveness with You,That You may be feared and worshiped
        [with submissive wonder].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I wait [patiently] for the Lord, my soul [expectantly] waits,And
        in His word do I hope.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'My soul waits for the LordMore than the watchmen for the morning;More
        than the watchmen for the morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'O Israel, hope in the Lord;For with the Lord there is lovingkindness,And
        with Him is abundant redemption.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And He will redeem IsraelFrom all his sins.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 131Childlike Trust in the Lord.A Song of See Psalm 120 title
        note.Ascents. Of David.'
      title: PSALM 131Childlike Trust in the Lord.A Song of See Psalm 120 title note.Ascents.
        Of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Lord, my heart is not proud, nor my eyes haughty;Nor do I involve
        myself in great matters,Or in things too difficult for me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Surely I have calmed and quieted my soul;Like a weaned child [resting]
        with his mother,My soul is like a weaned child within me [composed and freed
        from discontent].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: O Israel, hope in the LordFrom this time forth and forever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 132Prayer for the Lord\u2019s Blessing Upon the Sanctuary.A
        Song of See Psalm 120 title note.Ascents."
      title: "PSALM 132Prayer for the Lord\u2019s Blessing Upon the Sanctuary.A Song
        of See Psalm 120 title note.Ascents."
      number: 1
      content: "  O Lord, remember on David\u2019s behalfAll his hardship and affliction;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'How he swore to the LordAnd vowed to the Mighty One of Jacob:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI absolutely will not enter my house,Nor get into my bed\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I certainly will not permit my eyes to sleepNor my eyelids to slumber,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Until I find a place for the Lord,A dwelling place for the Mighty
        One of Jacob (Israel).\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Behold, we heard of it at Ephrathah;We found it in the field of Jaar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Let us go into His tabernacle;Let us worship at His footstool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Arise, O Lord, to Your resting place,You and the ark [the symbol]
        of Your strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Let Your priests be clothed with righteousness (right living),And
        let Your godly ones shout for joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the sake of Your servant David,Do not turn away the face of Your
        anointed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The Lord swore to DavidA truth from which He will not turn back:\u201COne
        of your descendants I will set upon your throne.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "If your children will keep My covenantAnd My testimony which I will
        teach them,Their children also shall sit upon your throne forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For the Lord has chosen Zion;He has desired it for His dwelling place:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThis is My resting place forever\u201D [says the Lord];\u201CHere
        will I dwell, for I have desired it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I will abundantly bless her provisions;I will satisfy her poor with
        bread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Her priests also I will clothe with salvation,And her godly ones
        will shout aloud for joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'There I will make the horn (strength) of David grow;I have prepared
        a lamp for My anointed [fulfilling the promises].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "His enemies I will clothe with shame,But upon himself shall his crown
        shine.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 133The Excellency of Brotherly Unity.A Song of See Psalm 120
        title note.Ascents. Of David.'
      title: PSALM 133The Excellency of Brotherly Unity.A Song of See Psalm 120 title
        note.Ascents. Of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Behold, how good and how pleasant it isFor brothers to dwell together
        in unity!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It is like the precious oil [of consecration] poured on the head,Coming
        down on the beard,Even the beard of Aaron,Coming down upon the edge of his
        [priestly] robes [consecrating the whole body].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It is like the dew of [Mount] HermonComing down on the hills of Zion;For
        there the Lord has commanded the blessing: life forevermore.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 134Greetings of Night Watchers.A Song of See Psalm 120 title
        note.Ascents.'
      title: PSALM 134Greetings of Night Watchers.A Song of See Psalm 120 title note.Ascents.
      number: 1
      content: '  Behold, bless and praise the Lord, all servants of the Lord (priests,
        Levites),Who stand and serve by night in the house of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Lift up your hands to the sanctuaryAnd bless the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: May the Lord bless you from Zion,He who made heaven and earth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 135Praise the Lord\u2019s Wonderful Works. Vanity of Idols."
      title: "PSALM 135Praise the Lord\u2019s Wonderful Works. Vanity of Idols."
      number: 1
      content: '  Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)Praise the name of the Lord;Praise
        Him, O servants of the Lord (priests, Levites),  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You who stand in the house of the Lord,In the courts of the house
        of our God,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Praise the Lord, for the Lord is good;Sing praises to His name, for
        it is gracious and lovely.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the Lord has chosen [the descendants of] Jacob for Himself,Israel
        for His own special treasure and possession.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For I know that the Lord is greatAnd that our Lord is above all gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Whatever the Lord pleases, He does,In the heavens and on the earth,
        in the seas and all deeps\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Who causes the clouds to rise from the ends of the earth;Who makes
        lightning for the rain,Who brings the wind from His storehouses;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who struck the firstborn of Egypt,Both of man and animal;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Who sent signs and wonders into your midst, O Egypt,Upon Pharaoh
        and all his servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Who struck many nationsAnd killed mighty kings,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Sihon, king of the Amorites,Og, king of Bashan,And all the kingdoms
        of Canaan;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And He gave their land as a heritage,A heritage to Israel His people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Your name, O Lord, endures forever,Your fame and remembrance, O Lord,
        [endures] throughout all generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For the Lord will judge His peopleAnd He will have compassion on
        His servants [revealing His mercy].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The idols of the nations are silver and gold,The work of men\u2019s
        hands.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They have mouths, but they do not speak;They have eyes, but they
        do not see;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They have ears, but they do not hear,Nor is there any breath in their
        mouths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Those who make idols are like them [absolutely worthless\u2014spiritually
        blind, deaf, and powerless];So is everyone who trusts in and relies on them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'O house of Israel, bless and praise the Lord [with gratitude];O house
        of Aaron, bless the Lord;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'O house of Levi, bless the Lord;You who fear the Lord [and worship
        Him with obedience], bless the Lord [with grateful praise]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Blessed be the Lord from Zion,Who dwells [with us] at Jerusalem.Praise
        the Lord! (Hallelujah!)
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 136Thanks for the Lord\u2019s Goodness to Israel."
      title: "PSALM 136Thanks for the Lord\u2019s Goodness to Israel."
      number: 1
      content: '    Give thanks to the Lord, for He is good;For His lovingkindness
        (graciousness, mercy, compassion) endures forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Give thanks to the God of gods,For His lovingkindness endures forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Give thanks to the Lord of lords,For His lovingkindness endures forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'To Him who alone does great wonders,For His lovingkindness endures
        forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'To Him who made the heavens with skill,For His lovingkindness endures
        forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'To Him who stretched out the earth upon the waters,For His lovingkindness
        endures forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'To Him who made the great lights,For His lovingkindness endures forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The sun to rule over the day,For His lovingkindness endures forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The moon and stars to rule by night,For His lovingkindness endures
        forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'To Him who struck the firstborn of Egypt,For His lovingkindness endures
        forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And brought Israel out from among them,For His lovingkindness endures
        forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'With a strong hand and with an outstretched arm,For His lovingkindness
        endures forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'To Him who divided the Red Sea into parts,For His lovingkindness
        endures forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And made Israel pass through the midst of it,For His lovingkindness
        endures forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But tossed Pharaoh and his army into the Red Sea,For His lovingkindness
        endures forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'To Him who led His people through the wilderness,For His lovingkindness
        endures forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'To Him who struck down great kings,For His lovingkindness endures
        forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And killed mighty kings,For His lovingkindness endures forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Sihon, king of the Amorites,For His lovingkindness endures forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Og, king of Bashan,For His lovingkindness endures forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And gave their land as a heritage,For His lovingkindness endures
        forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Even a heritage to Israel His servant,For His lovingkindness endures
        forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Who [faithfully] remembered us in our lowly condition,For His lovingkindness
        endures forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And has rescued us from our enemies,For His lovingkindness endures
        forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Who gives food to all flesh,For His lovingkindness endures forever;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Give thanks to the God of heaven,For His lovingkindness (graciousness,
        mercy, compassion) endures forever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 137An Experience of the Captivity.'
      title: PSALM 137An Experience of the Captivity.
      number: 1
      content: '  By the rivers of Babylon,There we [captives] sat down and wept,When
        we remembered Zion [the city God imprinted on our hearts].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'On the willow trees in the midst of BabylonWe hung our harps.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For there they who took us captive demanded of us a song with words,And
        our tormentors [who made a mockery of us demanded] amusement, saying,\u201CSing
        us one of the songs of Zion.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "How can we sing the Lord\u2019s songIn a strange and foreign land?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If I forget you, O Jerusalem,Let my right hand forget [her skill
        with the harp].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Let my tongue cling to the roof of my mouthIf I do not remember you,If
        I do not prefer JerusalemAbove my chief joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Remember, O Lord, against the sons of Edom,The day of [the fall of]
        Jerusalem,Who said \u201CDown, down [with her]To her very foundation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O daughter of Babylon, you devastator,How blessed will be the oneWho
        repays you [with destruction] as you have repaid us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: How blessed will be the one who seizes and dashes your little onesAgainst
        the rock.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 138Thanksgiving for the Lord\u2019s Favor.  A Psalm of David."
      title: "PSALM 138Thanksgiving for the Lord\u2019s Favor.  A Psalm of David."
      number: 1
      content: '  I will give You thanks with all my heart;I sing praises to You
        before the [pagan] gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will bow down [in worship] toward Your holy templeAnd give thanks
        to Your name for Your lovingkindness and Your truth;For You have magnified
        Your word together with Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'On the day I called, You answered me;And You made me bold and confident
        with [renewed] strength in my life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'All the kings of the land will give thanks and praise You, O Lord,When
        they have heard of the promises of Your mouth [which were fulfilled].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Yes, they will sing of the ways of the Lord [joyfully celebrating
        His wonderful acts],For great is the glory and majesty of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Though the Lord is exalted,He regards the lowly [and invites them
        into His fellowship];But the proud and haughty He knows from a distance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Though I walk in the midst of trouble, You will revive me;You will
        stretch out Your hand against the wrath of my enemies,And Your right hand
        will save me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Lord will accomplish that which concerns me;Your [unwavering]
        lovingkindness, O Lord, endures forever\u2014Do not abandon the works of
        Your own hands."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 139God\u2019s Omnipresence and Omniscience.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David."
      title: "PSALM 139God\u2019s Omnipresence and Omniscience.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David."
      number: 1
      content: '  O Lord, you have searched me [thoroughly] and have known me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You know when I sit down and when I rise up [my entire life, everything
        I do];You understand my thought from afar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You scrutinize my path and my lying down,And You are intimately acquainted
        with all my ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Even before there is a word on my tongue [still unspoken],Behold,
        O Lord, You know it all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You have enclosed me behind and before,And [You have] placed Your
        hand upon me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Such [infinite] knowledge is too wonderful for me;It is too high
        [above me], I cannot reach it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Where can I go from Your Spirit?Or where can I flee from Your presence?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'If I ascend to heaven, You are there;If I make my bed in Sheol (the
        nether world, the place of the dead), behold, You are there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'If I take the wings of the dawn,If I dwell in the remotest part of
        the sea,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Even there Your hand will lead me,And Your right hand will take hold
        of me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "If I say, \u201CSurely the darkness will cover me,And the night will
        be the only light around me,\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Even the darkness is not dark to You and conceals nothing from You,But
        the night shines as bright as the day;Darkness and light are alike to You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For You formed my innermost parts;You knit me [together] in my mother\u2019s
        womb.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will give thanks and praise to You, for I am fearfully and wonderfully
        made;Wonderful are Your works,And my soul knows it very well.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'My frame was not hidden from You,When I was being formed in secret,And
        intricately and skillfully formed [as if embroidered with many colors] in
        the depths of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Your eyes have seen my unformed substance;And in Your book were all
        writtenThe days that were appointed for me,When as yet there was not one
        of them [even taking shape].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'How precious also are Your thoughts to me, O God!How vast is the
        sum of them!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'If I could count them, they would outnumber the sand.When I awake,
        I am still with You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  O that You would kill the wicked, O God;Go away from me, therefore,
        men of bloodshed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For they speak against You wickedly,Your enemies take Your name in
        vain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Do I not hate those who hate You, O Lord?And do I not loathe those
        who rise up against You?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'I hate them with perfect and utmost hatred;They have become my enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Search me [thoroughly], O God, and know my heart;Test me and know
        my anxious thoughts;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And see if there is any wicked or hurtful way in me,And lead me in
        the everlasting way.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 140Prayer for Protection against the Wicked.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 140Prayer for Protection against the Wicked.To the Chief Musician.
        A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Rescue me, O Lord, from evil men;Protect me from violent men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They devise evil things in their hearts;They continually [gather
        together and] stir up wars.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They sharpen their tongues like a serpent\u2019s;Poison of a viper
        is under their lips. Selah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Keep me, O Lord, from the hands of the wicked;Protect me from violent
        menWho intend to trip up my steps.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The proud have hidden a trap for me, and cords;They have spread a
        net by the wayside;They have set traps for me. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I said to the Lord, \u201CYou are my God;Listen to the voice of my
        supplications, O Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'O God the Lord, the strength of my salvation,You have covered my
        head in the day of battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Do not grant, O Lord, the desires of the wicked;Do not further their
        evil device, that they not be exalted. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThose who surround me raise their heads;May the mischief of
        their own lips come upon them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Let burning coals fall upon them;Let them be thrown into the fire,Into
        deep [water] pits from which they cannot rise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Do not let a slanderer be established in the earth;Let evil quickly
        hunt the violent man [to overthrow him and stop his evil acts].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I know [with confidence] that the Lord will maintain the cause of
        the afflicted,And [will secure] justice for the poor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Surely the righteous will give thanks to Your name;The upright will
        dwell in Your presence.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 141An Evening Prayer for Sanctification and Protection.A Psalm
        of David.'
      title: PSALM 141An Evening Prayer for Sanctification and Protection.A Psalm
        of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Lord, I call upon You; hurry to me.Listen to my voice when I call
        to You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Let my prayer be counted as incense before You;The lifting up of
        my hands as the evening offering.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Set a guard, O Lord, over my mouth;Keep watch over the door of my
        lips [to keep me from speaking thoughtlessly].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Do not incline my heart to [consent to or tolerate] any evil thing,Or
        to practice deeds of wickednessWith men who plan and do evil;And let me not
        eat of their delicacies (be tempted by their gain).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Let the righteous [thoughtfully] strike (correct) me\u2014it is a
        kindness [done to encourage my spiritual maturity].It is [the choicest anointing]
        oil on the head;Let my head not refuse [to accept and acknowledge and learn
        from] it;For still my prayer is against their wicked deeds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Their [wicked, godless] judges are thrown down the sides of the rocky
        cliff,And they [who followed them] will hear my words, for they are pleasant
        (just).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'As when the one plows and breaks open the ground [and the soil scatters
        behind him],Our bones have been scattered at the mouth of Sheol [by the injustices
        of the wicked].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For my eyes are toward You, O God, the Lord;In You I take refuge;
        do not pour out my life nor leave me defenseless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Keep me from the jaws of the trap which they have set for me,And
        from the snares of those who do evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Let the wicked fall into their own nets,While I pass by and safely
        escape [from danger].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 142Prayer for Help in Trouble.A skillful song, or a didactic
        or reflective poem, of David; when he was in the cave. A Prayer.'
      title: PSALM 142Prayer for Help in Trouble.A skillful song, or a didactic or
        reflective poem, of David; when he was in the cave. A Prayer.
      number: 1
      content: '  I cry aloud with my voice to the Lord;I make supplication with
        my voice to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I pour out my complaint before Him;I declare my trouble before Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When my spirit was overwhelmed and weak within me [wrapped in darkness],You
        knew my path.In the way where I walkThey have hidden a trap for me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Look to the right [the point of attack] and see;For there is no one
        who has regard for me [to act in my favor].Escape has failed me and I have
        nowhere to run;No one cares about my life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I cried out to You, O Lord;I said, \u201CYou are my refuge,My portion
        in the land of the living.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Give attention to my cry,For I am brought very low;Rescue me from
        my persecutors,For they are stronger than I.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Bring my soul out of prison (adversity),So that I may give thanks
        and praise Your name;The righteous will surround me [in triumph],For You
        will look after me.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 143Prayer for Help and Guidance.A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 143Prayer for Help and Guidance.A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear my prayer, O Lord,Listen to my supplications!Answer me in
        Your faithfulness, and in Your righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And do not enter into judgment with Your servant,For in Your sight
        no man living is righteous or justified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For the enemy has persecuted me,He has crushed my life down to the
        ground;He has made me dwell in dark places, like those who have been long
        dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Therefore my spirit is overwhelmed and weak within me [wrapped in
        darkness];My heart grows numb within me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I remember the days of old;I meditate on all that You have done;I
        ponder the work of Your hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I reach out my hands to You;My throat thirsts for You, as a parched
        land [thirsts for water]. Selah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Answer me quickly, O Lord, my spirit fails;Do not hide Your face
        from me,Or I will become like those who go down into the pit (grave).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Let me hear Your lovingkindness in the morning,For I trust in You.Teach
        me the way in which I should walk,For I lift up my soul to You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Rescue me, O Lord, from my enemies;I take refuge in You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Teach me to do Your will [so that I may please You],For You are my
        God;Let Your good Spirit lead me on level ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Save my life, O Lord, for Your name\u2019s sake;In Your righteousness
        bring my life out of trouble.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: In your lovingkindness, silence and destroy my enemiesAnd destroy
        all those who afflict my life,For I am Your servant.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 144Prayer for Rescue and Prosperity.  A Psalm of David.'
      title: PSALM 144Prayer for Rescue and Prosperity.  A Psalm of David.
      number: 1
      content: '  Blessed be the Lord, my Rock and my great strength,Who trains my
        hands for warAnd my fingers for battle;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'My [steadfast] lovingkindness and my fortress,My high tower and my
        rescuer,My shield and He in whom I take refuge,Who subdues my people under
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Lord, what is man that You take notice of him?Or the son of man that
        You think of him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Man is like a mere breath;His days are like a shadow that passes
        away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Bow Your heavens, O Lord, and come down;Touch the mountains, and
        they will smoke.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Flash lightning and scatter my enemies;Send out Your arrows and confuse
        and embarrass and frustrate them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Stretch out Your hand from above;Set me free and rescue me from great
        waters,Out of the hands of [hostile] foreigners [who surround us]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Whose mouths speak deceit [without restraint],And whose right hand
        is a right hand of falsehood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will sing a new song to You, O God;Upon a harp of ten strings I
        will sing praises to You,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Who gives salvation to kings,Who sets David His servant free from
        the evil sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Set me free and rescue me from the hand of [hostile] foreigners,Whose
        mouth speaks deceit [without restraint],And whose right hand is a right hand
        of falsehood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Let our sons in their youth be like plants full grown,And our daughters
        like corner pillars fashioned for a palace;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Let our barns be full, supplying every kind of produce,And our flocks
        bring forth thousands and ten thousands in our fields;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Let our cattle bearWithout mishap and without loss,And let there
        be no outcry in our streets!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: How blessed and favored are the people in such circumstance;How blessed
        [fortunate, prosperous, and favored] are the people whose God is the Lord!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 145The Lord Extolled for His Goodness.  A Psalm of praise.
        Of David.'
      title: PSALM 145The Lord Extolled for His Goodness.  A Psalm of praise. Of
        David.
      number: 1
      content: '  I will exalt You, my God, O King,And [with gratitude and submissive
        wonder] I will bless Your name forever and ever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Every day I will bless You and lovingly praise You;Yes, [with awe-inspired
        reverence] I will praise Your name forever and ever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Great is the Lord, and highly to be praised,And His greatness is
        [so vast and profound as to be] unsearchable [incomprehensible to man].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'One generation shall praise Your works to another,And shall declare
        Your mighty and remarkable acts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'On the glorious splendor of Your majestyAnd on Your wonderful works,
        I will meditate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'People will speak of the power of Your awesome acts,And [with gratitude
        and submissive wonder] I will tell of Your greatness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They will overflow [like a fountain] when they speak of Your great
        and abundant goodnessAnd will sing joyfully of Your righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord is gracious and full of compassion,Slow to anger and abounding
        in lovingkindness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Lord is good to all,And His tender mercies are over all His works
        [the entirety of things created].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'All Your works shall give thanks to You and praise You, O Lord,And
        Your godly ones will bless You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They shall speak of the glory of Your kingdomAnd talk of Your power,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'To make known to the sons of men Your mighty actsAnd the glorious
        majesty of Your kingdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Your kingdom is an everlasting kingdom,And Your dominion endures
        throughout all generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The Lord upholds all those [of His own] who fallAnd raises up all
        those who are bowed down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The eyes of all look to You [in hopeful expectation],And You give
        them their food in due time.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'You open Your handAnd satisfy the desire of every living thing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The Lord is [unwaveringly] righteous in all His waysAnd gracious
        and kind in all His works.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The Lord is near to all who call on Him,To all who call on Him in
        truth (without guile).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He will fulfill the desire of those who fear and worship Him [with
        awe-inspired reverence and obedience];He also will hear their cry and will
        save them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The Lord keeps all who love Him,But all the wicked He will destroy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: My mouth will speak the praise of the Lord,And all flesh will bless
        and gratefully praise His holy name forever and ever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 146The Lord an Abundant Helper.'
      title: PSALM 146The Lord an Abundant Helper.
      number: 1
      content: '  Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)Praise the Lord, O my soul!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'While I live I will praise the Lord;I will sing praises to my God
        as long as I live.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Do not trust in princes,In mortal man, in whom there is no salvation
        (help).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When his spirit leaves him, he returns to the earth;In that very
        day his thoughts and plans perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'How blessed and graciously favored is he whose help is the God of
        Jacob (Israel),Whose hope is in the Lord his God,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Who made heaven and earth,The sea, and all that is in them,Who keeps
        truth and is faithful forever,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Who executes justice for the oppressed,Who gives food to the hungry.The
        Lord sets free the prisoners.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord opens the eyes of the blind;The Lord lifts up those who
        are bowed down;The Lord loves the righteous [the upright in heart].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Lord protects the strangers;He supports the fatherless and the
        widow;But He makes crooked the way of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The Lord shall reign forever,Your God, O Zion, to all generations.Praise
        the Lord! (Hallelujah!)
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: PSALM 147Praise for Jerusalem\u2019s Restoration and Prosperity."
      title: "PSALM 147Praise for Jerusalem\u2019s Restoration and Prosperity."
      number: 1
      content: '  Praise the Lord!For it is good to sing praises to our [gracious
        and majestic] God;Praise is becoming and appropriate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord is building up Jerusalem;He is gathering [together] the
        exiles of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He heals the brokenheartedAnd binds up their wounds [healing their
        pain and comforting their sorrow].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He counts the number of the stars;He calls them all by their names.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Great is our [majestic and mighty] Lord and abundant in strength;His
        understanding is inexhaustible [infinite, boundless].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The Lord lifts up the humble;He casts the wicked down to the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Sing to the Lord with thanksgiving;Sing praises to our God with the
        lyre,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who covers the heavens with clouds,Who provides rain for the earth,Who
        makes grass grow on the mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He gives to the beast its food,And to the young ravens that for which
        they cry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He does not delight in the strength (military power) of the horse,Nor
        does He take pleasure in the legs (strength) of a man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The Lord favors those who fear and worship Him [with awe-inspired
        reverence and obedience],Those who wait for His mercy and lovingkindness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Praise the Lord, O Jerusalem!Praise your God, O Zion!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For He has strengthened the bars of your gates,He has blessed your
        children within you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He makes peace in your borders;He satisfies you with the finest of
        the wheat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He sends His command to the earth;His word runs very swiftly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He gives [to the earth] snow like [a blanket of] wool;He scatters
        the frost like ashes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He casts out His ice like fragments;Who can stand before His cold?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He sends out His word and melts the ice;He causes His wind to blow
        and the waters to flow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He declares His word to Jacob,His statutes and His ordinances to
        Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: He has not dealt this way with any [other] nation;They have not known
        [understood, appreciated, heeded, or cherished] His ordinances.Praise the
        Lord! (Hallelujah!)
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 148The Whole Creation Invoked to Praise the Lord.'
      title: PSALM 148The Whole Creation Invoked to Praise the Lord.
      number: 1
      content: '  Praise the Lord!Praise the Lord from the heavens;Praise Him in
        the heights!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Praise Him, all His angels;Praise Him, all His hosts (armies)!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Praise Him, sun and moon:Praise Him, all stars of light!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Praise Him, highest heavens,And the waters above the heavens!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Let them praise the name of the Lord,For He commanded and they were
        created.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He has also established them forever and ever;He has made a decree
        which shall not pass away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Praise the Lord from the earth,Sea monsters and all deeps;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Lightning and hail, snow and fog;Stormy wind, fulfilling His orders;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Mountains and all hills;Fruitful trees and all cedars;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Beasts and all cattle;Creeping things and winged birds;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Kings of the earth and all people;Princes and all judges of the earth;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Both young men and virgins;Old men and children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Let them praise the name of the Lord,For His name alone is exalted
        and supreme;His glory and majesty are above earth and heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: He has lifted up a horn for His people [giving them strength, prosperity,
        dignity, and preeminence],Praise for all His godly ones;For the people of
        Israel, a people near to Him.Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 149Israel Invoked to Praise the Lord.'
      title: PSALM 149Israel Invoked to Praise the Lord.
      number: 1
      content: '  Praise the Lord!Sing to the Lord a new song,And praise Him in the
        congregation of His godly ones (believers).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Let Israel rejoice in their Maker;Let Zion\u2019s children rejoice
        in their King.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Let them praise His name with dancing;Let them sing praises to Him
        with the tambourine and lyre.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the Lord takes pleasure in His people;He will beautify the humble
        with salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Let the godly ones exult in glory;Let them sing for joy on their
        beds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Let the high praises of God be in their throats,And a two-edged sword
        in their hands,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'To execute vengeance on the nationsAnd punishment on the peoples,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'To bind their kings with chainsAnd their nobles with fetters of iron,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: To execute on them the judgment written.This is the honor for all
        His godly ones.Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PSALM 150A Psalm of Praise.'
      title: PSALM 150A Psalm of Praise.
      number: 1
      content: '  Praise the Lord!Praise God in His sanctuary;Praise Him in His mighty
        heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Praise Him for His mighty acts;Praise Him according to [the abundance
        of] His greatness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Praise Him with trumpet sound;Praise Him with harp and lyre.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Praise Him with tambourine and dancing;Praise Him with stringed instruments
        and flute.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Praise Him with resounding cymbals;Praise Him with loud cymbals.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Let everything that has breath and every breath of life praise the
        Lord!Praise the Lord! (Hallelujah!)
      comments: []
